<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="2CO" stage="Rev" version="C">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:49:47Z" when="2009-10-02 03:49:47Z" stage="Draft">1st draft by C. Grimes June 2006 based primarily on HCE; also NLT, AGNT, TW, ex. Summ.; C&amp;B Grimes, advisors; worked with team (June, Mus, Adriana) in Darwin Aug 2006, plus read-through pass with Barbara's comments; UNS check in Kupang, August 2006; BT by Chuck; Consultant check by Marge Crofts in Kupang 11-13 Sept 2006; final read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:53:48Z" when="2014-02-24 10:53:48Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 11-13 September 2006 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved. Report: KM-John-2Cor-ConsRep.doc; Adjustments to 2 Corinthians 8.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-16 07:41:01Z" when="2015-01-16 07:41:01Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read thru for Kupang mini-Bible done at UBB with Chuck, Lena, Rina. BackTrans also cleaned up a bit.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">2 Korintus</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Paulus pung surat kadua<bt>Paul's second letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">kasi orang parcaya di kota Korintus<bt>to the *believers in the city of Korintus</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">2 Korintus<bt>2 Korintus</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Salam<bt>Greetings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Ini surat dari beta, Paulus. Tuhan Allah su utus sang beta pi mana-mana ko kasi tau orang dong so'al Yesus Kristus, yang Tuhan su tunju memang dari dolu. Kotong pung adi Timotius ada di sini ju. Dia ada titip salam.<bt>This letter is from me, Paulus. God has sent/commissioned me to go all over the place to tell/explain to people about Yesus Kristus, whom God2 has designated beforehand from long ago. Our-inc younger sibling Timotius is also here. He sends greetings.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta tulis ini surat kasi samua orang parcaya yang biasa bakumpul di kota Korintus deng di propinsi Akaya.<bt>I write this letter to all believers who normally/customarily gather in the city of Korintus and the province of Akaya.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apostolos: apostle, messenger, commissioned one, envoy,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">apostolos: apostle, messenger, commissioned one, envoy, delegate thelema: will, purpose, aspiration, wish<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>Christóu Ieesóu: marked form, not the usual name Timótheos: even though Paul uses the plural a lot in this letter, he alternates it with "I" enough to make it clear that he does not consider Timothy a coauthor, but merely takes note of his being there and in agreement*<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>Most of the time "we" in 2 Corinthians is an epistolary plural. syn: focuses on Corinth, brings in Achaia secondarily*<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>ekklesia: church, congregation, assembly, gathering, meeting hagios: saint, holy ones, person consecrated to God, person set apart for God, person dedicated to God<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus through the will of God, and Timothy the brother, to the church of God which is in Corinth, with all the saints who are in all Achaia;</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:1</note><v n="2" />Beta sambayang sang Tuhan Allah, andia kotong pung Bapa, deng Yesus Kristus, andia kotong pung Bos. Beta minta ko Dong kasi tunju Dong pung hati bae sang bosong, ko biar bosong bisa idop aman, dame, deng tanáng.<bt>I pray to God, that is our-inc Father, and Yesus Kristus, that is our Bos. I request that They show Their goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you-pl, so that you can live safe (external peace), at peace (relationships), and calm (inner peace). [EXEG: 3 senses of peace; commentaries that want to restrict it to just the last sense haven't done their homework.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xaris: grace, favor, abundance of undeserved"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">xaris: grace, favor, abundance of undeserved gifts, divine favor bestowed on people eireénee: "As in the Old Testament, the word peace means more than an absence of war or peaceful feeling that a person may have. It refers to a total state of well-being that God gives to a person or a community." Peace, welfare, health, reconciliation. Used here in a way very similar to Hebrew shalom.*<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: grace to you and peace from God our father and the Lord Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah<bt>Paulus gives thanks to God</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Botong suka ko samua orang angka tinggi-tinggi sang Tuhan Allah pung nama. Te Dia tu, kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus pung Bapa. Samua rasa kasian ba'akar dari Dia, deng Dia yang suka kasi kuat kotong pung hati.<bt>We-exc want/desire for everyone to elevate on high the name/reputation of God. Cuz (elaboration) He is the Father of our-inc Bos Yesus Kristus. All mercy/pity is rooted/sourced in Him, and He is the one who likes to/often encourages our-inc livers. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eulogetos: blessed, thanks and adoration, praised"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">eulogetos: blessed, thanks and adoration, praised ho theòs kaì pateèr: might not need "God" in the same phrase as "Fadda", but it fits the Greek syntax better to have it.*<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>oiktirmos: mercy, compassion, pity pásees: on every occasion*<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>paraklesis: comfort, consolation, encouragement. Pidgin selects encouragement.* LITERALLY: Blessed be the God and father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the father/source of mercies and God of all encouragement,<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Dia yang kasi hibur sang kotong kalo kotong dapa susa. Andia ko kotong ju bisa kasi hibur orang laen yang dapa susa. Te kotong bisa kasi kuat dong pung hati, sama ke Tuhan ju su kasi kuat kotong pung hati.<bt>He is also the one who comforts us when we get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife. That is why we are also able to comfort other people who get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife. Cuz (elaboration) we are able to strengthen/encourage their livers, just like God2 has also strengthened/encouraged our livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thlipsis: (outward) tribulation, affliction, oppression, trial"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">thlipsis: (outward) tribulation, affliction, oppression, trial (strong) eis tò dýnasthai: can be purpose, more likely should be result because purpose sounds like he's manipulating us in order to help other people.*<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>dunamai: to be able, can LITERALLY: the one who comforts us in all our tribulation, so that we can comfort those in all tribulation, through the comfort by which we are comforted by God;<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Kristus su dapa susa bam-banya kasi sang kotong. Jadi, tagal Kristus su rasa susa bagitu macam, andia ko Dia pung Bapa kasi kuat kotong pung hati bam-banya, kalo kotong ada dapa susa.<bt>Kristus has also got/experienced a lot of trouble/difficulty/strife for us/on our behalf. So (consequently), because Kristus has experienced so many kinds of difficulty, that is why His Father strengthens/encourages our livers a lot, if/when we get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife. [EXEG: “sharing in His sufferings” NLT &amp; Ex. Summ.; NRSV tries to map Gk connectors with “just as A, so also B”; NLT uses “the more A, the more B”. Like CEV, we've undertranslated this so as not to force the RL.] [NOTE to daughter translations: check if your lg has a natural way to reflect the “just as A, so also B” relationship, without dismantling the hard work on reflecting the famously difficult “share in the sufferings of Christ”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kathoós: one thing sets the pattern"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kathoós: one thing sets the pattern for the other.* perisseuei: be present in abundance, be left over<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>pathema: suffering, misfortune diá + genitive: through, cuz Christ wen do dat<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>Q: Is the second part a natural consequence of the first part? Or what is the connection?* LITERALLY: that just as the sufferings of Christ are present in abundance for us, thus through Christ our comfort is present in abundance.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Kalo botong di sini dapa susa, Tuhan Allah kasi kuat botong pung hati. Deng kalo botong dapa susa, ais batahan deng hati bésar, na, bosong ju musti mangarti bilang, Tuhan ju pake jalan bagitu ko kasi kuat bosong pung hati, deng kasi lapás sang bosong dari yang jahat. Te kalo bosong dapa susa sama ke botong, Tuhan kasi kuat bosong pung hati, ko bosong ju bisa batahan deng hati bésar.<bt>If/when we-exc here get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife, God strengthens/encourages our-exc livers. And if/when we get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife, and/then endure/persevere with patience (Idiom: big livers), na, you-pl must understand that God2 also uses that way/means to strengthen/encourage your-pl livers, and release/save2/spare you from evil. Cuz (elaboration) if/when you get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife like us-exc, God2 strengthens/encourage your livers, so that you are also able to endure/persevere with patience (Idiom: big livers). [EXEG: HCE] [EXEG: we-exc = ??; in 1:1 mentions Timothy, but later also mentions Silas, may be others; considerable commentary discussion about “epistilary ‘we’”. Implied proposition in first part (resonating with second part): “and/then endure/persevere with patience (Idiom: big livers).” UNS's got stuck without it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Why narrowed to Tim &amp; me??"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Why narrowed to Tim &amp; me?? Implied proposition when we come through Deng kalo botong dapa susa, ais lolos/batahan dalam itu susa/batahan deng hati bésar, na, bosong ju musti mangarti, bilang, (Avoid the guy they don't like is in trouble (intro says they weren't on good terms.)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thlibw: suffer, distress, afflict swteria: deliverance,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">thlibw: suffer, distress, afflict swteria: deliverance, salvation<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>energew: experience, work hupomone: patience, endurance, fortitude, steadfastness, perseverance<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>pasxw: experience, be treated, endure éite ... éite: radically restructured, "afflicted" leads to "comforted" leads to "effect of both on you". We suffer and are helped; you suffer and are helped. The "if" doesn't imply any lack of certainty about whether God will encourage us.*<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: But whether [we are] suffering, [it is] for your comfort and salvation; whether [we are] comforted, [it is] for your comfort and endurance in patience of the sufferings which we endure.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo beta deng Timotius dapa susa,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Kalo beta deng Timotius dapa susa, Tuhan Allah kasi kuat botong pung hati. Bosong ju musti mangarti, bilang, Tuhan ju nanti kasi kuat bosong pung hati, deng kasi lapás sang bosong dari yang jahat. Te kalo bosong dapa susa sama ke botong, Tuhan kasi kuat bosong pung hati, ko bosong bisa batahan deng hati bésar.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Andia ko botong yakin bilang, bosong bisa batahan kuat deng sonde tagoyang. Te botong tau bilang, kalo bosong dapa susa sama ke botong, Tuhan ju kasi kuat bosong pung hati, deng Dia ju kasi kuat botong pung hati.<bt>That is why we are sure/confident that you-pl can endure strongly/firmly and not be shaken. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc know that if/when you get/experience trouble/difficulty/strife like us, God2 also strengthens/encourages your livers, and He also strengthens/encourages our livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="elpis: hope, expectation, prospect bebaios: reliable,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">elpis: hope, expectation, prospect bebaios: reliable, dependable, certain, steadfast<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>koinwnos: take part in together, share parakleéseoos: Pidgin switches to the more general "kokua". Otherwise the passage goes around in circles.*<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: And our hope concerning you is unshaken, knowing that as you share our sufferings, thus also our comfort.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Sodara dong! Botong pung mau ko bosong mangarti batúl so'al itu susa yang botong parná dapa di propinsi Asia. Botong rasa barát, lebe dari yang botong bisa pikol. Sampe-sampe botong mau ilang samangat, tagal botong pikir kata, botong su mau mati sa.<bt>Siblings! Our-exc desire if for you-pl to really understand about that trouble/difficulty which we once experienced in the province of Asia. We felt heavy (sad, depressed), more that we were able to shoulder carry. To the point that we were about to give up/despair/lose hope, because we thought that we were about to die.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thelw: wish, want, desire agvoew: be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">thelw: wish, want, desire agvoew: be ignorant, be uninformed<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>thlipsis: tribulation, affliction, hardship, trouble huperbole: excess, beyond measure, extraordinary, far beyond<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>dunamis: power, ability, strength barew: burden, weighed down, under great pressure<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>eksaporeethéenai: be in great difficulty, despair, be at a loss what to do, at wits' end* zaw: live<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: For we desire you not to be ignorant, brothers, concerning the hardship we went through in Asia, that far beyond our ability we were burdened, so that we despaired even of our life;</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 15:32</note><v n="9" />Botong sandiri rasa barát, sama ke satu orang baru dengar hakim putus hukuman mati kasi sang dia. Ma itu samua jadi, ko biar botong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, deng sonde parcaya sang botong pung diri. Te Tuhan tu, yang ada pung kuasa ko kasi idop kambali orang mati.<bt>We ourselves felt heavy (sad, depressed), like a person who has just heard the judge decide the death penalty for him. But all that happened, so that we-exc believed/trusted in God, anad did not believe in ourselves. Cuz (elaboration) God2 is the one who has the power/authority to bring dead people back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokrima: official report, judgment, sentence, verdict,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">apokrima: official report, judgment, sentence, verdict, warrant. The emphasis is on sure, officially sanctioned death, not just apprehension that we might die.* thanatos: death<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>exw: have pepoithotes: trust, place confidence in, rely on, depend on<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>egeirw: raise nekros: dead<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: But we in ourselves had a death sentence so that we might not trust in ourselves, but on God who raises the dead;</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Dia yang <span class="Italic">su</span> kasi lapás sang botong dari yang jahat, waktu botong amper mati. Nanti Dia ju <span class="Italic">mau</span> kasi lapás sang botong dari yang jahat. Botong tatáp baharap bilang, Dia nanti kasi lapás sang botong dari hal jahat <span class="Italic">tarús-tarús.</span><bt>He is the one who <span class="Italic">has</span> freed/saved us from evil when we were nearly dead. Later He also <span class="Italic">will</span> free/save us from evil. We continue to hope that He will later free/save us free evil things <span class="Italic">continually</span>.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="telikoutos: so great thanatos: death|i(10) (10)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">telikoutos: so great thanatos: death<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>hruomai: save, deliver, rescue, preserve elpizw: hope<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: He rescued us from so great a death, and he will deliver us, on whom we hope that he will even still deliver us,</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Kalo bosong sambayang tarús kasi sang botong, itu tolong sang botong ju, te Tuhan Allah mau bekin banya hal bae kasi botong. Dia mau bekin bagitu, tagal banya orang ada sambayang kasi sang botong. Ais waktu banya orang inga sang botong, nanti dong ju minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang Dia.<bt>If/when you keep praying for us-exc, that also helps us, cuz (elaboration) God is going to do many good things for us-exc. He wants to do that, because many people are praying for us-exc. So then when many people remember/think of us, they will also give many thanks to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunupourgew: cooperate with, help. The participle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">sunupourgew: cooperate with, help. The participle can be conditional, and that fits the Pidgin framework well. deesis: prayer<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>proswpon: face, presence, person xarisma: gift, gracious favor, help, blessing. Most commentators regard this as something God is going to do in the future, not something he has already done.<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>euxaristew: give thanks LITERALLY: as you help by your prayers for us, that many people will give thanks on our behalf for the favor given us through the prayers of many.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus susun rancana baru<bt>Paulus makes new plans</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Botong bisa omong bésar, tagal botong tau di botong pung dalam hati bilang, apa yang botong bekin di ini dunya, iko Tuhan pung mau kasi botong. Botong sonde ondor dari itu tugas, ko biar samua orang bisa lia botong ada karjá deng hati barisi. Botong ju kasi jalan botong pung karjá, pake pintar<bt>We-exc could boast/brag, because we know in our livers that what it is that we do in this world, is according to God2's will for us. We do not retreat/withdraw from that work/responsibility/mission, so that everyone can see we are working with clean/pure/holy livers (character &amp; motives). We also carry out our work, using the smarts/cleverness/wisdom</bt><note reference="1:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Paulus pung maksud di sini, andia &lt;pintar yang bekin orang pikir panjang, ko mangarti hal, iko Tuhan pung pandangan&gt;. Deng bagitu ini &lt;pintar&gt; ni, bukan cuma dari otak sa, ma dari hati ju.<bt>Paulus' intention here is ‘smarts/cleverness/wisdom that makes a person think long (through things), or understand things, according to God2's view’. In this way, this smarts/cleverness/wisdom, is not just from the brain/mind, but also from the liver.</bt></note>yang turun dari Tuhan Allah, bukan pake pintar yang ba'akar di ini dunya. Te Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang botong. Andia ko botong bisa karjá lebe karás lai waktu botong ada sama-sama deng bosong.<bt>which comes from God, not using the smarts/cleverness/wisdom that is rooted/source in this world. Cuz (elaboration) God2 shows His goodness/kindness/grace/generosity to us. That is why we are able to work even harder while we were together with you. [EXEG: HCE; Q: “We do not retreat/flee from that work/responsibility,” This does match something in the verse, doesn’t it? A: Sort of. Picking up on context from vs. 8 and trying to get at the sense of “sincerity” and “confidence”. It's also partly BT noise. It's how you describe doing something from pure motive without any doubts or second thoughts.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For our boasting is this:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For our boasting is this: the testimony of our conscience, that in the integrity and sincerity of God, and not in worldly/selfish wisdom, but by the grace of God, we behaved in the world, but more toward you. haútee: marked, refers to what follows.<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>kauxnsis: boasting. "Proud" in its positive sense in Pidgin refers to something you had a hand in bringing about; "brag" or "talk big" implies more that one is less involved, more of a bystander, and may be hyping as well. marturion: testimony<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>suneidesis: conscience haplotes: frankness, sincerity, integrity, singleness of mind; or as an adjective frank, open, honest, above board. Honesty or integrity of conduct is what needs to come through here.<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>[The alternate reading "hagiotes" for holiness, moral purity, would be a weak reason for the "we do um fo him" type of rendering.] eilikrinei: sincerity, purity of motive, transparency.<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>sophia: wisdom, how a person applies what he knows sarkikos: fleshly, worldly, earthly, self-interest, expedient<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>xaris: favor, grace, gift, gracious influence avastrephw: live, behave, act, conduct oneself<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>kosmos: world perissoterws: more<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Beta cuma tulis kasi bosong so'al hal-hal yang bosong bisa baca deng mangarti. Sakarang bosong su mangarti beta pung maksud saparu. Ma beta baharap, nanti bosong bisa mangarti lebe langkáp lai.<bt>I only write to you-pl about matters/issues that you can read and understand. Now you already understand some/part of my purpose. But I hope later you will be able to understand even more completely/fully.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="graphw: write anaginwskw: read, recognize|i(13) (13)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">graphw: write anaginwskw: read, recognize<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>epivinwskw: know, understand, acknowledge elpizw: hope, hope for<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>telos: end, to the end, to the last, fully epigivwskw: know, understand, acknowledge<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: For we write to you nothing but what you read or understand, but I hope that you will understand fully,</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Sakarang bosong baru mangarti sadiki sa so'al botong. Ma nanti, kalo kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus su datang kambali, na, beta yakin bosong su mangarti banya. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa omong bésar so'al botong, sama ke botong ju omong bésar so'al bosong.<bt>Now you-pl are just (beginning to) understand a little about us-exc. But later, if/when our-inc Bos Yesus Kristus has already come back, na, I am sure/confident that you will already understand a lot. In that way, you will be able to boast about us-exc, just like we also boast about you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apò mérous: conversational hedge? omitted* kauxema:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">apò mérous: conversational hedge? omitted* kauxema: boast, object of boasting, object of pride<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>kathaper: just as LITERALLY: just as you understand in part, that we may boast of you just as you of us in the day of the Lord Jesus.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Tagal beta yakin bosong mangarti ini hal dong, andia ko dolu, beta parná putus ko mau pi lia ulang lai sang bosong, ko biar bosong bisa dapa berkat dua kali.<bt>Because I was sure that you-pl understand these things, that is why previously, I had once decided to go see/check up on you again, so that you could get a blessing two times. [EXEG: restored missing “I was so sure/confident of your understanding and trust”, NIV, NLT, CR Amarasi 2014] [NOTE to daughter translations: avoid ambiguity: two times (volume of blessing) vs. two times (times seeing you)--the latter is what is intended here Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pepoithesis: trust, confidence, absolute confidence in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pepoithesis: trust, confidence, absolute confidence in men boulomai: desire, will, want, decision of the will after previous deliberation, decide<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>elthéin: Paul wasn't in Corinth when he wrote this, so his thinking was "I goin go," not "I goin come" proteron: earlier, beforehand, previously (time adverb); goes better with eboulómeen than with elthéin<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>deuteros: second, double (here as adjective). As he explains in the next verse, he was setting up his travel plans so that instead of seeing them just once, he would see them two times, and be a benefit to them each time* xaris: favor, goodwill, gracious deed, gift, benefit<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: And I decided in this confidence first to come to you, that you may have a second benefit,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, beta su putus ko mau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Ais, beta su putus ko mau susun rancana, ko pi lia ulang lai sang bosong, ko biar bosong dapa berkat dua kali.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Jadi dolu beta ada pikir, kalo beta jadi pi propinsi Makedonia, na, beta bisa singga lia sang bosong. Ais kalo beta pulang dari Makedonia, beta bisa singga di bosong ulang lai. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa tolong bantu beta, ko beta bisa jalan tarús pi propinsi Yudea.<bt>So (consequently), previously I was thinking if it worked out for me to go to the province of Makedonia, na, I could stop in and see you. Then when I came back from Makedonia, I could stop in and see you again. In that way, you could help me, so I could continue travelling on to the province of Yudea. [EXEG: Scholars say 2 Cor was written from Macedonia, so this verse doesn't fit that, unless he is referring to a plan at an earlier time that was later changed. The key is the Gk /proteron/ in vs.15, which indicates “my earlier plan, I had been planning...but”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dierkhomai: go through erkhomai: go|i(16) (16)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">dierkhomai: go through erkhomai: go<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>propempoo: accompany, help on a journey, send me on my way, escort; in this case it was probably to help with his expenses LITERALLY: and by you to go into Macedonia, and again from Macedonia to come to you, and to be helped by you on my journey into Judea.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, beta pung pikir bagini: nanti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Jadi, beta pung pikir bagini: nanti kalo beta pi di propinsi Makedonia, beta bisa singga lia sang bosong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 19:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ma karmana lai? Tiap kali beta kasi tau bilang, beta kapingin datang lia sang bosong, mangkali bosong kira, beta tunda-tunda tarús, ko? Ko, bosong kira beta cuma putus hal iko beta pung mau sandiri sa, sama ke orang laen di ini dunya, ko? Ko, bosong kira beta orang yang muka-balakang, yang suka bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo.&gt;&gt; Padahal dalam beta pung hati, beta ada pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde mungkin!&gt;&gt; Mangkali bosong ada pikir beta ni, model bagitu, to?<bt>But how about it? Each time I tell (you) that I desire to come see you, perhaps/probably you-pl think/assume I keep delaying, or (what)? Or, you think/assume that I only decide things according to my own desires/wishes, like other people in this world, or (what)? Or, you think/assume I am a fickle person (idiom: a front-back person), who likes to say, “Hoo. (=yes, affirmation)” Whereas in fact in my liver, I am thinking, “Not likely/no way!” Perhaps/probably you are thinking that I'm a person of that sort, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="boulomai: desire, will, want meti: perhaps,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">boulomai: desire, will, want meti: perhaps, not<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>ara: then elaphria: vacillation, levity, fickle, lightness in reference to the mind, playing games, inconstancy, changeableness, no serious intention<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>xraomai: use, act, proceed bouleuw: decide, purpose, plan<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>sarks: body, flesh, worldly, self LITERALLY: Did I therefore proceed with fickleness, desiring this? Or the things which I decide, do I decide them according to the flesh, that I say &lt;&lt;yes, yes&gt;&gt; and &lt;&lt;no, no&gt;&gt; at the same time?<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mangkali bosong kira, tiap kali beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Mangkali bosong kira, tiap kali beta kasi tau, bilang, beta kapingin datang lia sang bosong, beta tunda-tunda tarús, ko? Ko,</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Kotong bisa parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, te kalo Dia omong satu hal, na, pasti Dia bekin iko. Andia ko botong ju bagitu. Kalo botong omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo,&gt;&gt; na, botong sonde pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde.&gt;&gt;<bt>We-inc can believe/trust in God, cuz (elaboration) if He says one thing, na, surely He will do accordingly. That is why we-exc are also like that. If/when we speak saying, “Hoo,” na, we don't think, “No.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pistis: faithful, trustworthy, dependable logos: word,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pistis: faithful, trustworthy, dependable logos: word, doctrine, plans<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: But God is faithful, that our word to you is not &lt;&lt;Yes&gt;&gt; and &lt;&lt;No.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Beta, Silas, deng Timotius su ajar sang bosong so'al Yesus Kristus, Tuhan Allah pung Ana. Dia bukan orang muka-balakang yang omong &lt;&lt;hoo&gt;&gt;, ma maksud &lt;&lt;sonde&gt;&gt;. Dia ju sonde tagoyang, te kalo Dia omong &lt;&lt;hoo&gt;&gt;, Dia pung maksud batúl-batúl &lt;&lt;hoo&gt;&gt;.<bt>I, Silas, and Timotius have taught you-pl about Yesus Kristus, God's Child. He is not a fickle (front-back) person who says “hoo”, but means “no”. He also is not shaken/doesn't waver, cuz (elaboration) if He says “hoo”, His meaning really is “hoo”.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kerussw: announce, preach, proclaim aloud givomai:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kerussw: announce, preach, proclaim aloud givomai: be, become<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: For the Son of God, Jesus Christ, who was preached among you by us, by me, and Silas, and Timothy, was not &lt;&lt;Yes&gt;&gt; and &lt;&lt;No,&gt;&gt; but it has been &lt;&lt;Yes&gt;&gt; in him.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:5</note><v n="20" />Samua hal yang Tuhan Allah su janji, Dia nanti bekin jadi. Andia ko, kalo Yesus janji satu hal bilang, &lt;&lt;hoo,&gt;&gt; kotong bisa manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl. Andia tu! Amin!&gt;&gt; Tagal botong su tau memang apa yang Yesus mau bekin. Botong kasi tau ini hal ko kasi tunju Tuhan Allah pung hebat.<bt>Everything that God has promised, He will make happen. That is why if/when Yesus promises something saying, “hoo,” we can respond saying, “That's right. That's the way it is! Amin!” Because, we-exc already know beforehand what Yesus is going to do. We tell these things to show God's greatness/amazingness. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hosai: as many as epaggelia: promise,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hosai: as many as epaggelia: promise, announcement, pledge, offer<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>dio therefore dià + genitive in marked position: through, cuz a wat Jesus Christ wen do. Our verbal response does not just reflect understanding; if Jesus hadn't done what he did, we would have nothing at all to say*<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>doksas: glory LITERALLY: For all the promises of God in him [Jesus] are &lt;&lt;Yes&gt;&gt;; and therefore through him the &lt;&lt;Amen&gt;&gt; to the glory of God through us.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Tuhan tu, yang su pili ame sang bosong deng botong. Dia yang angka sang kotong ko jadi Dia pung orang. Dia ju yang bekin kotong batahan tarús.<bt>God2 is the one who chose/selected you-pl and us-exc. He is the one who elevates/appoints us-inc to be His people. He is also the one who makes us-inc keep on enduring/persevering. [EXEG: HCE, NLT; 1st two sentences covering ‘anointed’, and the presupposed (chosen) that is necessarily implied for the anointed to work in context, and obligated by RL discourse (ellipted proposition).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bebaiow: establish, make firm, steadfast eis"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">bebaiow: establish, make firm, steadfast eis Khriston: Christ's people.<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>khrísas: anoint. In what sense? Like chrism? LITERALLY: But the one who establishes us with you into Christ, and anoints us, is God,<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-05-23 07:23:06Z">; 1st two sentences</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Dia yang kasi Dia pung Roh ko ator sang kotong, deng kasi tunju Dia pung rancana kasi kotong. Itu sama ke satu orang taro dia pung cap di satu barang ko kasi tau bilang, itu dia pung harta milik.<bt>He is the one who gave His Spirit to oversee/organise/control us-inc, and show His plans to us. That is like like a person places/puts his stamp/brand on some thing (physical) to show that it is his possession. [NOTE: because of UNS reponses, we needed to unmix topic and image of metaphor.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="to show ownership ; itu sama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">to show ownership ; itu sama ke satu orang taro dia pung cap di satu barang ko kasi tau, bilang, itu dia pung harta milik [unmix topic and image of metahpor]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sphragizw: seal, mark, ownership and protection"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">sphragizw: seal, mark, ownership and protection didwmi: give<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>arrabwn: down payment, guarantee, deposit, pledge, assurance pneuma: spirit<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>kardia: heart LITERALLY: the one who marks us and gives us the assurance of the Spirit in our hearts.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu sama ke Dia su taro"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Itu sama ke Dia su taro Dia pung cap di kotong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Beta ada minta ko Tuhan sandiri yang jadi saksi di beta pung omong ni. Te Dia tau beta pung dalam hati. Dia tau kanapa beta balóm jadi pi kota Korintus. Beta sonde mau bekin bosong jadi malu, andia ko beta balóm pi sana.<bt>I am requesting that God2 himself is the one who is witness to what I say here. Cuz (elaboration) He knows my inner liver (core being). He knows why it has not yet worked out for me to go to the city of Korintus. I don't want to make you ashamed/embarrassed, so that is why I have not yet gone there (remote).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin bosong jadi malu (indirect) /"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">bekin bosong jadi malu (indirect) / bekin malu sang bosong (direct, deliberate)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="martus: witness, testimony epikalew: call upon,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">martus: witness, testimony epikalew: call upon, call as a witness, call on my behalf<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>psuxe: soul, life pheidomai: spare, not punish<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>ouketi not yet, no longer erxomai: come<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>LITERALLY: But I call upon God as a witness upon my soul, that to spare you, I did not come to Corinth yet.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Botong sonde angka-angka diri jadi bos ko suru-suru sang bosong bilang, bosong musti parcaya sang sapa. Ma botong ada karjá sama-sama deng bosong, ko biar bosong pung hati bisa babunga. Te bosong bisa batahan kuat, tagal bosong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>We-exc do not keep elevating ourselves as bosses who keep ordering you-pl around saying, who you must believe/trust in. But we are working together with you, so that your livers can be happy/glad. Cuz (elaboration) we can stand/endure firmly, because we believe/trust in God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kurieuw: rule, be master over, lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kurieuw: rule, be master over, lord it over pistis: faith<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>suvergos: working with xapa: joy<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>histemi: stand, stand firm LITERALLY: not that we lord it over your faith, but we work with you for your joy, for by faith you stand firm.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi beta sandiri yang su putus bilang, beta balóm mau pi lia sang bosong, ko biar samua orang sonde usa hati barát.<bt>So (consequently) I myself am the one who has decided that I am not yet going to see you, so that everyone doesn't have to be heavy livered (sad, apprehensive, depressed).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krivw: decide, determine, make up my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">krivw: decide, determine, make up my mind, intend, propose emautw: myself<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>lypee: grief, sorrow, heaviness, sad, pain, distress, affliction. Though grief at bereavement and remorse are included in Greek "lypee", the Pidgin word for intense personal grief at bereavement, and sometimes remorse, "sore inside", is too personal for this context. So "sad" covers this area better in Pidgin. LX. elthein: come<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: For I decided this for myself, not to come to you again in sorrow;</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te kalo beta bekin bosong hati barát, na, sapa lai yang nanti bekin beta pung hati sanáng? Cuma bosong sa. Ma kalo beta datang sakarang, beta bekin bosong hati susa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if/when I make your livers heavy, na, who else will make my liver happy? Only just you-pl. But if I came now, I would make your livers troubled/strife. [DISCOURSE: higher-level context, and Hughes.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euphrainw: make glad, make happy, cheer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">euphrainw: make glad, make happy, cheer up, give joy, give pleasure lupew: grieve<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: for if I make you sad, who is the one who will make me glad, except the one whom I have made sad?</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Andia ko beta tulis surat baru-baru tu bilang, beta balóm jadi pi bosong. Beta masi tunggu tahan, ko biar bosong urus abis bosong pung parkara dolo. Ais kalo nanti beta jadi datang, na, beta sonde usa rasa barát tagal bosong pung parkara dong. Te yang batúl, bosong tu, yang bekin beta pung hati sanáng. Beta kanál sang bosong samua. Jadi beta yakin, kalo beta pung hati sanáng, na, bosong pung hati ju sanáng bagitu.<bt>That is why i wrote my recent letter saying, it had not yet worked out for me to go to you-pl. I'm still waiting temporarily, so that you (can) finish handling/taking care of your issues/matters/disputes first. Then if/when it works out for me to come, na, I don't need to feel heavy (sad, apprehensive) about your issues. Cuz (elaboration ) in truth, you-pl there are the ones who make my liver happy. I know/recognise all of you. So (consequently) I am sure/confident that if my liver is happy, na, your livers will also be happy like that. [NOTE: generally accepted that this other letter is NOT 1 Cor. see UBS TH “translating 2 Cor.” and Ex. Summ.; HCE, linking to context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Paul is leaving half of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">Paul is leaving half of the connections implicit. He's saying "If things go on as they have been, it will be bummers for everybody. Clean up your act; then we'll all be happy." tóuto autó: the same content he has just expressed.*<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>ekhw: have dei: it is necessary<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>khairein: rejoice peithw: convince<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>khara: joy LITERALLY: and I wrote this same thing, so that when I come I would not have sorrow from the ones who ought to make me rejoice, but having confidence in you all that my joy comes from all of you.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Waktu beta tulis itu surat kasi bosong baru-baru tu, beta rasa susa deng hati barát. Beta ju manangis bam-banya. Ma beta tulis bagitu, ko biar bosong bisa mangarti beta pung sayang sang bosong. Te beta sonde tulis itu hal ko bekin bosong rasa susa.<bt>When I wrote that letter to you recently, I felt troubled and heavy livered. I also wept a lot. But I wrote like that so that you-pl could understand my love for you. Cuz (elaboration) I didn't write those things to make you feel disturbed/troubled.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@reorder chronologically. purpose before result"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">@@reorder chronologically. purpose before result</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ek: circumstances* polus: many|i(4) (4) |rthlipsis:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ek: circumstances* polus: many<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>thlipsis: tribulation, affliction, oppression, trouble sunokhe: distress, anguish, dismay, pressure, anxiety, unhappy<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>kardia: heart dakruon: tear<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>lupew: grieve, make sad, feel hurt, cause pain agape: love<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>ginwskw: know perissoterws: more, abundant, especially, very much<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: For from much affliction and anguish of heart I wrote to you, through many tears, not in order that you might be grieved, but so that you might know the love I have abundantly for you.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu beta tulis itu surat kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Waktu beta tulis itu surat kasi bosong baru-baru tu, beta rasa susa deng hati barát. Beta ju manangis bam-banya. Ma beta sonde tulis itu hal ko bekin bosong rasa susa. Te beta tulis bagitu, ko biar bosong bisa mangarti beta pung sayang sang bosong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lupa buang orang pung sala<bt>Forgive (completely forget) people's wrongs</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(1 Korintus 5:1-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Di bosong pung jama'at situ, ada satu orang yang bekin banya orang pung hati susa. Beta ju iko susa tagal itu orang pung bekin. Padahal dia pung bekin-bekin tu, memang sonde talalu kaná di beta, ma itu lebe banya kaná di bosong saparu.<bt>In your congregation there, there is one person who has made many people's livers troubled. I also share the difficulty because of what that person has done. Whereas in fact, his doings really don't effect me too much, but they effect some of you a lot. [NOTE to daughter translations: even though Corinth is far/remote from Paul, in Indo the convention for addressing those receiving a letter is ‘situ’ rather than ‘sana’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ei: implies that this is an"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ei: implies that this is an actual happening, not a possibility -- "since" rather than "if".* lupew: grieve, cause grief, cause sorrow, make sad, cause distress<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>meros: in part, to some degree, to some extent, in some measure apò mérous: what the person did affected part of the group more than the rest; Paul is trying not to make it sound like it was a disaster for everybody, and it certainly wasn't for him*<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>epibarew: burden, press down, be hard on, put it too severely, exaggerate, overstate the case* LITERALLY: But if anyone has caused grief [=since there is someone who has caused grief], he has not caused grief to me, but in part, so that I may not press too hard, to you all.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bukan kasi bosong samua, ma kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Bukan kasi bosong samua, ma kasi bosong saparu.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Beta sonde usa omong banya lai. Te banya dari bosong su togor sang dia, ais dia su barenti.<bt>I don't need to say much more. Cuz (elaboration) many of you have scolded him, and he has already stopped.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hikanon: sufficient, enough, adequate, satisfies the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hikanon: sufficient, enough, adequate, satisfies the requirements toioutos: of such a kind, such as this, such a one<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>epitimia: reprimand, penalty, reproof. Here it is not physical punishment or beating. It was probably social pressure, not having anything to do with him. Furthermore, it's clear that it achieved the desired effect.* pleiónoon: sounds like they held a meeting and the punishment was decided on by the majority*; same as each other<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: His reprimand by the majority is enough for such a person,</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Jadi sakarang bosong musti lupa buang dia pung sala, ais bosong musti omong bae-bae deng dia. Te jang sampe dia ilang samangat.<bt>So (consequently) now you must completely forget (forgive) his wrong, and you must speak nicely with him. Lest he give up/lose heart.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hwste: therefore, so that enantion: before|i(7)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hwste: therefore, so that enantion: before<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>mallon: rather, instead xarizw: give freely, give favor, forgive, pardon, remit<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>parakalew: comfort, encourage, put heart into, cheer up me pws: lest somehow, lest perhaps<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>perissoteros: greater, excessive lupe: grief, sorrow, remorse, misery<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>katapinw: swallow, drink down, be overwhelmed, be engulfed toioutos: such a one<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: therefore instead forgive and comfort him, lest excessive sorrow overwhelms such a one.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Andia ko beta minta ko bosong bakumpul sama-sama, ko kasi yakin sang dia bilang, bosong ada sayang sang dia.<bt>That's why I request that you-pl gather together, so assure him that you live him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dio: wherefore, for this reason, so"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">dio: wherefore, for this reason, so parakalew: implore, beg, appeal to, exhort, encourage<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>kurow: confirm, reaffirm, ratify, conclude, decide in favor of, make valid; sounds like they are supposed to take the same kind of official action that they took when they imposed sanctions, but now in the opposite direction* agape: love<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: For this reason I appeal to you to confirm your love for him;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Beta tulis beta pung surat baru-baru tu, ko mau uji sang bosong. Te beta mau tau, kalo bosong ada bekin yang batúl, deng bekin iko samua yang beta parenta sang bosong.<bt>I wrote my recent letter to test you. Cuz (elaboration) I wanted to know whether you were doing what is right/correct, and doing according to everything that I have commanded you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eis tóuto gàr kaì: I had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">eis tóuto gàr kaì: I had an additional reason for doing what I did dokime: quality of being approved, put someone to the test, character<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>hupekoos: obedient, more likely to Paul, since it's his personal authority that is on the line in both epistles.* LITERALLY: for this reason I also wrote, so that I may put you to the test, if you are obedient in all things.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Kalo bosong sonde simpan hati lai, deng lupa buang orang pung sala, na, beta ju iko apa yang bosong su putus. Kalo ada dia pung sala yang parlú beta lupa, na, beta ju lupa buang itu orang pung sala. Beta bekin bagitu di Kristus pung muka, ko jadi conto yang bae kasi bosong.<bt>If you don't store liver (=hate resentment) anymore, and completely forget (forgive) a person's wrong/sin, na, I will also go along with what you have decided. If there is a wrong (of his) that needs to be forgotten/forgiven, na, I will also forgive that person's wrong. I do that before Kristus, to be a good example for you-pl. [MC “example” from higher level context and purpose.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kharizomai: give freely, grant a favor,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kharizomai: give freely, grant a favor, forgive kagw: I also (marked)<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>kaì gàr egoò: (marked) eí ti kekhárismai: if indeed there was something for me to forgive, to the extent that I have had anything to forgive. Paul isn't sure the offence touched him deeply enough to need his forgiveness, but he's glad to go along with the others on it.*<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>proswpon: face, in the presence of LITERALLY: Anyone whom you forgive, I also; and what I have forgiven, if I have forgiven anything, for your sake in Christ's presence,<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Te beta sonde suka setan dong pung bos hiki ame sang kotong, ko, kasi kala sang kotong. Kotong musti mangarti dia pung rancana kotor dong. Jadi jang bodo-bodo, é!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I don't like the boss of the evil spirits to ensnare/trap us-inc, or, cause us defeat. We must undersand his dirty/scheming/nasty plans. So (consequently) don't be stupid, é!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pleonektew: outwit, outsmart, gain the advantage"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pleonektew: outwit, outsmart, gain the advantage over, take advantage of Satanaa: da Devil<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>noemata: designs, purposes, devices, wiles, plots, schemes agnoew: be ignorant, not to know<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: in order that we may not be outwitted by Satan, for we are not ignorant of his designs.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus pung hati sonde tanáng di Troas<bt>Paulus' liver wasn't at peace/calm in Troas</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dolu waktu beta pi kota Troas, ko ajar orang so'al Kristus pung Kabar Bae tu, Tuhan buka jalan kasi beta di sana.<bt>Previously when I went to the city of Troas, to teach people about Kristus' Good News, God2 opened the way for me there (remote).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thura: door anoígoo: open.|i(12) (12) |rLITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">thura: door anoígoo: open.<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: But coming into Troas to preach the Gospel of Christ, a door was opened for me in the Lord,</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ma beta pung hati sonde tanáng, tagal beta sonde katumu beta pung sodara Titus di sana. Ais beta minta diri sang orang parcaya di Troas dong, ju barangkat pi propinsi Makedonia.<bt>But my liver wasn't at peace/calm, because I didn't meet my sibling Titus there. So I took my leave from the believers in Troas, and left for the province of Makedonia.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Titus was supposed to be there."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">Titus was supposed to be there. anesis: rest<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>heuriskw: find -- Titus hadn't shown up by the time Paul got to Troas.* apotassw: say farewell<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>ekserkhomai: go out LITERALLY: I did not have rest in my spirit, not finding Titus my brother, but saying farewell to them, I went out into Macedonia.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 20:1</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus yang bekin kotong manáng<bt>Kristus is the one who makes us win</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma biar beta ada di mana sa, beta minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang Tuhan Allah. Te Kristus su baparáng lawan hal jahat dong, ais Dia su manáng, deng kotong ju ta'ika deng Dia. Andia ko Tuhan Allah kasi tunju tarús bilang, kotong ni, Dia pung orang. Jadi waktu kotong kasi tau orang so'al Kristus, itu sama ke satu bau wangi yang samua orang dapa ciom ame.<bt>But no matter where I am, I give many thanks to God. Cuz (elaboration) Kristus has warred/battled opposing evil things/matters/issues, and He has already won, and we-inc are also bound/linked to Him. That is why God keep showing that we-inc are His people. So (consequently), when we tell people about Kristus, that is like an aromatic fragrance that everyone can smell.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The point Paul is making is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">The point Paul is making is that whether he is in Corinth or Troas or Macedonia, he is delighted because he is having a positive influence in letting people know about God. Otherwise verses 12 and 13 have no contextual ties* kharis: favor, grace, gift, thanks<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>pantote: always thriambeuw: lead in a triumphal procession, triumph over. This metaphor has to do with winning a war, and holding a victory parade with both soldiers and prisoners in it - here it doesn't say what our role is directly. It doesn't support "God like da peopo all ova da place fo know Christ, an he send us fo tell um", which is implied instead by the last part of the verse<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>osmee: fragrance, odor gnwsis: knowledge<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>phanerow: reveal, show, manifest topos: place<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: But thanks to God who always leads us in triumph in Christ, and the fragrance of the knowledge of him is shown through us in every place;</Message></Annotation><v n="15-16" />Dolu waktu orang Yahudi bekin korban bakar, dia pung bau asap nae pi Tuhan ko bekin sanáng Dia pung hati. Kotong ju sama ke satu bau wangi yang kasi inga sang Tuhan so'al Kristus. Ma kasi orang saparu, kotong sama ke satu bau busuk. Te kalo orang yang idop jao dari Tuhan ada lia kotong pung idop, itu bekin dong pikir-pikir bilang, dong nanti mati, deng dong tapisa buang dari Tuhan. Ma kasi orang saparu lai, kotong sama ke satu bau wangi. Te kalo orang yang dapa idop batúl, ada lia kotong pung idop, itu bekin dong inga karmana Kristus su kasi salamat sang dong, deng kasi dong idop yang sonde tau putus-putus. Manusia sapa yang mampu bekin ini hal dong samua? Sonde ada, to?<bt>Previously when Yahudi people made a *burnt sacrifice, the smell of its smoke ascended to God2 to make His liver happy. We are also like a fragrant smell that reminds God2 about Kristus. But to some people, we are like a foul smell. Cuz (elaboration). if/when a person who lives far from God2 sees our-inc lives, that makes them keep thinking that they will die and they will be separated off/cut off from God2. But to some other people, we are like a fragrant smell. Cuz (elaboration) if/when a person who has real life sees our lives, that makes them remember how Kristus has *saved them, and given them life that never ends. What human is able to do all this? There is none, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euwdia: sweet smell, fragrance, aroma. This"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">euwdia: sweet smell, fragrance, aroma. This is mentioned frequently in the Old Testament in connection with sacrifices. swzw: save<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>apollumi: perish LITERALLY: that we are the fragrance of Christ to God among those who are saved and those who are perishing,<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>thanatos: death zwe: life<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>hikanos: sufficient, adequate, enough LITERALLY: Indeed to those who are of death a fragrance toward death, to those who are of life a fragrance toward life. And who is sufficient for these things?<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>Q: Would the chiasm between verses 15 and 16 be clearer as a parallelism?*</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te kalo orang yang mau idop"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Te kalo orang yang mau idop jao dari Tuhan lia kotong pung idop, itu bekin dong pikir-pikir, nanti dong mati, ais dong tapisa tarús dari Tuhan. Ma kalo orang yang nanti dapa idop batúl ada lia sang kotong, itu bekin dong pikir/inga karmana Kristus su kasi salamat sang dong, ju kasi dong idop yang sonde putus-putus. Kasi orang saparu, kotong sama ke satu bau wangi. Ma kasi orang saparu lai, kotong sama ke satu bau busuk. Te kalo orang yang idop jao dari Tuhan ada lia kotong pung idop, itu bekin dong pikir-pikir, bilang, dong nanti mati, deng dong tapisa tarús dari Tuhan. Ma kalo orang yang dapa idop batúl, ada lia kotong pung idop, itu bekin dong inga karmana Kristus su kasi salamat sang dong, deng kasi dong idop yang sonde tau putus-putus. Manusia sapa yang mampu bekin ini hal dong samua? Sonde ada, to?<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Inga, te botong ni, sonde sama ke orang laen yang cuma ajar Tuhan pung Kata-kata ko biar dong cari ontong, sama ke dong ada badagang pake Tuhan pung Kata-kata. Sonde! Kalo botong ada omong, samua orang bisa lia taráng-taráng bilang, botong ada ajar deng hati barisi. Botong pung omong ba'akar dari Tuhan Allah. Deng botong pung idop ada ta'ika deng Kristus.<bt>Keep in mind that we are not the same as other people who only teach God2's Words/Message so that they can seek profit/benefit, like they are doing commerce using God2's Words/Message. No! If/when we-exc are speaking, everyone can see clearly/openly that we are teaching with clean/pure livers. What we say is rooted in God. And our lives are bound/linked with Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="2 UNS not know papalele"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">2 UNS not know papalele</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="polus: many kapeleuw: peddle, sell for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">polus: many kapeleuw: peddle, sell for money<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>logos: word eilikrineia: sincerity<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>katevanti: in the sight of lalew: speak<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: for we are not as the many who peddle the word of God, but as from sincerity, but we speak as from God in the sight of God in Christ.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cari ontong, sama ke orang papalele"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">cari ontong, sama ke orang papalele</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung orang yang kasi jalan Janji Baru<bt>God2's people who carry out the New Promise</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Jang kira bilang, botong ada mulai bamulu bésar, ko, angka-angka botong pung diri. Sonde! Kira-kira botong sama ke orang laen yang parlú bawa surat rekomendasi kasi bosong, baru bisa kasi jalan botong pung karjá, ko? Ko, botong parlú minta surat rekomendasi dari bosong ko bawa pi orang laen? Sonde, to?<bt>Don't think that we-exc are beginning to boast (be big mouthed), or elevate ourselves. No! Perhaps (you think) we are like other people who need to bring a letter of recommendation to you-pl, before (we) can start carrying out our work, or (what)? Or, (that) we need to request a letter of recommendation from you to take to other people? No, right? [NOTE to daughter translations: surat rekomendasi is not a surat izin. It is a surat ko minta bosong tarima bae deng kasi tunju hormat sang itu orang.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="arxomai: begin sunistemi: present, introduce, recommend"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">arxomai: begin sunistemi: present, introduce, recommend someone, commend<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>xreéizomen: need sustatikos: introducing, commendatory, recommendation; letter of introduction*<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>hoós tines: indefinite, not singling out particular people, hence "da odda guys" says too much; "get peopo" is looser.* as some do: persons who came to Corinth from somewhere else with letters of recommendation from recognized authorities, and who are opposed to Paul. May be the same ones as in 2:7 and 10:2. Would it be clearer as a statement than a question? (see UBS commentary p. 54, and alternate above)*<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: Are we beginning again to commend ourselves? Or do we need, as some do, letters of recommendation to you or from you?</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te botong pung surat rekomendasi su ada. Itu surat tu, andia bosong sandiri. Te botong kanál banya hal so'al bosong pung idop. Itu hal dong su tasimpan di botong pung hati. Samua orang bisa baca bosong pung idop; dari situ dong kanál botong pung hasil karjá.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) our letter of recommendation already exists. That letter is you yourselves. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc know/recognise many things about your lives. Those things are stored away in our livers. Everyone can read your lives; from there they know/recognise the results of our-exc work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hyméis: emphatic position. Anybody who knows"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hyméis: emphatic position. Anybody who knows about you automatically knows what kind of people we are.* ginooskoménee kaì anaginooskoménee: a play on words in Greek that probably can't be reproduced in Pidgin*<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: Our letter is you, written on our hearts, known and read by all men;</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te su jalás bilang, bosong sama ke satu surat yang Kristus su tulis. Ais Dia titip di botong. Kristus sonde pake tinta ko tulis itu surat, ma Dia pake Tuhan yang Idop pung Roh Barisi. Kristus ju sonde ukir Dia pung Kata-kata di batu plat, macam ke yang Tuhan su bekin kasi sang Musa. Ma Dia tulis di kotong pung hati yang idop.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it's clear that you are like a letter that Kristus has written. And He entrusted it to us-exc. Kristus did not use ink to write that letter, but He used the *Holy Spirit of the God who Lives. Kristus also did not carve His Words/Message in flat stones, like God2 had done for Musa. But He wrote (it) in/on our-inc livers that live.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phaneroúmenoi: reveal, show. The middle-passive form"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">phaneroúmenoi: reveal, show. The middle-passive form probably means "you are shown to be" or "you show yourselves to be" = "it is clear that you are", rather than "you demonstrate", which would be phaneróuntes.* diakovew: minister, sent by, delivered<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>melas: black, ink plaks: flat stone, and its counterpart in the human spirit*<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>lithinos: made of stone sarkinos: fleshy, living and beating heart*<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: showing that you are a letter from Christ, delivered by us, written not with ink but by the Spirit of the living God, not on flat stones but on fleshy heart tablets.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais Dia titip sang botong, ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Ais Dia titip sang botong, ko botong yang bawa Dia pung pasán.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 24:12, Yeremia 31:33, Yeskial 11:19, 36:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Botong yakin bilang, botong bisa parcaya sang Tuhan bilang, ini hal dong samua memang batúl, tagal Kristus yang su kasi tunju bagitu.<bt>We-exc are sure/confident that we can believe God that all these things really are true, because Kristus is the one who has shown that. [EXEG: Gk /pros theon/ was undertranslated in OV; CR Amarasi 2014]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pepoithesis: trus, confidence, certainty toioutos: such"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pepoithesis: trus, confidence, certainty toioutos: such a kind, referring to verses 2 and 3*<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>"we" is Paul and friends, not the Corinthians* LITERALLY: And we have such a confidence through Christ toward God.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Kalo cuma dari botong pung diri sandiri sa, na, botong sonde ada pung kuasa ko bisa bekin apa-apa. Te kuasa deng hak yang ada di botong ni, ba'akar di Tuhan Allah.<bt>If it were only from we ourselves, na, we have no power/authority to do anything. Cuz (elaboration) the power/authority and rights that we have, are rooted/sourced in God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hikanos: sufficient, competent, qualified, able, worthy,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hikanos: sufficient, competent, qualified, able, worthy, fit, can* logizomai: consider, think about, ponder<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: Not that by ourselves we are qualified to consider anything as from ourselves, but our qualification is from God,</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Tuhan tu, yang su angka sang botong jadi Dia pung orang karjá yang kasi tau orang so'al Dia pung Janji Baru. Ma Dia pung Janji Baru tu, bukan so'al orang cuma bekin iko atoran macam-macam, ma so'al orang ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh Barisi. Kalo orang cuma bekin iko atoran buta-buta sa, itu sama ke dong su mati di dong pung hati, deng sonde dapa idop yang batúl, yang sonde tau putus-putus. Ma kalo orang idop ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh, dia dapa itu idop yang batúl.<bt>God2 is the one who elevated/appointed us-exc to be His workers to tell people about His New Promise. But that New Promise of His, is not about people only doing according to/just obeying various regulations/rules, but about people bound/linked with God2's Holy Spirit. If a person just blindly follows regulations, that is like they are already dead in their livers, and don't have/get real life that never ends. But if a person lives bound/linked with God2's Spirit, he gets/obtains that real life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hikanow: qualify diakonos: servant, minister|i(6) (6)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hikanow: qualify diakonos: servant, minister<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>kainos: new diatheke: covenant, decree, arrangement.<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>apokteinw: kill zooiopoiéi: make alive, give life to. An active verb.*<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: who has qualified us ministers of a new arrangement, not of the letter but of the Spirit; for the letter kills, but the Spirit makes alive.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 31:31</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dolu waktu Tuhan ukir Dia pung Atoran di batu plat dong, itu memang hebat. Ma biar orang bekin iko itu Atoran dong samua, dong nanti masi tapisa buang dari Tuhan Allah. Ais waktu Musa su tarima ame itu Atoran dong, dia pung muka bacaya talalu hebat. Andia ko orang Isra'el dong sonde bisa lia dia pung muka. Ma lama-lama ju, itu cahaya ilang.<bt>Previously when God2 carved His Regulations/Law on the flat stones, that really was incredible/amazing. [EXEG: Gk: glory here 12x in vs. 7-13] But even if a person does according to/obeys all those Regulations/Law, they will still be separated off from God. So/then when Musa had received that Regulations/Law, his face shone too amazing. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] That is why the people of Isra'el were not able to look at his face. But eventually, that radiance/light disappeared/dissipated.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cahaya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">cahaya</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diakonia: ministry, service. Here it refers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">diakonia: ministry, service. Here it refers to the Law of Moses.* thanatos: death, in genitive characterized by, associated [how?] with death*<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>gramma: letter entupow: carve<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>lithos: stone givomai be, become<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>dokse: glory, splendor dunamai: can, be able<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>atevizw: look intently at, behold proswpon: face<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>katargew: cease, pass away, abolish LITERALLY: But if the ministry of death in letters carved in stone was in glory, so that the children of Israel could not look into Moses' face, which glory of his face was fading,<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 34:29</note><v n="8" />Jadi kalo yang tatulis di batu bisa jadi hebat bagitu, na, karmana deng apa yang Tuhan pung Roh su taro dalam kotong pung hati? Pasti lebe hebat lai, to?<bt>So (consequently), if what is written in stone can be so amazing/incredible like that, [EXEG: Gk: glory here] na, how about with what God2's Spirit has place in our-inc livers? Surely that is even greater/more impressive, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: how shall not the ministry"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: how shall not the ministry of the spirit be more glorious?</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Naa, itu Atoran kasi tunju bilang, kotong musti dapa hukuman mati ko tapisa buang dari Tuhan, tagal kotong sonde bekin iko itu Atoran dong samua. Biar bagitu, ma itu Atoran masi tatáp hebat ju. Ma Tuhan pung Roh lebe hebat lai, te Dia kasi tunju jalan ko kotong bisa babae kambali deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>Naa [shift], those Regulations/Law showed that we-inc must get the punishment of death to be separated off/cut off from God2, because we do not do according to all those Regulations. Even that being the case, nevertheless those Regulations/Law remains amazing. But God2's Spirit is even more amazing, [EXEG: Gk: glory here] cuz (elaboration) He has shown the way so we-inc can be restored to a good relationship again with God. [EXEG: “ministry of condemnation” Ex. Summ. CEV. And suggested by CR.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katakrisis: condemnation perissew: be abundant, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">katakrisis: condemnation perissew: be abundant, be left over, exceed<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>dikaiosune: righteousness LITERALLY: For if the ministry of condemnation is glorious, much more the ministry of righteousness will be abundantly glorious.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Jadi itu Atoran yang dolu orang anggap hebat, sakarang su sonde bagitu hebat lai, te sakarang su ada yang lebe hebat.<bt>So (consequently), those Regulations/Law that people used to think were great, now are not so great/impressive anymore, cuz (elaboration) now there is something that is even more impressive. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doksazw: glorify meros: part, point, respect,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">doksazw: glorify meros: part, point, respect, matter, affair<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>heineken: on account of huperballw: surpass, excel<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: For that which had glory does not have glory in this respect on account of the surpassing glory;</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Naa, itu Atoran dong pung hebat, sama ke ba'i Musa pung muka, yang bacaya dolu, ais baru dia pung cahaya ilang. Musa deng itu Atoran masi hebat, ma yang lebe hebat lai, andia yang pung hebat batahan tarús sonde putus-putus.<bt>Naa, those Regulations/Law's greatness, is like Gf/Ff (historical figure) Musa's face, which shone previously, and then later its radiance disappered. Musa and those Regulations/Law are still great/impressive, but what is more impressive is the one/thing whose greatness keeps on enduring/sustaining forever. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katargew: abolish. Used here of fading"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">katargew: abolish. Used here of fading splendor, linking back to Verse 7.* menw: remain<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: for if that which is abolished has glory, much more that which remains has glory.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Botong samua yakin bilang, Tuhan pung Janji Baru mau batahan tarús, sonde putus-putus. Andia ko botong ba'omong taráng-taráng, sonde pake pele-pele.<bt>We-exc are all sure/confident that God2's New Promise is going to endure on, without end. That is why we are speaking clearly/openly, without restraint/holding back.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exw: have toioutos: such a kind|i(12)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">exw: have toioutos: such a kind<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>elpis: hope parresia: outspokenness, frankness, plainness<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>xraomai: use LITERALLY: Therefore having such hope we use great frankness,<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Botong sonde usa bekin sama ke ba'i Musa. Te dia musti tutu dia pung muka pake kaen, ko biar orang Isra'el dong sonde bisa lia kalo itu cahaya su ilang.<bt>We don't need to do the same as Gf/Ff Musa. Cuz (elaboration) he had to cover his face using a cloth, so that the people of Isra'el couldn't see if/whether that radiance had gone/disappeared.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kathaper: just as tithemi: put|i(13) (13)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kathaper: just as tithemi: put<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>kalumma: covering, veil proswron: face<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>atevizw: look intently at telos: end<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>katargew: abolish, fade. Not feminine, referring to glory, but neuter, referring to the old covenant, as in Verse 11* LITERALLY: not like Moses put a cover over his face, so the children of Israel would not see the end of that which faded.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 34:33-35</note><v n="14" />Ma Tuhan Allah bekin orang Isra'el dong otak tumpul. Te sampe sakarang ju, kalo dong ada baca di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi so'al Dia pung Janji Lama tu, itu sama ke ada satu kaen yang tutu ame dong pung kapala, ko dong sonde mau dengar, deng sonde mau mangarti. Sonde ada orang laen lai yang bisa buka dong pung hati ko dong bisa mangarti. Cuma Kristus sandiri sa.<bt>But God made/caused the people of Isra'el to be dull brained. Cuz (elaboration) to this day, if/when they are reading in the *Scriptures about His Old Promise, that is like there is a cloth that covers their head, so they don't want to listen, and don't want to understand. There is nobody else who is able to open/uncover their livers to they can understand. Only just Kristus alone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epooroóthee: hardened. Not &quot;dey get hard"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">epooroóthee: hardened. Not "dey get hard head" but "dey wen come hard head" or "God make um come hard head". Their thought processes were dulled, not just made stubborn (which would be epooroóthee hee kardía)* noema: thought, mind; thought processes*<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>axri: until semeron: today<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>hemeras: day kalumma: covering<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>avagvwsis: reading palais: old<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>diatheke: covenant menw: remain<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>avakaluptw: uncover katargew: abolish, fade<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: But their minds were hardened. For [beginning from/to] this very day the covering remains upon the reading of the old covenant. It is not uncovered, because in Christ it is abolished;</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Sampe sakarang ju, kalo orang Yahudi dong baca ba'i Musa pung tulisan, dong dengar, ma dong sonde mangarti batúl. Itu, tagal dong sonde dengar pake dong pung hati, sama ke ada yang tutu ame dong pung hati.<bt>To this day also, if/when Yahudi people read Gf/Ff Musa's writings, they hear/listen, but they don't really understand. That is because they are not listening with their livers, like there is something that is covering up their livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hews: until semeron::|i(15) (15) |rhenika an:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hews: until semeron::<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>henika an: whenever. Needs to match heeníka eàn in the next verse, so "weneva" fits better than "everytime" for both parts* anagivwskw read:<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>kalumma: covering keitai: lie, stay<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: but until today whenever Moses is read a covering stay upon their hearts;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ma kalo ada orang yang mulai parcaya sang kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, na, Kristus buka itu orang pung hati ko biar dong bisa mangarti batúl-batúl. Itu sama ke ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia su buka itu kaen yang ada tutu dia pung muka.&gt;&gt;<bt>But if/when there is a person who begins to believe in our-inc Bos Yesus Kristus, na, Kristus opens/uncovers that person's liver so that they can truly understand. That is like what is written in the Scriptures saying, “He has opened/uncovered that cloth that is covering/hiding his face.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kálymma: in this case, a reference"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kálymma: in this case, a reference back to Moses, who when he was dealing with the people, had to cover his face, but when he was dealing with God, he took off the veil: Ex 34:34.* LITERALLY: But whenever anyone turns to the Lord, "the veil is taken away."<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 34:34</note><v n="17" />Naa, dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi, waktu ba'i Musa omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos&gt;&gt;, dia pung maksud Tuhan Allah pung Roh. Kalo kotong dapa itu Roh, na, Dia bekin kotong jadi bebas.<bt>Naa, in the Scriptures, when Gf/Ff Musa spoke saying, “Bos”, he was meaning God's Spirit. If/when we-inc get that Spirit, na, He makes us become free. [EXEG: freedom from what? what is this freedom? (UNS); Ex. Summ shows commentaries are all over the place on this--so we keep it broad if we can get reasonable responses on this. Implicit to explicit because UNSs had no background to make sense of it. We tried to build it to the minimal level to where they could make some sense of the passage and give it cohesion. Support for vs 16 to include a quote. (EH) And that in turn justifies the reference to Moses in vs 17.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now the Lord is the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now the Lord is the Spirit, and where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is freedom.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Deng bagitu, Dia bekin kotong tamba hari tamba hebat, sama ke Dia. Kotong pung muka sonde usa kaná tutu. Deng kotong bapikir tarús so'al kotong pung Bos pung hebat, te Dia pung Roh ada tolong sang kotong bagitu.<bt>In that way, He makes us become increasingly great/impressive/amazing, like Him. Our-inc faces don't need to be covered. And we keep thinking about our Bos's greatness/impressiveness, cuz (elaboration) His Spirit is helping us like that. [EXEG: Gk: glory here 2x]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heeméis: emphatic* avakaluptw: uncover|i(18) (18) |rkatoptrizw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">heeméis: emphatic* avakaluptw: uncover<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>katoptrizw: take a long look at, contemplate; also reflect as in a mirror* eikwn: form, idol, image<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>metamorphow: transform, change katháper apò kyríou pneúmatos: precisely what you would expect from a Lord who is Spirit by nature*<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: But we all, with uncovered face, looking at the glory of the Lord, we are being changed from glory to glory, just as by the Spirit of the Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Barang mahal yang tasimpan dalam pareu tana<bt>Valuable/expensive things that are stored in a clay pot</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju rasa kasian sang botong. Andia ko Dia su utus sang botong ko kasi tau orang so'al Dia pung Janji Baru. Andia ko botong batahan tarús, deng sonde ilang samangat.<bt>God has shown His mercy/pity to us-exc. That is why He has sent/commissioned us to tell people about His New Promise. That is why we keep persevering/enduring, and don't give up/lose heart.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pareu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">pareu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diakonia: service, ministry, 3:6 eleew: have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">diakonia: service, ministry, 3:6 eleew: have mercy<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>egkakow: despair, lose heart, be disheartened, faint-hearted, discouraged; UBS show fear* LITERALLY: Because of this, having this ministry, just as we have been shown mercy, we do not give up,<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Jadi dari dolu botong su putus bagini: botong su kasi tau taráng-taráng bilang, botong sonde mau bekin hal-hal jahat, sama ke orang laen dong. Dong suka bekin sambunyi-sambunyi, ko biar orang sonde bisa lia. Deng dong ju sonde tau malu. Ma botong sonde mau putar-balek deng orang. Botong ju sonde omong kosong so'al Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata, ma botong ajar taráng-taráng apa yang batúl. Deng bagitu, samua orang bisa pareksa sandiri botong pung omong di Tuhan pung muka, ais nilei sandiri botong ni, manusia macam apa.<bt>So (consequently) from long ago we-exc have deicded like this: we have told/explained clearly/openly that we to not want to/are not going to do evil things, like other people. They like to do (things/them) in secret, so people can't see (them). And they also have/know no shame. But we-exc don't want to deceive people. We also don't lie/b.s. about God's Words/Message, but we teach clearly/openly what is true. In that way, everyone is able to examine for themselves what we are saying before God, and assess/evaluate for themselves what sort of humans we are. [EXEG: what does “before God” modify? Ex. Summ strong on it modifying “we commend ourselves”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apeipeipámetha: disown, renounce, spurn, scorn with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">apeipeipámetha: disown, renounce, spurn, scorn with aversion; repudiate. The time is a problem--best not to imply a sequence (with "wen"), but a policy. The situation was that Paul had early on made a decision never to do certain things, and he had followed that decision.* kryptos: hidden, secret, concealed<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>aisxune: shame, disgrace, scandalous peripatew: go about, practice, live conduct oneself<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>panourgíaai: cunning, craftiness, trickery, shrewdness, unscrupulousness, deception* dolow: falsify, tamper with<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>phanerwsis: announcement, open statement, proclamation, disclosure sunistemi: unite, commend<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>suneidesis: conscience enoópion tóu theóu: goes with synistánontes. God is our witness, he knows what we are up to*<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: but we renounced the hidden things of shame, not going around in trickery, not falsifying the word of God, but by proclamation of the truth commending ourselves to every person's conscience before God.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Kalo orang sonde mau mangarti Tuhan pung Kabar Bae yang botong ajar tu, dong nanti ancor, te dong tapisa dari Tuhan.<bt>If people don't want to understand God2's Good News that we-exc teach, they will (eventually, in the end) be come to ruin/things fall apart, cuz (elaboration) they are separated off/cut off from God2. [EXEG: Gk ‘perishing’ is present participle, so removed ‘will’ from OV, and reduced serial verb construction to shift aspect from accomplishment/result to activity/process (ongoing). CR Amarasi 2014]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kekalymménon: hide, cover, veil. Doesn't imply"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kekalymménon: hide, cover, veil. Doesn't imply that they are dumb (which "no can undastan" might), but more likely, unwilling to deal with the message, as in chapter 3.* apollumi: perish<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: But if our gospel is hidden, it is hidden to those who are perishing,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Setan dong pung bos tu, sama ke satu tuhan yang orang dong ada sémba sakarang. Dia bekin orang saparu dong pung otak jadi tumpul, sama ke dong su jadi buta di dong pung hati. Dong tu, orang yang sonde parcaya sang kotong pung Tuhan Allah yang batúl. Tagal dong buta bagitu, itu sama ke dong sonde bisa lia Tuhan Allah pung taráng. Andia ko dong sonde bisa mangarti Kabar Bae so'al Kristus. Dong ju sonde mangarti Kristus pung hebat. Te Kristus tu, satu model deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>The boss of the evil spirits is like a god (tuhan) who people are worshipping now. He makes some people's brains become dull, like they have become blind in their livers. They are people who don't believe in our-inc true/real God. Because they are blind like that, it is like they ae not able to see God's light. That is why they are not able to understand the Good News about Kristus. They also don't understand Kristus' greatness/amazingness. Cuz (elaboration) Kristus is the same model/type/kind as God. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [NOTE: because of ‘tuhan’ above, not change to pronoun Dia in middle.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tuphlow: to blind noema: mind, thought|i(4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">tuphlow: to blind noema: mind, thought<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>apistos: faithless, unbelieving eis tò meé: result OK, but could be purpose*<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>augazw: shine forth phwtismos: illumination<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>eikwn: image, likeness LITERALLY: among whom the god of this age has blinded the minds of the unbelievers so the illumination of the glorious gospel of Christ, who is the image of God would not shine on them.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Botong sonde omong banya, so'al botong pung diri. Ma botong omong banya, so'al Yesus Kristus, kotong pung Bos. Yang botong omong so'al botong pung diri cuma ini sa: andia, botong bekin diri sama ke orang suru-suru ko layani sang bosong, tagal botong jadi Yesus pung orang.<bt>We-exc don't say a lot about ourselves. But we talk a lot about Yesus Kristus, our Bos. What we say about ourselves is just this: we make ourselves like a servant to serve you, because we are Yesus' people. [NOTE: target lg requirement; can't say the Bos, must be possessed “our Bos”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doúlous: focuses more on the permanency"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">doúlous: focuses more on the permanency of the binding relationship than on the idea that the relationship is involuntary* LITERALLY: For we do not preach ourselves but Jesus Christ the Lord, and ourselves your servants for Jesus sake.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Dolu-dolu, Tuhan Allah yang parná omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Musti ada taráng yang bacaya di tampa galáp.&gt;&gt; Ais Dia bekin Dia pung taráng ko basinar dalam kotong pung hati. Te Dia suka kasi Dia pung taráng sang kotong. Itu, dia pung arti bilang, waktu kotong ada pikir so'al Kristus, kotong ju ada inga Tuhan Allah pung hebat.<bt>Long ago, God once said, “There must be light which shines in the dark place.” So then He made His light to shine into our-inc livers. Cuz (elaboration) He likes to give His light to us. That means that when we-inc are thinking about Kristus, we are also remembering God's greatness/amazingness. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Beta bekin taráng bacaya kaluar dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">&lt;&lt;Beta bekin taráng bacaya kaluar dari tampa galáp.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bacaya = broad, general ; basinar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">bacaya = broad, general ; basinar = directed, transitive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skotos: darkness; ek not the same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">skotos: darkness; ek not the same as en. phws: light<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>lámpsei: shine; this isn't a future tense that says what's going to happen; it's a pronouncement that causes it to happen* phwtismos: illumination<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>gnwsis: knowledge Ieesóus: textual evidence about fifty-fifty<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: Because God is the one who said, "Out of darkness the light will shine", who has shined in our hearts to the illumination of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Christ.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 1:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Biar botong ni, cuma manusia biasa sa, ma Tuhan su taro ini barang mahal dalam botong pung hati. Itu sama ke satu orang su simpan dia pung barang mahal dalam pareu tana. Barang mahal ni, andia Tuhan pung taráng. Su jalás bilang, kuasa yang hebat yang ada di botong, sonde ba'akar di botong, ma ba'akar di Tuhan Allah.<bt>Even though we-exc are only normal humans, nevertheless God2 has put/placed this valuable/expensive thing in our livers. That is like a person has stored away his expensive/valualable things in a clay pot. The expensive/valuable thing, is God2's light. It's clear that the amazing power/authority that we have, is not rooted/sourced in us-exc, but is rooted/sourced in God. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. Inc-Exc in NT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dè: unexpected; &quot;treasure in clay pots&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">dè: unexpected; "treasure in clay pots" would have been an instant oxymoron to a person in that culture thesauron: treasure<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>ostrakinos: made of earth; for today's culture, the ordinariness is more important than the exact material*. Clay bowls: reference to human bodies, ordinary, fragile, weak (2 Tim. 2:20) UBS. skeuos: thing<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>huperbole: excess, extraordinary quality dunamis: power<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: But we have this treasure in earthen things, that the excellence of the power might be of God and not of us;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma kotong ada pung barang mahal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Ma kotong ada pung barang mahal dari Tuhan dalam kotong pung hati, biar kotong ni, cuma manusia biasa sa. Itu kasi tunju, bilang, kuasa bésar ada ba'akar di Tuhan Allah. Itu kuasa sonde ba'akar di kotong. Itu sama ke satu orang su simpan dia pung barang mahal dalam pareu tana.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Jadi, biar orang tendes bekin susa sang botong di mana-mana, ma botong batahan tarús sa. Biar botong sonde mangarti samua, ma botong ju sonde ilang samangat.<bt>So (consequently) even if/though people press/oppress causing difficulty for us-exc all over the place, nevertheless we-exc keep on enduring/persevering. Even though we don't understand everything, nevertheless we also don't give up/lose heart.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thlibw: oppress, afflict, be distressed, under"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">thlibw: oppress, afflict, be distressed, under pressure stenoxwrew: cramp, crush, in hopeless condition (external, not mental)<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>aporew: uncertain, perplexed, without means or resources, in doubt eksaporew: be in great difficulty, extremely perplexed<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: in everything being oppressed, but not crushed, uncertain but not [at a loss,/ in despair]</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Biar orang bekin susa bam-banya sang botong, ma Tuhan Allah sonde kasi tenga sang botong sandiri-sandiri. Biar orang hantam sang botong, ma dong sonde bisa kasi ancor buang sang botong.<bt>Even though people csuse us-exc lots of difficulty/trouble, nevertheless God does not abandon us to be on our own. Even though people beat/attack/abuse us, nevertheless they are not able to completely ruin/destroy us-exc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diwkw: persecute, persue egkataleipw: forsake, desert,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">diwkw: persecute, persue egkataleipw: forsake, desert, abandon<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>kataballw: throw down, strike down apolluw: destroy<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: persecuted but not abandoned, thrown down but not destroyed,</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Tagal botong su kaná siksa macam-macam, botong pi mana, na, botong bisa kasi inga sang orang bilang, Yesus ju kaná siksa bam-banya waktu Dia mati. Te biar orang hantam macam-macam sang botong, ma botong idop tarús. Itu ju kasi inga bilang, Yesus ada idop tarús dalam botong pung diri.<bt>Because we-exc have experienced so much/kinds of persecution/torture, wherever we go, na, we can remind people that Yesus also experienced so much/kinds of persecution/torture when He died. Cuz (elaboration) even though people beat/attack/abuse us, nevertheless we keep living. That also reminds us that Yesus is living on in our selves/beings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pantote: always nekrwsis: death, dying|i(10) (10)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pantote: always nekrwsis: death, dying<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>peripherw: carry around, carry here and there, bear about zwe: life<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>phanerow: reveal, show, manifest, demonstrate, become visible LITERALLY: always carrying around the death of Jesus in our bodies, that the life of Jesus may be seen in our bodies.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Batúl! Su banya kali, botong yang idop ni, amper mati, tagal botong jadi Yesus pung orang. Deng bagitu, samua orang bisa tau bilang, Yesus ada kasi botong idop yang batúl, biar botong nanti mati.<bt>That's right! Several times, we-exc who are living now, nearly died, because we were Yesus' people. In that way, everyone can know that Yesus is giving us real life, even if later we die.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="c.m. = cari muka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">c.m. = cari muka</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aei: always paradidwmi: give over|i(11) (11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">aei: always paradidwmi: give over<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>thnetos: mortal LITERALLY: For we who live are always being given over to death through Jesus, that the life of Jesus may be shown in our mortal flesh.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Jadi biar dia pung ahir tu, botong mati, ma botong sonde taku ba'omong so'al Kristus. Te botong sadia mati bagitu, ko biar bosong bisa dapa idop yang batúl.<bt>So (consequently), even if in the end we die, nevertheless we are not afraid to talk about Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) we are prepared to die like that, so that you-pl can get/obtain real life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hwste: therefore energew: work, work in."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hwste: therefore energew: work, work in. This is putting our lives on the line, not wasting away gradually. It's like what firemen and policemen do, and their willingness to stick their necks out is expressed by "no scared fo ..., no matta can mahke cuz a dat."<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>dè: some commentators take it is result, not just contrast* LITERALLY: Therefore death is at work in us, but life in you.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada yang tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal beta parcaya sang Tuhan, andia ko beta omong.&gt;&gt; Botong pung pikiran, ju sama. Tagal botong parcaya sang Tuhan, andia ko botong musti omong kasi tau orang so'al Dia.<bt>In the Scriptures it is written saying, “Because I believe in God2, that is why I speak.” Our-exc thoughts are also the same. Because we believe in God2, that is why we must speak (out) telling people about Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pisteuw: believe, trust lalew: speak|i(13) (13)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pisteuw: believe, trust lalew: speak<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>katà: UBS suggests that since it's an attributable quotation, it shouldn't be "Da Bible say"* LITERALLY: Having the same spirit of faith, just as it has been written, "I believed, therefore I spoke," we also believe, therefore we also speak.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 116:10</note><v n="14" />Botong tau bilang, Tuhan Allah yang kasi idop kambali sang kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus dari Dia pung mati. Dia ju yang nanti kasi idop kambali sang kotong, tagal kotong ta'ika deng Yesus. Nanti Tuhan kasi badiri sang kotong samua di Dia pung muka, ko Dia tarima ame sang kotong.<bt>We-exc know that God is the one who brought back to life our-inc Bos Yesus Kristus from His death. He is also the one who will bring us-inc back to life, because we are bound/linked with Yesus. Later God2 will stand us all in front of Him, to receive us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eidotes: knowing, being confident egeirw: raise|i(14)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">eidotes: knowing, being confident egeirw: raise<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>paristemi: bring before, present [?] LITERALLY: knowing that the one who raised the Lord Jesus will also raise us with Jesus and present us with you.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Tuhan bekin ini hal dong samua ko tolong sang bosong. Dia ju mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang orang dong, yang tamba hari tamba banya. Nanti dong ju minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang Dia. Ais dong ju mangaku Dia pung hebat.<bt>God2 does all these things to help you-pl. He is also going to show His goodness/kindness/ grace/ generosity to people, who increase in quantity over time. Later they will also give many thanks to Him. So/then, they will also acknowledge/confess His greatness/amazingness. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: Q: Does this include the idea that “more and more people will come to Christ” (as per Neva Miller)? A: that is certainly included in the meaning of the Gk, but I think the Gk and the intention are much broader than just that (see complexities in Ex. Summ. for many meanings of “grace having extended”.) Our protocols say that if we can reflect the range of (acceptable) possibilities of the Gk without forcing a narrower reading, then we need to do that.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xapis: grace, favor, gift, goodwill pleonazw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">xapis: grace, favor, gift, goodwill pleonazw: increase<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>pleionwn: euxaristia: thankfulness<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>perisseuw: be abundant, be left over, abound doksa: glory, splendor, fame<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: For all these things are for you, that the increasing grace may be abundant through the thankfulness of multitudes, to the glory of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong parcaya tarús sang Tuhan<bt>We-inc keep on believing in God2</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Andia ko kotong batahan tarús, deng sonde ilang samangat. Biar kotong pung badan dong jadi rusak, ma Tuhan Allah bekin kotong pung hati batamba kuat tiap hari.<bt>That is why we-inc keep on enduring/persevering, and do not give up/lose heart. Even though our bodies break down/decay, nevertheless God makes our livers gain/grow in strength each day. [EXEG: NRSV, CEV, TB, and ES all put a section break here, between vs.15-16.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="turun-turun = shrivel"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">turun-turun = shrivel</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egkakew: despair, lose heart eksw: outside,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">egkakew: despair, lose heart eksw: outside, outer<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>diaphtheirw: spoil, be destroyed, decay, waste away, wear out, grow weak with age MC esw: inside, inner<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>anakainóutai: renew, renovated, invigorated, strengthened. Focus is on the process* LITERALLY: Therefore we do not lose heart, but even if our outer person is decaying, our inner person is being renewed day by day.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Te iko kotong pung pikir, sakarang kotong ada kaná susa macam-macam. Ma kotong musti inga bilang, nanti Tuhan mau angka tinggi-tinggi sang kotong. Andia ko kotong anggap apa yang jadi sakarang, sonde ada pung arti apa-apa!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) according to our thinking, now we are experiencing various sorts of troubles/difficulties. But we must remember that later God2 is going to *glorify (elevate way up high) us. That is why we consider/view what is happening now, as having no meaning/significance at all! [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [NOTE: “according to our thinking” is not an addition, but is linking this verse into the context of vs.4:16-5:1 and helps clarify the attitudinal contrast of “slight” with the eternal reality, as hinted at by NLT, CEV, and HCE. It's talking about perspective.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parautika: momentary, immediately, on the spot,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">parautika: momentary, immediately, on the spot, for the present elaphros: light, slight, easy to bear, insignificant. LXX sounds dismissive.<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>thlipsis: tribulation, trouble, affliction huperbole: excess, beyond comparison, extraordinary quality<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>aiwnios: eternal baros: fulness, weight, high degree. Need to highlight the superlative effect. Not the ordinary way to talk about glory*<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>doksa: glory katergazomai: prepare, achieve, bring about<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: For our slight, momentary trouble, prepares for us a degree of eternal glory beyond comparison.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Jadi kotong musti lia hal-hal yang sonde kantara dong ju. Jang cuma lia yang kantara sa. Te hal-hal yang ada kantara ni, sonde batahan lama. Ma hal-hal yang sonde kantara tu, dong yang nanti batahan tarús deng sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>So (consequently), we must see things that are not visible/obvious. Don't just see things that are visible/obvious. Cuz (elaboration) things that are visible now, don't endure/last long. But the things that are not visible, they are what later will endure/last long forever/without end.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skopew: notice, look for, see blepw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">skopew: notice, look for, see blepw: see<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>proskairos: temporary, transient, last only for a time, fleeting LITERALLY: not looking at the things which are seen but the things which are not seen; for the things which are seen are temporary, but the things which are not seen are eternal.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Te kotong tau, kotong pung badan yang sakarang, kotong pake tahan di ini dunya, sama ke satu tenda yang kotong ada kasi badiri tahan. Biar kotong pung badan nanti ancor buang, ma kotong sonde usa pikiran, tagal Tuhan Allah su sadia satu tampa yang bagus kasi kotong di sorga. Manusia sonde bekin itu tampa. Ma Tuhan yang bekin, ais itu tampa batahan tarús.<bt>Cuz we-inc know our bodies (that we have) now, we use/wear temporarily in this world, like a tent that we have erected temporarily. Even though our bodies will later be destroyed/come to ruin/fall apart, nevertheless we don't need to worry, because God has already prepared a beautiful place for us in the heaven. Humans did not make that place. But God2 is the one who made it, so that place will keep on lasting.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oida: know, perceive epigeios: earthly, on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">oida: know, perceive epigeios: earthly, on the earth, belonging to the earth<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>oikia: house skeenous: tent, temporary dwelling place<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>kataluw: destroy, demolish, tear down, pull down oikodome: building<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>axeiropoietos: not made by hand aiwnios: eternal<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>ouravos: heaven LITERALLY: For we know that even if our earthly tent-house [body] is destroyed, we have a building from God, an eternal house in heaven, not made with hands.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te kotong su cape deng kotong pung badan sakarang di ini dunya. Deng kotong rindu mau dapa badan baru yang kotong nanti pake di sorga.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we are already tired with the bodies we have now in this world. And we yearn to get new bodies that we will use later in heaven. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stenazw: sigh, groan (not from pain,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">stenazw: sigh, groan (not from pain, but from wanting a good thing.) oiketerion: dwelling with someone living inside<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>to ex ouranou: source, not location. UBS doesn't clarify it. "comes from heaven" sounds right, but I'm not sure why the ex (from) is there--Joe. UBS suggests it is because of the mixed metaphor of clothes and house ependuomai: put on<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>epipothew: desire something, long for LITERALLY: For we also groan about this, desiring to put on our heavenly dwelling,<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais nanti kalo kotong su sampe di sana, itu sama ke kotong sonde talanjang, ma pake pakean baru.<bt>So later when we have arrived there, it's like we won't be naked, but will be wearing new clothes.</bt><note reference="5:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada tulisan Yunani yang tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;pake pakean&gt;&gt;. Ma ada saparu ju yang tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;buka pakean&gt;&gt;.<bt>There are Yunani language writings that write saying, “wear/put on clothes”. But there are also some that write saying, “take off clothes”.</bt></note>Te kotong bukan cuma jadi roh sa, ma kotong dapa badan baru di sana.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc are not only just spirit, but we will get new bodies there. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gar (for): purpose of having a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">gar (for): purpose of having a heavenly dwelling, with mixed metaphors*. enduw: put on, wear, dress, clothe<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>gumnos: bare, uncovered, naked heuriskw: find, appear<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: if indeed being clothed, we will not be found naked.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Kotong pung badan yang rusak sakarang, bekin kotong hela napas panjang, tagal rasa barát. Biar bagitu, ma kotong sonde mau mati ais sonde ada pung badan apa-apa lai. Sonde! Kotong mau dapa kotong pung badan baru, ko biar kasi tenga badan lama dong, ganti deng idop baru yang batúl.<bt>Our bodies that are spoiling/out of order/not functioning properly down now, make us draw a long breath, because we feel heavy (sad/discouraged). Even that being the case, nevertheless we don't want to die and then not have any body anymore. No! We want to get our new bodies, so that we can leave behind our old bodies, replacing them with new life that is true/real. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skeenos: tent; clashes with the &quot;clothing&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">skeenos: tent; clashes with the "clothing" metaphor in the next sentence. stenazw: sigh, groan (because of undesirable circumstances)<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>barew: burden, weigh down, oppressed thelw: desire<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>ekduw: take off, undress, strip, become unclothed ependuomai: dress, put on, clothe<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>katapinw: swallow, absorbed by (emphasizes completeness) thnetos: mortal<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>zwe: life, physical life LITERALLY: For we who are burdened groan, being in the tent, because we do not desire to be stripped [take off the clothes we've got], but to be clothed, so that that which is mortal may be swallowed by life.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Tuhan Allah yang bekin kotong siap tarima ame itu idop baru. Dia ju yang kasi kotong Dia pung Roh, ko jadi satu jaminan dari Dia pung Janji.<bt>God is the one who makes us ready to receive/accept that new life. He also gives us His Spirit, as a guarantee/surety (as in pawnshops and banks) from His Promise.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katergazomai: prepare someone for something, achieve"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">katergazomai: prepare someone for something, achieve didwmi: give<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>arrabwn: down payment, guarantee, deposit (not proof like evidence that something happened, but proof of what hasn't happened yet) pneuma: spirit<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: But the one who prepared us for this is God, who gives us the [down payment / guarantee] of the Spirit.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tagal itu, kotong yakin tarús. Kotong mangarti bilang, salama kotong masi ada dalam kotong pung badan sakarang, kotong ju masi jao dari Tuhan.<bt>Because of that, we-inc stay confidant/sure. We understand that as long as we are still in our current bodies, we are also still far from God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV missed &quot;confident&quot;."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">!@ CEV missed "confident".</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tharrew: be confident, courageous pantote: always|i(6)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">tharrew: be confident, courageous pantote: always<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>eidon: know endemew: be at home<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>swma: body ekdemew: be absent, be away<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: Therefore, being confident always, even though we know that being present in the body we are absent from the Lord,</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Andia ko kotong idop lewat parcaya sang Tuhan. Kotong sonde idop lewat apa yang kotong bisa dapa lia di ini dunya sa.<bt>That is why we live by/via believing/trusting in God2. We don't live just by/via what we are able to see in this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lewat = by (means) ; deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">lewat = by (means) ; deng would be ambiguous here</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pistis: faith peripatew: walk around, go"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pistis: faith peripatew: walk around, go around, live<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>eidon: see LITERALLY: for we live by faith, not by sight--<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma kotong ju yakin bilang, andekata kotong mati kasi tenga kotong pung badan sakarang ko pi idop sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah di sorga, na, pasti kotong lebe sanáng lai.<bt>But we are also sure/confident that if perchance (hypothetical) we were to die leaving behind our current bodies to go live together with God in heaven, na, surely we would be even happier.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tharrew: be confident eudokew: well pleased|i(8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">tharrew: be confident eudokew: well pleased<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>mallon: rather, instead, more ekdemew: be absent<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>swma: body endemew: be present<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: but we are confident that we would be pleased instead to be absent from the body and present with the Lord.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Biar kotong idop tarús di ini dunya, ko, kotong mati di sini ko idop di sana, ma yang pantíng tu, andia, kotong bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati. Te itu, kotong pung mau.<bt>Even though we continue to live on in this world, or, we die here to live there (remote), nevertheless the important thing is that we make God2's liver happy. Cuz (elaboration) that is our desire.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="philotimeomai: aspire, make it our aim,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">philotimeomai: aspire, make it our aim, have ambition, to make something a point of honor euarestos: pleasing, acceptable<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: Wherefore also we have the ambition, whether present or absent, to be pleasing to him.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma biar kotong idop tarús di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Ma biar kotong idop tarús di ini dunya, ko, kotong mati di sini ko idop di sana, yang pantíng tu, kotong bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati. Itu tu, kotong pung mau.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Jang lupa. Lama-lama samua orang musti mangada sang Kristus. Dia tu, Tukang Putus Parkara yang nilei samua orang pung idop di ini dunya. Ais nanti Kristus balas yang pantas iko apa yang orang bekin. Te Kristus tau, kalo itu orang bekin yang bae, ko, bekin yang tar bae.<bt>Don't forget. Eventually everyone must front up (before authority) to Kristus. He is the Judge who assesses/evaluates everyone's live in this world. So then later Kristus will respond/repay/reward/revenge what is appropriate according to a person's deeds. Cuz (elaboration) Kristus knows, whether that person has done good, or, done not good. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV undertranslated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">!@ CEV undertranslated</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phanerow: show, be revealed, appear emprosthen:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">phanerow: show, be revealed, appear emprosthen: in front, before, in the presence of<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>bema: tribunal, judicial bench, judgement seat komizw: carry off, get (for oneself), receive pay or wages<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>hekastos each one prassw: do, accomplish<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>phaulos: worthless, evil, bad LITERALLY: For we all must [be revealed / appear] before the judgment seat of Christ, that each one may receive what he has done when he was in the body, whether good or worthless.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="5:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 14:10</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong bisa babae deng Tuhan, tagal Kristus<bt>We-inc can be restored to a good/right relationship with God2, because of Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Tagal botong inga nanti Kristus pareksa botong pung idop, andia ko botong taku deng hormat sang Dia. Deng botong ada karjá banting tulang ko buju-buju orang ko dong parcaya sang Kristus. Tuhan Allah su tau botong pung hati barisi. Beta mau ko bosong ju tau botong pung hati barisi.<bt>Because we-exc remember that Kristus will examine our lives, that is why we fear and honour Him. And we are working our buns off (idiom: working throwing down bones) to persuade/coax/cajole people to believe in Kristus. God knows our livers are clean/pure. I want for you-pl also to know that our livers are clean. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. #2.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eidee: know phobos: causing of fear."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">eidee: know phobos: causing of fear. Seems to include deep respect as well. Many lgs differentiates the two.<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>peithw: persuade, convince phanerow: reveal, show<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>elpizw: hope suneidesis: conscience<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: Therefore knowing the fear of the Lord we persuade men, but we are revealed to God; and I hope also shown to your consciences.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Botong sonde angka-angka diri di bosong pung muka. Sonde! Ma botong ada kasi alasan sang bosong, ko biar bosong bisa omong bésar so'al botong, deng sonde usa malu-malu. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa manyao sang itu orang dong yang bamulu bésar. Te dong ada bamulu bésar so'al dong pung hasil karjá yang orang bisa dapa lia, padahal dong pung hati sonde barisi.<bt>We do not elevate/promote ourselves in front of you. No! But we are giving you a reason/s so that you can boast about us-exc, and don't need to be ashamed/embarrassed. In that way, you will be able to respond to those people who are boasting. Cuz (elaboration) they are boasting about work results that people are able to see, whereas their livers are not clean/pure. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunistemi: recommend, commend aphorme: pretext, occasion,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">sunistemi: recommend, commend aphorme: pretext, occasion, opportunity, reason, cause<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>didwmi: give kauxema: boast, pride<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>kauxaomai: boast, be proud proswpwn: face, external, appearance<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>kardia: heart, internal LITERALLY: We are not commending ourselves to you again, but giving you a reason to boast about us, so that you may have a reason to give those who boast about appearance and not about the heart.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Kalo bosong anggap botong gila, na, botong omong bagitu su, ko kasi jalan Tuhan pung karjá. Biar bosong sonde mangarti, ma Tuhan mangarti. Kalo botong ada omong pake pikiran lurus, na, botong omong bagitu ko tolong sang bosong.<bt>If you-pl consider us crazy, na, we are talking like that to carry out God2's work. Even though you don't understand, nevertheless God2 understands. If we are talking using straight (coherent, logical) thinking, na, we talk like that to help you. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eksistemi: lose our mind, crazy, beside"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">eksistemi: lose our mind, crazy, beside ourselves for God: not to benefit God, but it's between us and God. It is for God to judge.<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>swphrovew: sane, sound mind, in right mind, be sober LITERALLY: For if we are crazy, it is for God; if we are sane, it is for you.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Kristus sayang mati sang kotong. Itu yang kasi samangat sang botong ko kasi jalan botong pung tugas. Te botong parcaya bilang, satu Orang, andia Kristus, mati ko ganti sang samua orang. Dia pung arti bilang, itu sama ke kotong samua su mati ko kasi tenga idop yang lama, deng sonde ada pung hak apa-apa lai di ini dunya.<bt>Kristus dearly loves us-inc. That is what encourages/enthuses/inspires us to carry out our work/responsibilities/mission. Cuz (elaboration) we believe that one Person, that is Kristus, died to replace every person. That means that it is like/the same as we have all died leaving behind the old life, and have no more rights in this world. [EXEG: Ex Summ #2, NLT + context. NOTE to daughter translations: compare with your rendering of Rom. 6:4.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ check die to / dead"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">@@ check die to / dead to in prison epistles @@ mati kasi tenga idop yang lama NLT</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agape: love sunexw: urge on, impel,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">agape: love sunexw: urge on, impel, control, govern<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>krinw: judge, think, consider apothneskw: die Romans 6:5<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>ara: then LITERALLY: For the love of Christ urges us on, considering this, that one died for all, then all died;<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te botong parcaya, bilang, Dia su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Te botong parcaya, bilang, Dia su mati ganti sang samua orang. Padahal, Dia tu, cuma satu Orang sa.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Kristus mati kasi sang samua orang, ko biar samua orang yang idop di ini dunya, sonde idop iko dong pung mau-mau sandiri lai. Ma sakarang dong musti idop iko Kristus pung mau, tagal Dia yang su mati ganti sang dong, ais Dia idop kambali.<bt>Kristus died for all people, so that all people who live in this world, do/would not live according to their own desires/passions anymore. But now they must live according to Kristus' will/desires, because He is the one who has died in their place/replacing them, and He came back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zaw: live meketi: no longer|i(15) (15)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">zaw: live meketi: no longer<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>egeirw: rise, raise LITERALLY: and he died for all that those who live should no longer live for themselves but for him who died for them and rose.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kristus mati kasi sang samua orang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Kristus mati kasi sang samua orang, ko biar samua orang yang idop, sonde idop kasi sang dong pung diri sandiri lai. Ma sakarang dong idop kasi sang Kristus, yang su mati ganti sang dong, ais idop kambali.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Jadi mulai sakarang, kotong jang nilei orang pake manusia biasa pung ukuran. Biar dolu kotong sandiri nilei sang Kristus pake manusia biasa pung pikiran. Ma sakarang botong sonde nilei sang Dia bagitu lai.<bt>So (consequently), beginning now, we should not assess/evaluate/judge people using normal human standards/measurements. Even though previously/formerly we ourselves assessed Kristus, using normal human thinking. But now we don't assess Him like that anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hwste: henceforth, from now on, wherefore"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hwste: henceforth, from now on, wherefore nun: now<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>oida: know, regard, be intimately acquainted with sarks: flesh, body, human<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>ginwskw: know, come to know LITERALLY: From now on we regard no one from a human viewpoint; even though we knew Christ from a human viewpoint, but now no longer do we know [him that way].<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Andia ko, orang yang ta'ika deng Kristus su jadi manusia baru, yang ada pung idop baru. Dia sonde sama ke dolu lai, te dia pung idop lama su ilang buang. Su sonde ada lai! Te sakarang, yang baru su ada.<bt>That is why a person who is bound/linked with Kristus has already become a new human, who has a new life. He is not the same as before anymore, cuz (elaboration) his old life has disappeared completely. It's not there anymore! Cuz (elaboration) now, the new (one, life) already exists.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV &quot;forgotten&quot; misses the strength"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">!@ CEV "forgotten" misses the strength of Paul's claim</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kainos: new ktisis: creature, created thing|i(17)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kainos: new ktisis: creature, created thing<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>arxaios: old, ancient parexomai: pass away, go away, come to an end<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>idou: look! behold! ginomai: be, become, come<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: Therefore if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old things have gone. Look! The new things have come.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Samua ni, Tuhan Allah yang bekin. Dia yang bekin dame ko kotong babae kambali deng Dia, tagal Kristus su hapus buang kotong pung sala. Ais Dia ju kasi tugas sang kotong, ko kotong ju kasi tunju jalan ko biar orang laen ju bisa badame kambali deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>All this, God is the one who does it. He is the one who made peace (in relationships) so we-inc could be restored to a good/right relationship with Him, because Kristus has wiped away our wrongs/sins. So He also gives work/job/responsibilities/mission to us, so we also show the way so that other people can also be able to be restored to peace (in relationships) with God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katallazw: reconcile someone to someone didwmi:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">katallazw: reconcile someone to someone didwmi: give<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>diakonia: service, ministry kattallage: reconciliation<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: All this is from God, who reconciled us to himself through Christ, and gave us the ministry of reconciliation,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Inga, te waktu Kristus masi ada di ini dunya, Tuhan Allah ada pake sang Dia ko bawa orang pi badame kambali deng Tuhan. Jadi Dia sonde itong dong pung sala lai, ais dong sonde pikol sala pung hukuman lai. Ju Dia kasi tugas sang kotong ko pi kasi tau orang bilang, dong bisa babae kambali deng Dia.<bt>Remember that when Kristus was still in this world, God was using Him to bring people to be restored to a right relationship with God2. So (consequently), He does not count/keep track of their wrongs anymore, so they don't carry/bear the punishment of those wrongs anymore. And He gives work/job/ responsibilities/mission to us, to go tell people that they can be restored to a right relationship with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV grossly undertranslated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">!@ CEV grossly undertranslated</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="logizomai: count, reckon, charge paraptwma: transgression,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">logizomai: count, reckon, charge paraptwma: transgression, false step. Different emphasis from hamartia: sin.<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>tithemi: entrust LITERALLY: that just as God was in Christ reconciling the world to himself, not counting their transgressions [to / against] them, and has entrusted to us the word of reconciliation.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Te kotong jadi Kristus pung duta. Jadi Tuhan Allah pake kotong ko bawa datang orang, ko biar dong badame kambali deng Dia. Tagal botong jadi Kristus pung duta, andia ko botong ju minta sang bosong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan ada rindu ko bosong babae kambali deng Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc are Kristus' emmisaries/envoys/ ambassadors/representatives. So (consequently), God uses us to bring coming people, so that they are restored to a right relationship with Him. Because we-exc are Kristus' emmisaries/envoys/ ambassadors/representatives, that is why we request/urge you saying, “God2 is yearning for you to be restored to a right relationship with Him.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="presbeuw: be an ambassador, envoy parakalew:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">presbeuw: be an ambassador, envoy parakalew: appeal to, urge, exhort, encourage<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>deomai: ask, beg, implore, plead LITERALLY: Therefore we are ambassadors on behalf of Christ, just as [if] God is pleading through us; we beg you on behalf of Christ, be reconciled to God.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Kristus sandiri sonde parná bekin sala. Ma Tuhan Allah su bekin Dia pikol kotong pung sala. Tuhan bekin bagitu kasi sang kotong, tagal Kristus pung mati buka jalan ko kotong bisa idop deng hati lurus, sama ke Tuhan ju hati lurus.<bt>Kritus himself never did wrong/sin. But God made Him carry our-inc wrongs/sin. God2 did that for us, because Kristus' death opened the way so that we could be able to live with a straight/righteous liver, just like God2 also has a straight/righteous liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="givwskw: know hamartia: sin|i(21) (21) |rpoiew:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">givwskw: know hamartia: sin<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>poiew: do, make dikaiosune: righteousness<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>LITERALLY: He made the one who knew no sin become sin for us, that we might become the righteousness of God in him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan bekin yang bae kasi sang kotong<bt>God2 does what is good for us-inc</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Tagal botong ada karjá sama-sama deng Tuhan, botong mau nasiat sang bosong bagini: Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae bam-banya sang bosong. Jadi bosong jang tarima ame Dia pung hati bae deng sia-sia sa.<bt>Because we-exc are working together with God2, we want to advise you-pl like this: God has shown His goodness/grace/ kindness/generosity in abundance to you. So (consequently), you shsouldn't accept/receive His goodness/grace/ kindness/generosity lightly/pointlessly/trivially.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="terpaksa /e/ avoids CIE with tar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">terpaksa /e/ avoids CIE with tar paksa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="de kai: And also, not but."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">de kai: And also, not but. sunergew: work with, work together<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>parakalew: appeal to, urge, exhort, encourage kenos: empty, vain, without result, to no purpose<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>xaris: grace, favor, gift dexomai: receive, accept<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: But working together with [him] we also urge you not to receive the grace of God in vain--</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te di Dia pung Tulisan Barisi, ada tulis bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in the Scriptures it is written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Pas dia pung waktu, Beta dengar sang lu.<bt>“At just the right time, I heard you-sg.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta ju tolong sang lu waktu Beta kasi salamat orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>I also helped you when I saved people.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, dengar bae-bae, é! Sakarang ni, dia pung waktu yang bae. Te sakarang ni, Tuhan pung hari ko kasi salamat orang.<bt>Naa, [shift] listen carefully, é! Right now is just the right time. Cuz (elaboration) right now is God2's day/time for saving people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kairos: time, a point or period"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kairos: time, a point or period of time dektos: acceptable, welcome, favorable<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>epakouw: hear, listen to swteria: salvation, deliverance, preservation<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>boethew: help, come to the aid of euprosdektos: acceptable, pleasant, welcome, favorable (stronger than dektos)<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: For he says, &lt;&lt;I heard you in a favorable time, and I helped you on the day of salvation.&gt;&gt; Behold now is the very favorable time, behold now is the day of salvation.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 49:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Andia ko botong mau jaga diri bae-bae ko idop lurus sa. Te botong sonde mau jadi halangan kasi orang yang mau datang di Tuhan pung jalan idop. Deng botong ju mau omong lurus, ko biar orang jang omong bekin busuk botong pung nama bae.<bt>That is why we must guard ourselves carefully to just live straight/righteous. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc don't want to be a barrier/hindrance to people who are wanting to come to God2's way of life. And we also want to speak straight/honestly, so that people won't speak ruining our-exc good name/reputation. [EXEG: Gk is just ‘the ministry’, so question is “whose/which ministry?” NRSV, NLT, CEV take it as narrower “our (Paul's) ministry” which is certainly supported by the context and higher level book theme, rather than broader “work of the Lord (in general).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="halangan ~ alangan (variant)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">halangan ~ alangan (variant)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="medeis: no, nothing proskope: time for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">medeis: no, nothing proskope: time for taking offence, stumblingblock<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>momaomai: find fault, blame, criticize, ridicule LITERALLY: giving no offence in anything, so that the ministry may not be ridiculed,<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Botong mau idop lurus, ko biar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Botong mau idop lurus, ko biar botong sonde jadi (h)alangan kasi orang yang mau datang di Tuhan pung jalan idop. Botong ju mau omong lurus, ko biar orang sonde omong bekin busuk Tuhan pung nama bae di ini dunya.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Deng samua-samua yang botong bekin, botong usaha ko kasi tunju bilang, botong ni, Tuhan Allah pung orang karjá yang bae. Jadi biar botong dapa susa, kaná sangsara, ko, ada idop di tenga kaco-balo, na, botong batahan tarús sa.<bt>And everything we do, we make an effort to show that we are God's good workers. So (consequently), even if we get/encounter trouble/difficulty, experience suffering, or, are living in the midst of chaos, na, we just keep on enduring/persevering.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cuz: not that they were proving"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">cuz: not that they were proving that they are servants of God; but rather, that because they are servants of God, they are able to put their lives forward as examples UBS. sunistemi: commend, present<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>polleei: lots of patience hupomone: patience, endurance, fortitude, steadfastness, perseverance (especially of toil and suffering)<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>thlipsis: affliction, oppression, tribulation, pressure (brought about by outward circumstances) anagke: distress, calamity, taxed to the utmost, hardships of which no mitigation is possible (verb = 'press tight')<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>stenoxwria: distress, difficulty, anguish, trouble, hemmed in, in narrow straits LITERALLY: but in everything we show ourselves as God's servants, in much endurance, in affliction, in calamity, in distress,<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Botong ju batahan tarús waktu kaná papoko, waktu dong lempar buang sang botong pi dalam bui, waktu orang bekin huru-hara, waktu karjá banting tulang, waktu sonde dapa tidor, deng waktu rasa lapar.<bt>We also keep on enduring when beaten up, when they (non-referential) throw us into prison, whe people make disturbances/riots, when we are working our buns off (idiom: work throwing down bones), when we can't sleep, and when we feel hungry.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="plege: blow, strike, beating, whipping phulake:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">plege: blow, strike, beating, whipping phulake: prison, watch, guard<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>akatastasia: disturbance, tumult, upheaval, disorder, commotion, riot, mob violence kopos: work, labor, toil, hard work, toil with fatigue, overworked<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>agrupnia: wakefulness, sleepless nights nesteia: hunger, fasting of necessity<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: in beatings, in prison, in riots, in hard work, in sleepless nights, in hunger,</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 16:23</note><v n="6" />Botong ju batahan deng hati barisi. Botong tau banya, so'al Tuhan Allah. Botong batahan deng sabar. Botong bekin yang bae kasi orang. Botong kasi biar ko Tuhan pung Roh ator sang botong. Botong ju sayang batúl-batúl sang orang deng sonde muka-balakang.<bt>We also endure/persever with clean/pure livers. We know much about God. We endure patiently. We do good for/to people. We allow God2's Spirit to arrange/oversee/put in order us. We also really love people without being two-faced (front-back).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hagnotes: purity, sincerity, purity of life"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hagnotes: purity, sincerity, purity of life (in morality and in thought) - Galatia 5:22 gnwsis: knowledge, Christian knowledge, knowledge of God<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>makrothumia: patience, forbearance, longsuffering (toward others) xrestotes: goodness, kindness, generosity, graciousness, benevolence<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>anupokritos: genuine, sincere, without hypocrisy LITERALLY: in purity, in knowledge, in patience, in goodness, [in a dedicated spirit / by the Holy Spirit], in sincere love,<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Waktu botong omong, botong omong yang batúl, deng sonde tau omong kosong. Botong ju tarima ame kuasa dari Tuhan ko bekin yang bae. Itu sama ke botong jadi tantara yang ada pegang sanjata langkáp dari Tuhan, ko botong baparáng lawan musu, deng sonde kala.<bt>When we speak, we say what is true, and don't lie/b.s. We also receive power/authority from God2 to do what is good. That is like we are soldiers, who are holding complete weaponry from God2, so we war/battle against enemies, and don't lose. [NIV, NRSV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aletheia: truth dunamis: power|i(7) (7) |rhoplws:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">aletheia: truth dunamis: power<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>hoplws: weapon dikaiosune: righteousness<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>right hand and left hand: offense and defense, or completely equipped LITERALLY: [in truthful speech / in the word of truth], in the power of God, through the weapons of righteousness on the right hand and the left hand,<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Botong ju batahan, biar lai orang kasi tunju hormat sang botong, ko, dong omong bekin busuk botong pung nama; biar lai dong omong kasi jato sang botong, ko, dong jaga botong pung nama bae; biar lai orang omong kosong bilang, botong ada tipu ame orang, ko, dong omong bilang, botong ada omong yang batúl.<bt>We also endure/persevere, whether people are showing respect to us, or, they are trashing out name/reputation; whether they are speaking to bring us down, or, they are guarding our good name/reputation; whether people are lying/b.s. that we are deceiving people, or, they say that we are speaking the truth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="biar lai = even though, whether"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">biar lai = even though, whether</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doksa: glory, honor atimia: dishonor, disgrace,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">doksa: glory, honor atimia: dishonor, disgrace, shame, withholding honor (personal treatment), degrading<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>dusphemia: slander, ill repute (behind his back) euphemia: good report, good repute<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>planos: deceitful, leading astray, imposters, false alethes: true, honest, righteous<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: through honor and dishonor, through slander and good reputation, through deceit and truth,</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ada yang sonde kanál sang botong. Ma ada banya yang kanál botong pung nama. Botong su amper mati banya kali, ma botong masi tatáp idop ju. Dong hukum barát sang botong banya kali, ma botong sonde tau mati-mati ju.<bt>There are those who do not know/recognise us-exc. But there are many who do know/recognise our name/reputation. we have nearly died many times, but we still keep on living. They (non-referential) have punished us severely/heavily many times, but we just don't seem to die (special grammatical construction).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde tau mati-mati ju = never"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">sonde tau mati-mati ju = never achieved their goal of killing us by punishment</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agnoew: not to know, unknown, not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">agnoew: not to know, unknown, not worth knowing epiginwskw: know, well known<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>apothneskw: about to die, face death, mortal paideuw: discipline, punish, chastened<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>thanatow: put to death LITERALLY: as unknown and well known, as dying and behold we live, as punished and not dying,<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Biar botong ada rasa barát, ma botong ju hati babunga tarús. Biar botong sonde ada doi, ma botong ada bekin banya orang kaya dalam dong pung hati. Itu sama ke botong sonde ada pung apa-apa, ma botong ju dapa samua-samua.<bt>Even though we are feeling heavy (sad, discouraged), nevertheless our livers are glad continually. Even though we have no money, nevertheless we are making many people rich in their livers. That is like we have nothing whatsover, but we also get/obtain everything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lupew: sorrowful, sad, grieved aei: always|i(10)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">lupew: sorrowful, sad, grieved aei: always<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>xairos: rejoice ptwxos: begging, poor<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>ploutizw: make rich katexw: keep, possess, hold fast<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: as sorrowing but always rejoicing, as poor but making many rich, as having nothing and possessing all things.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Botong omong taráng-taráng sang bosong di kota Korintus. Botong ju sayang batúl sang bosong.<bt>We spoke clearly/openly to you-pl in the city of Korintus. We also really love you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ Good example of figurative speech."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">@@ Good example of figurative speech. (see KJV for 11-12 :) )</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stoma: mouth ('speak') anoigw: open ('freely')|i(11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">stoma: mouth ('speak') anoigw: open ('freely')<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>platunw: enlarge, wide ('strong affection') LITERALLY: Our mouth is open toward you, Corinthians, our heart has been enlarged. [We speak freely to you, Corinthians, we have strong affection for you.]<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Botong su kasi tunju botong pung sayang sang bosong deng sonde tahan-tahan. Ma bosong ada tahan-tahan bosong pung sayang sang botong.<bt>We have shown our love to you without restraint. But you hold back your love for us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stenokhwrew: cramp, crowd, restrict, confine splagxnon:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">stenokhwrew: cramp, crowd, restrict, confine splagxnon: inward parts, seat of the affections, ('heart')<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: You are not restricted by us, but you are restricted in your affection;</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Jadi beta mau nasiat sang bosong sama ke bosong jadi beta pung ana dong. Lebe bae, bosong sayang sang botong deng sonde tahan-tahan.<bt>So (consequently), I am going to advise you like you are my children. It would be better/best if you love us without restraint.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="antimisthia: return, exchange, reward, penalty teknon:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">antimisthia: return, exchange, reward, penalty teknon: child<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>platunw: enlarge LITERALLY: In exchange, I speak as to children, enlarge [your hearts].<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang ba'ika diri deng orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan<bt>Don't bind/link (active, deliberate) yourselves with people who don't believe in God2/Lord</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Jang ba'ika diri deng orang yang sonde parcaya sang Kristus. Te bosong sonde sama. Orang parcaya yang idop lurus sonde bacocok deng orang yang malawan sang Tuhan, ais sonde pantas kalo dong coba usaha ko karjá sama-sama. Orang hati bae deng orang tar bae sonde pantas jadi tamán satu kaki. Itu sama ke taráng sonde bisa bacampor deng galáp.<bt>Don't bind/link (active, deliberate) yourselves with people who don't believe in Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) you-pl are not the same. Believers who live straight/righteous do not fit/match (recip) with people who oppose God2, so it is not appropriate if they try to make the effort to work together. A person who is good livered and a person who is not good livered are not fitting/appropriate to be/become one-footed friends (best friends). That is like light cannot mix with dark.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bapár = bakawan ; bakele(r) ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">bapár = bakawan ; bakele(r) = arm-in-arm ; mitra =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heterozugew: be mismated, mated with another"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">heterozugew: be mismated, mated with another of a different kind, yoked, as a donkey and an ox (Deut. 22:10). Probably refers to more than marriage. apistos: faithless, unbelieving (connotation of evil doing)<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>metoxe: sharing, partnership, participation, have in common anomia: lawlessness, opposition to the law of God (as a frame of mind)<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>koinwnia: association, fellowship, communion, relationship phwtos: light ('righteousness, holiness')<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>skotos: darkness, gloom ('error, sin, misery') LITERALLY: Do not be unequally mated with unbelievers; for what partnership do righteousness and lawlessness have? Or what fellowship light with darkness?<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang jadi mitra deng orang yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Jang jadi mitra deng orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Kristus sonde bisa basakongkol deng setan dong pung bos, to?<bt>Kristus cannot reach agreement with the boss of evil spirits, right?</bt><note reference="6:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani di sini tulis <span class="Italic">Beliar</span>. Beliar tu, dong pinjam ame dari bahasa Ibrani <span class="Italic">Belial.</span> Dia pung maksud bilang, &lt;&lt;yang jahat, yang sonde bae, sonde ada pung guna, setan dong pung bos&gt;&gt;.<bt>The Yunani language here writes <span class="Italic">Beliar</span>. That Beliar, they borrowed from the Ibrani language <span class="Italic">Belial</span>. It means, “what is evil, what is not good, what has no use, boss of the evil spirits”.</bt></note>Bagitu ju, orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan Allah sonde ada bagian sama-sama deng orang yang parcaya sang Dia.<bt>In the same way also, people who don't believe in God have no share/portion/part together with people who believe in Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@example of TB wierdness in translation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">@@example of TB wierdness in translation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sumphwnesis: agreement, accord, harmony meris: share,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">sumphwnesis: agreement, accord, harmony meris: share, in common, portion, participation, fellowship<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>Belial: wickedness, worthlessness, the Devil. LITERALLY: And what agreement does Christ have with Belial? Or what part faith with unbelief?<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu ju, orang yang parcaya sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Bagitu ju, orang yang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah sonde ada bagian sama-sama deng orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Bosong pikir karmana, é? Kira-kira bosong kira kata, bosong bisa maso Tuhan Allah pung ruma sambayang ko sémba sang Dia dolo, baru maso lai di ruma sosonggo ko sambayang sang barang songgo dong, ko? Sonde pantas, to! Te Tuhan tu, Allah yang idop. Dia ju jadi kotong pung Bos yang hak parenta sang kotong. Ais kotong su jadi sama ke Dia pung ruma sambayang, tagal Dia ada tenga di kotong pung hati. Te Tuhan su tulis dalam Dia pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>What/how is your thinking, é? Perhaps you are thinking that we can enter God's house of worship to worship Him first, and then further enter into a house of traditional worship to pray to the objects of traditional worship, or (what)? That's not appropriate, right! Cuz (elaboration) the Lord/God2 is the God who lives. He is also our Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over us. So then we-inc are also like His house of worship, because He is living in our livers. Cuz (elaboration) God has written in His Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta pung ruma ada di Beta pung orang pung teng-tenga.<bt>“My house is in the midst of My people. [EXEG: Not addition. Gk is verbal figurative form of noun ‘house’ often glossed as “dwell, live” but also “fix one's home” NJB and “make one's home” TEV; following HCE to resonate with context of 16a “temple”. Lev. 26:11-12 NRSV, “I will place my dwelling in your midst,” NIV “I will put my dwelling place among you,”; Ez. 37:26-27 NRSV “will set my sanctuary among them forevermore. My dwelling place shall be with them,” NIV “I will put my sanctuary among them forever. My dwelling place will be with them;”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta mau bangun Beta pung ruma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Beta mau bangun Beta pung ruma di Beta pung orang pung teng-tenga.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta ju maso-kaluar di dong pung teng-tenga.<bt>I also enter-exit in their midst.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta mau jadi dong pung Tuhan Allah.<bt>I'm going to be their God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong ju jadi Beta pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>They're also going to be My people.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sugkatathesis: agreement, union, decision arrived at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">sugkatathesis: agreement, union, decision arrived at by a group, approval, assent, accordance of sentiments. enoikew: live, dwell in, dwell among, fix one's home<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>emperipatew: walk about, move among the temple: referring to the church, body of believers, community as a whole (Eph 2:21).<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: But what union does God's temple have with idols? For we are the temple of the living God; just as God said, that "I will live among them and move around, and I will be their God, and they will be my people."</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 26:11-12, Yeskial 37:26-27, 1 Korintus 3:16, 6:19; Efesus 2:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Andia ko Tuhan ju tulis bagini bilang,<bt>That's why God2 also wrote like this saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bosong musti kaluar dari dong pung teng-tenga, deng tapisa dari dong,<bt>“You-pl must come out from their midst, and be separate from them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko bosong jang jadi sama ke dong.<bt>so you are not the same as them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bosong pung hati musti barisi.<bt>Your livers must be clean/pure/holy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais bosong musti jao-jao dari samua yang bekin bosong pung hati kamomos,<bt>So/and you must distance (yourselves) from everything that makes your livers filthy/defiled, [EXEG: The Gk /akathartos/ impure, unclean, polluted (spiritually, morally), defile (religiously); if the quote is taken merely physically, as an earlier version in KM, consider explicating further with the line in \ov to force the spiritual/religious reading (as in HCE.). Isa. 52:11 NRSV “Depart, depart, go out from there! Touch no unclean thing; go out from the midst of it, purify yourselves, you who carry the vessels of the LORD.” NIV “(same)...Come out from it and be pure, you who carry the vessels of the LORD.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[\q3] yang bekin bosong sonde bisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">[\q3] yang bekin bosong sonde bisa sambayang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng bagitu, Beta tarima bae sang bosong.<bt>In that way, I will accept/receive you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@CEV undertranslated, doesn't capture strong sense"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">!@CEV undertranslated, doesn't capture strong sense of needing to be different</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekserxomai: go out, go away, withdraw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ekserxomai: go out, go away, withdraw aphorizw: separate, take away<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>akathartos: impure, unclean, polluted (spiritually, morally), defile (religiously) haptw: touch, take hold of, hold<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: For that reason, "Come out from among them and be separate," says the Lord, "and do not touch the unclean thing; and I will receive you,</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:11</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Beta mau jadi bosong pung Bapa;<bt>I want to/am going to be your Father;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong ju jadi Beta pung ana dong.<bt>you will also be My children.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Itu tu, yang kotong pung Bos ada bilang.<bt>That there is what our-inc Bos is saying.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia yang Paling Kuasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>He is the one who is Most Powerful/Authoritative.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="esomai eis: 'be to you, come"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">esomai eis: 'be to you, come into being' pantokratwr: almighty, all powerful, omnipotent<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: and I will be a father for you, and you will be my sons and daughters, says the Lord almighty."</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Samuel 7:14, 1 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 17:13, Yesaya 43:6, Yeremia 31:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara sayang dong! Tagal Tuhan su janji ini hal dong samua kasi kotong, andia ko kotong musti bekin barisi kotong pung hati deng kotong pung idop. Jang kasi biar kamomos sadiki ju, tenga di kotong pung diri. Te kotong mau jadi barisi 100 parsén kasi sang Tuhan, ko kasi tunju bilang, kotong taku deng hormat sang Dia.<bt>Dear siblings! Because God2 has promised all these things to us-inc, that is why we must make clean/pure/holy our livers and our lives. Don't allow/permit even a little filth/defilement stay/live/remain in yourselves. Cuz (elaboration) we want to be/become 100 parsén clean/pure/holy for God2, to show that we fear and honour Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epaggelia: announcement, promise, pledge, offer agapetos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">epaggelia: announcement, promise, pledge, offer agapetos: beloved, loved one, dear [close relationship]<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>katharizw: cleanse, make clean, purify molusmos: defilement, pollution, stain, filthiness<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>sarks: flesh, body, material part of a person epitelew: perform, complete, finish, accomplish, bring about<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>hagiwsune: holiness, moral excellence, purity phobos: fear, reverence and devotion, awe and dread, respect<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: Therefore having these promises, beloved, let us cleanse ourselves from all defilement of body and spirit, perfecting holiness in the fear of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Hal yang bekin sanáng Paulus pung hati<bt>A matter/things that make Paulus' liver happy</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Sodara dong! Kasi salák sang botong. Buka hati ko tarima bae-bae sang botong. Jang tutu bosong pung hati. Te dolu, waktu botong ada di bosong pung teng-tenga, botong sonde parná bekin sala kasi satu orang ju. Botong sonde parná buju orang ko bekin sala. Botong ju sonde parná tipu ame orang ko cari ontong dari dong.<bt>Siblings! Give opportunity/chance/time to us. Open your livers to receive/welcome us. Don't close your livers. Cuz (elaboration) previously, when we-exc were there among you, we never did wrong to a single person. We never persuaded/coaxed anyone to do wrong/sin. We also never tricked/deceived anyone to get advantage/profit from them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kans"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">kans</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xwpew: have room for, hold, contain,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">xwpew: have room for, hold, contain, leave a space for, understand, give a favorable hearing, be patient, receive; trust us, open up to us adikew: do wrong, treat unjustly<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>phteirw: ruin, injure, destroy, corrupt, spoil pleonektew: outwit, take advantage of, defraud, cheat<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: Make room for us; we wronged no one, we ruined no one, we did not take advantage of anyone.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Beta pung maksud, bukan mau lempar sala sang bosong. Te beta su bilang, botong sayang sang bosong. Ais biar karmana ju, botong ada ta'ika deng bosong, biar kotong mati ko, kotong idop.<bt>What I mean is not to try to accuse/pass blame to you. Cuz (elaboration) I have already said we love you. So no matter what, we are bound/linked with you, whether we die or we live. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. (fairly unanimous); CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ review “together” @@ nothing in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">@@ review “together” @@ nothing in life or death will keeping us fom loving you. We'll love you whether we're alive or dead ; HCE review “together with” CHECK order of live or die !!! @@</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katakrisis: condemnation, pass judgment on proeipon:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">katakrisis: condemnation, pass judgment on proeipon: foretell, tell beforehand<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>sunapothneskw: die with, die together suzaw: live with, live together<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: I do not say this to condemn you, for I said before that you are in our hearts to die together and live together.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, biar karmana ju, botong mau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Ais, biar karmana ju, botong mau ko botong ada sama-sama deng bosong, biar kotong mati ko kotong idop.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Sakarang beta sonde usa pikiran lai, te beta parcaya sang bosong. Beta ju omong bésar so'al bosong. Bosong ju kasi kuat beta pung hati. Jadi biar botong kaná susa macam-macam, ma beta pung hati babunga tarús tagal bosong.<bt>Now I don't need to worry anymore, cuz (elaboration) I believe in/trust you-pl. I also boast about you. You also strengthen/encourage my liver. So (consequently), even though we encounter various sorts of difficulty, nevertheless my liver continues to be glad because of you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parresia: confidence, boldness, courage, fearlessness kauxesis:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">parresia: confidence, boldness, courage, fearlessness kauxesis: boasting, pride in<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>plerow: make full, be full, fill paraklesis: comfort, consolation<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>huperperisseuw: be abundant, cause to overflow xara: joy<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>thlipsis: tribulation, trouble, oppression, affliction, pressure [brought by outward circumstances] LITERALLY: I have much confidence toward you, I have great boasting concerning you; I have been filled with comfort, I overflow with joy in all our troubles.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta parcaya sang bosong, ais beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Beta parcaya sang bosong, ais beta sonde usa pikiran lai.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Waktu dolu botong datang di propinsi Makedonia, botong cape mau mati. Te botong dapa susa kiri-kanan. Botong ada bakanjar deng orang luar. Botong ju ada rasa taku dalam botong pung hati.<bt>When previously we-exc came to the province of Makedonia, we were extremely tired. Cuz (elaboration) we encountered troubles/difficulties/strife left-right. We were arguing/fighting with outsiders. We also felt afraid in our livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="erxomai: come exw: have|i(5) (5) |ranesis:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">erxomai: come exw: have<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>anesis: rest, relief, relaxation, loosening of tension thlibw: oppress, afflict someone<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>ekswthen: outside maxe: battle, fighting, quarrel, strife, dispute<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>eswthen: inside phobos: fear<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: [For also our coming / when we came] into Macedonia our body had no rest, but we were afflicted in everything, fighting outside, fears inside.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te botong dapa susa dalam samua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Te botong dapa susa dalam samua hal di mana-mana.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Korintus 2:13</note><v n="6" />Ma Tuhan Allah yang kasi kuat sang orang yang su ilang samangat, deng yang rasa barát. Ais Dia kasi kuat botong pung hati waktu Dia kirim Titus ko datang di botong.<bt>But God is the one who strengthens people who have given up/lost heart, and who feel heavy (sad, discouraged, depressed). So He strengthened/encouraged our livers when He sent Titus to come to us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parakalew: comfort, encourage, cheer up tapeivos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">parakalew: comfort, encourage, cheer up tapeivos: low [figurative], downcast, downhearted, depressed<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>parakalew: implore parousia: coming, appearance<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: But God who comforts the downhearted comforted us by the coming of Titus</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Naa, Titus pung datang tu, ada kasi kuat botong pung hati. Te dia kasi laporan bilang, waktu dia masi di sana, bosong su kasi kuat dia pung hati. Dengar bagitu, itu kasi kuat botong pung hati ju. Dia ju carita bilang, bosong rindu mau lia sang beta, deng bosong ada manyasal batúl deng parkara yang dolu su jadi di bosong pung teng-tenga. Dia ju carita so'al bosong pung usaha ko tolong sang beta. Andia ko beta pung hati babunga.<bt>Naa, Titus' coming strengthened/encouraged our livers. Cuz (elaboration) he gave a report saying, when he was still there, you-pl had strengthened/encouraged his liver. Hearing that, that also strengthened/encouraged our livers too. He also told/narrated that you yearned to see me, and you really felt regret/sorry with the matter/dispute/issue which previously had happened in your midst. He also told/narrated about your efforts to help/assist me. That is why my liver is glad. [EXEG: NLT. On the Gk “zeal”, the sources in Ex. Summ. are all over the place on this, only one of which is “defend”. Our protocols are to keep it broad to mirror the possibilities from the Gk where possible. ‘Help’ can encompass ‘defend’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anaggellw: report, tell epipothesis: longing, earnest"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">anaggellw: report, tell epipothesis: longing, earnest desire. Is more needed? Cf. verse 11.<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>odurmos: mourning, lamentation zelos: zeal, ardor, determination<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>xarew: rejoice, be glad LITERALLY: And not only by his coming, but also by the comfort which you comforted him with, reporting to us your longing, your mourning, your zeal for me, so that made me rejoice more.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naa, Titus pung datang tu, ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Naa, Titus pung datang tu, ada kasi kuat botong pung hati. Waktu dia balóm datang di beta, bosong su kasi kuat dia pung hati lebe dolu. Itu ju kasi kuat sang botong. Te dia ada carita, bilang, bosong rindu mau lia sang beta, deng bosong ada manyasal batúl deng parkara yang dolu su jadi di bosong pung teng-tenga. Dia ju carita so'al bosong pung usaha ko tolong sang beta. Andia ko beta pung hati babunga.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Korintus 2:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Naa, beta tau bilang, beta pung surat dolu yang togor karás sang bosong tu, memang bekin bosong rasa susa. Ma beta sonde manyasal tulis itu surat. (Padahal itu waktu, beta ada manyasal sadiki, waktu beta dapa tau bilang, beta pung surat tu, ada bekin bosong susa, biar cuma sabantar sa.)<bt>Naa, I know that my previous letter that scolded you harshly, really made you feel troubled. But I don't regret writing that letter. (Whereas in fact at that time, I did regret a little, when I found out that my letter was making you troubled, even though only for a short period.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lupew: grieve, cause sorrow epistolos: letter|i(8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">lupew: grieve, cause sorrow epistolos: letter<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>metamelomai: repent, change mind LITERALLY: That although you were grieved by the letter, I do not repent; although I did repent (I see that that letter grieved you for a time),<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naa, waktu beta tulis beta pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Naa, waktu beta tulis beta pung surat dolu, itu bekin bosong rasa susa. Ma beta sonde manyasal beta su tulis itu surat. (Padahal itu waktu, beta ada manyasal sadiki, waktu beta dapa tau, bilang, beta pung surat tu, ada bekin bosong susa, biar sonde lama.)</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ma sakarang beta pung hati babunga. Beta sonde rasa sanáng tagal itu waktu bosong rasa susa. Sonde! Beta rasa sanáng, tagal itu waktu, beta pung surat ada buju-buju ko bosong bartobat. Ais bosong mangaku bosong pung sala, deng kasi tenga bosong pung hal yang tar bae dong, ko bale iko sang Tuhan pung jalan idop yang lurus. Te Tuhan yang bekin bosong manyasal bagitu. Deng bagitu, bukan botong ni, yang bekin bosong jadi kaco.<bt>But now my livered is glad. I don't feel happy because you were feeling troubled at that time. No! I feel happy, because at that time, my letter was persuading/coaxing/cajoling you to *repent. Then you acknowledged/confessed your wrongs/sin, and left behind the things that were not good, to turn and follow God2's straight/righteous way of life. Cuz (elaboration) God2 is the one who made you regretful like that. In that way it was not us-exc here who made you become chaotic/disrupted.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zemiow: inflict injury or punishment, suffer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">zemiow: inflict injury or punishment, suffer damage or loss, produce a bad permanent change LITERALLY: I rejoice now, not that you were grieved, but that your grief led to repentance; for you grieved according to God, so that you were not damaged by us.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te kalo kotong rasa manyasal di hati iko Tuhan pung mau, kotong barenti bekin hal jahat dong, ais bale iko jalan idop yang lurus. Itu kasi lapás sang kotong dari Tuhan pung hukuman, ais kotong sonde usa idop deng manyasal tarús. Ma kalo kotong cuma manyasal di bibir sa, sama ke orang di ini dunya dong pung biasa, nanti kotong ancor.<bt>Cuz if/when we feel regret in our livers according to God2's will, we stop doing evil things, and then turn to follow the straight/righteous way of life. That frees/saves us from God2's punishment, so.then we don't need to live with regret continually. But if/when we only regret with just our lips, like people in this world normally/customarily do, then we will be destroyed/fall apart.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ametameletos: without regret LITERALLY: For sorrow"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ametameletos: without regret LITERALLY: For sorrow according to God produces repentance unto salvation without regret; but repentance of the world produces death.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Coba bosong pikir! Waktu bosong baca beta pung surat tu, beta tau bosong ada manyasal ju. Itu iko Tuhan pung mau. Te itu bekin bosong karjá banting tulang ko hapus buang hal jahat dari bosong pung idop. Bosong su cape deng bosong pung jahat. Bosong ju taku, jang sampe bosong nanti bekin jahat ulang lai. Bosong rindu mau lia sang beta, deng siap tarús ko bekin yang bae. Bosong ju siap mau kasi hukum orang yang bekin sala. Tagal bosong bekin yang batúl bagitu, andia ko bosong barisi. Deng bagitu, sonde ada yang bisa lempar sala sang bosong.<bt>Have a think about this! When you-pl read that letter of mine, I knew that you were also feeling regret. That was according to God2's will. Cuz (elaboration) that made you work your buns off (idiom: work throwing down bones) to wipe away evil things from your lives. You-pl were already tired of your evil. You were also afraid, hoping lest you might later do evil again. You yearned to see me, and were ready continually do do what is good. You were also ready to judge/punish people who do wrong. Because you were doing what is right/correct like that, that is why you are clean/pure/holy. In that way, there is nobody who can accuse/blame you (of any fault). [EXEG: HCE. Expect some BT noise here, since in the RLs this “tired of your evil” is a pretty close match for the range of the Gk ‘indignation, alarm, anger’. In these lgs the ‘tired of’ construction is often used in the sense of ‘fed up with; had enough of x and want to do s.t. about it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="posos: how great, how much spoude:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">posos: how great, how much spoude: eagerness, earnestness, diligence<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>apologia: defense, give an account of oneself haganaktesis: indignation, pain one causes himself<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>phobos: fear, alarm epipothesis: longing, yearning, affectionate desire<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>zelos: zeal ekdikesis: vengence, punishment. Verse 7.<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>sunistemi: demonstrate, show, bring out hagnos: pure, holy, innocent<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: For look, this same thing, to sorrow according to God, how much eagerness it produces in you, what defense, what indignation, what fear, what longing, what zeal, what punishment; in everything you do you have shown yourselves to be pure.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong pung manyasal yang iko Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Bosong pung manyasal yang iko Tuhan pung mau, bekin bosong karjá banting tulang ko hapus buang hal jahat dari bosong pung idop. Deng bagitu, sonde ada yang bisa lempar sala sang bosong.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Jadi beta sonde tulis beta pung surat dolu tu, kasi itu orang yang bekin jahat. Beta ju sonde tulis kasi orang yang takaná dia pung jahat. Ma beta tulis itu surat kasi bosong, ko biar beta kasi tunju bilang, bosong pung omong di Tuhan pung muka tu, sunggu-sunggu. Deng bosong ada sayang batúl sang botong.<bt>So (consequently), I didn't write my previous letter to that person who did evil. I also didn't write it to the people who were effected by his evil. But I wrote that letter to you-pl, so that I could show that what you were saying before God, was in earnest/sincere. And you were truly loving us-exc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ara: then, so, consequently, accordingly heneka:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ara: then, so, consequently, accordingly heneka: because of<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>adikew: do wrong phanerow: reveal, show, become visible<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>spoude: earnestness, eagerness, diligence, zeal. On the specific occasion, or in general? LITERALLY: So even though I wrote to you, not because of the wrongdoer, nor because of the one who was wronged, but so that your earnestness for us might be revealed before God.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, beta su tulis beta pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Jadi, beta su tulis beta pung surat dolu kasi bosong, ko biar beta kasi tunju, bilang, bosong pung omong di Tuhan pung muka tu, sunggu-sunggu. Deng bosong ada sayang batúl sang botong. Beta sonde tulis itu surat kasi itu orang yang bekin jahat tu. Deng sonde tulis kasi orang yang takaná dia pung jahat.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ini samua ni, kasi kuat beta pung hati.<bt>All of these things (that I am referring to), strengthened/encouraged my liver.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bosong ju su kasi kuat Titus pung hati, ko biar dia pung hati bisa tanáng. Itu ju bekin sanáng tamba sang botong pung hati.<bt>You also strengthened/encouraged Titus' liver, so that his liver could be calm/at peace. That also made our livers even happier.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parakalew: comfort, encourage paraklesis: comfort, encouragement."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">parakalew: comfort, encourage paraklesis: comfort, encouragement. REFRESHING? Acts 3:19<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>perissoterws: more xairw: rejoice<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>xapa: joy anapauw: cause to rest, put at rest<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: Because of this we are encouraged. And upon our encouragement we rejoice even more because of Titus' joy, that his spirit has been put at rest by you all;</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Beta parná angka-angka sang bosong di Titus so'al bosong pung bekin bae. Beta ju kasi tau sang dia bilang, bosong sonde parná bekin beta jadi malu. Te samua hal yang botong parná carita sang bosong tu, batúl. Ais samua hal yang botong carita di Titus so'al bosong tu, ju batúl.<bt>I have elevated/promoted you to Titus about your good deeds. I also told him saying, you-pl have never made me become ashamed/embarrassed. Cuz (elaboration) everything that we-exc have ever told/narrated to you is true. So then everything that we told Titus about you is also true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kataisxunw: be humiliated, put to shame,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kataisxunw: be humiliated, put to shame, be embarrassed LITERALLY: that if I have boasted of anything to him about you, I have not been put to shame; but as we spoke all things to you in truth, even so our boasting before Titus was true.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Jadi tiap kali dia inga sang apa yang bosong bekin, deng apa yang bosong omong, dia pung sayang sang bosong batamba-tamba. Deng dia ju inga waktu dia pi sana, ais bosong ada tarima sang dia deng hormat, ma bosong ju jadi pikiran deng beta pung surat.<bt>So (consequently) each time he remembers what you have done, and what you have said, his love for you keeps increasing. And he also remembers when he went there, and then you received him with respect, but you were also concerned because of my letter. [EXEG: MC has a note that suggest “fear &amp; trembling” here means respect &amp; humility; NLT “respect and deep concern”; TNTC “respect”; LN “sense #3: reverence”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="splagxnon: inward parts, heart [intestines, love,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">splagxnon: inward parts, heart [intestines, love, compassion] avamineskw: remind<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>hupakoe: obedience tromos: trembling [because of the letter]<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>dexomai: receive, take LITERALLY: And his inward affection increases toward you, when he remembers the obedience of all of you, as with fear and trembling you received him.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ais bosong ada tarima sang dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">ais bosong ada tarima sang dia deng taku deng gamatar.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Beta pung hati babunga, tagal beta bisa parcaya sang bosong dalam samua hal. Jadi beta su sonde jadi pikiran deng bosong lai!<bt>My liver is glad, because I can believe/trust you in everything. So (consequently), I don't need to worry about you anymore!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ganjil = awkward"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">ganjil = awkward</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tharrew: be confident LITERALLY: I rejoice"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">tharrew: be confident LITERALLY: I rejoice because in everything I have confidence in you.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong kasi sumbangan deng hati barisi<bt>They give a money.gift/contributions with clean/pure livers</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Marge Crofts notes: ch.8-9 two whole"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Marge Crofts notes: ch.8-9 two whole chapters talking about money, but doesn't use the word "money" once in the Greek, uses euphemisms such as "grace" "service" "of giving".</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara sayang dong! Botong pung mau ko bosong mangarti Tuhan pung hati bae, yang Dia su kasi tunju sang jama'at di propinsi Makedonia dong.<bt>Dear siblings! Our desire is for you-pl to understand God2's goodness/grace/kindness/generosity, which He has shown to the *congregations in the province of Makedonia.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gnwrizw: make known, reveal, inform, cause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">gnwrizw: make known, reveal, inform, cause to know LITERALLY: And we want you to know, brothers, the grace of God which has been shown in the churches of Macedonia,<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te biar dong dapa susa bam-banya, ma dong pung hati babunga tarús. Andia ko, biar dong sandiri miskin, ma dong masi kasi dong pung doi bam-banya deng hati barisi, ko bantu orang parcaya laen yang dapa susa dong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) even though/if they encounter lots of difficulties/trouble, nevertheless their livers are glad continually. That is why, even though they themselves are poor, nevertheless they still give a lot of their money with clean/pure livers, to help/assist (this lexical choice is the one that carries overtones of ‘financial’) other believers who encounter trouble/difficulties. [EXEG: all commentators agreed that chapters 8-9 are about money and giving (to those in need/difficulty), even though the Gk never uses the term ‘money’ in these two chapters. So a number of things are made explicit early to set the stage and provide high level cohesion. In this verse attitudes are tied to action, so it is not just about giving, but about being generous, overflowing, and doing it with abundant joy. So also in discussion with UNSs and MTTs, because of regional norms of giving stingily, grudgingly, with strings, and expecting quid pro quo, the consultant felt these explications (deng hati barisi and yang dapa susa) were appropriate for high level cohesion.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="polus: much, great, strong, severe, hard,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">polus: much, great, strong, severe, hard, deep, profound dokime: test, ordeal [has been tried and stood the test]<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>thlipsis: tribulation, affliction, oppression, trial [by outward circumstances], trouble perisseia: surplus, abundance, exuberant<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>xara: joy bathos: depth, extreme, bottom, lowest<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>ptwsxeia: extreme poverty, beggarliness, poor perisseuw: be left over, abound, overflow<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>ploutos: riches, wealth, abundance haplotes: generosity, liberality, singleness of heart, sincerity<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: because in a severe test of trouble, their abundant joy and their extreme poverty overflowed in a wealth of generosity;</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Beta sandiri bisa carita bilang, dong kasi samua yang dong bisa kasi. Ais dong kasi tamba lebe dari itu lai. Sonde ada yang paksa sang dong.<bt>I myself am able to tell/narrate that they give everything they are able to give. So/then they give in addition to/beyond that too. There is nobody who forces them to do that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dunamis: power, ability, capacity marturew: testify,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">dunamis: power, ability, capacity marturew: testify, bear witness<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>authairetos: of ones own accord, free will, self-motivated, voluntarily LITERALLY: because [they gave] according to their ability, I can testify, and beyond their ability, of their own free will<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Dong sandiri yang minta deng sunggu-sunggu ko biar botong buka jalan kasi sang dong. Deng bagitu, dong bisa ame bagian ko bantu orang parcaya yang kaná susa di Yerusalem.<bt>They themselves are the ones to requested in all earnestness/sincerity so that we-exc would open the way for them. In that way, they could have a share/portion/part to help/assist believers who are effected by trouble/difficulty in Yerusalem. [EXEG: NLT &amp; Ex. Summ (unanimous).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraklesis: appeal, request deomai: ask, beg|i(4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">paraklesis: appeal, request deomai: ask, beg<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>xaris: favor koinwnia: association, participation, sharing, fellowship<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>diakonia: relief, aid, support, distribution, service, ministry, help LITERALLY: with strong request begging us the favor of sharing in the help for the saints--<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="8:1-4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 15:26</note><v n="5" />Dolu botong ada harap dong mau bekin bagini, ma yang dong bekin tu, lebe dari yang botong ada harap! Partama, dong sarakan dong pung diri sang kotong pung Bos. Ais dong omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong ada mau sarakan botong pung diri ko layani sang bosong, tagal itu iko Tuhan pung mau.&gt;&gt;<bt>Previously we-exc had been hoping they would do this, but what they have/are doing, is more than what we were hoping! First, they turned over/surrendered/dedicated themselves to our-inc Bos. Then they spoke further saying, “We are going to turn over/surrender/dedicate ourselves to serve you-pl, because that is according to God2's will.” [EXEG: ‘layani’ is actually further fleshing out Gk diakonias which is slightly undertranslated in KM vs. 4, and necessary from UNS responses to explain what “gave themselves … to us” means.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kathws: just as, as elpizw: hope,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kathws: just as, as elpizw: hope, expect, foresee<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>thelema: will, wish, desire LITERALLY: and not as we expected, but they gave themselves first to the Lord and to us by the will of God,<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tagal jama'at di Makedonia dong pung conto bagitu, andia ko botong ada minta ko Titus pi kambali di bosong di Korintus lai, ko biar bosong ju bisa bantu Tuhan pung orang yang dapa susa dong di Yerusalem. Te dolu, dia yang mulai kumpul doi kasi sang dong. Ais sakarang botong ada minta ko dia bisa bekin langkáp bosong pung tugas bantu orang.<bt>Because of the example of the congregations in Makedonia, that is why we-exc are requesting that Titus return to you-pl in Korintus again, so that you also can help God's people who are in difficulty in Yerusalem. Cuz (elaboration) previously, he is the one who began to collect money for them. So now we are requesting for him to be able to finish/make complete your work/responsibility/mission of helping/assisting people. [EXEG: NLT] [EXEG: Fleshed out to make referent tracking and time frame clearer.] [OV: Dolu, Titus yang mulai kasi jalan karjá ko biar bosong bisa bantu Tuhan pung orang yang dapa susa. Ais, botong ada minta ko dia pi kambali di bosong lai, ko biar bosong bisa bekin langkáp bosong pung tugas bantu orang.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parakalew: appeal to, urge, command, encourage,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">parakalew: appeal to, urge, command, encourage, exhort proenarxomai: begin:<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>epitelew: end, complete, finish LITERALLY: accordingly we have urged that as Titus had already made a beginning, thus also he complete among you this gracious work.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="8:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Titus 2:14</note><v n="7" />Bosong pung karjá kasi sang Tuhan memang talalu bae. Conto ke: bosong pung parcaya, kuat; bosong pung omong, bagus; bosong tau banya, so'al Tuhan; bosong pung samangat, tinggi; deng bosong talalu sayang sang botong. Andia ko beta mau ko bosong ju bantu Tuhan pung orang yang ada dapa susa deng kasi doi bam-banya.<bt>Your work for God2 really is very/exceptionally good. For example: your faith is strong; your speech/what you have to say is great; you know a lot about God2; your enthusiasm/zeal/zest is high; and you really (grammatical construction = superior degree) love us. That is why I want you to also help/assist God2's people who are encounterings trouble/difficulty by/through giving a lot of money.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="spoude: diligence, earnestness, eagerness, zeal, carefulness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">spoude: diligence, earnestness, eagerness, zeal, carefulness LITERALLY: But as you excel in everything, in faith, in word, in knowledge, in all carefulness, and in your love for us, see that in this favor you excel.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Beta sonde parenta sang bosong di Korintus ko kasi doi bam-banya, ma beta mau uji sang bosong. Te jama'at di Makedonia dong su mau bantu sang dong. Jadi deng bagini bosong ju bisa kasi tunju, bosong ada sayang batúl-batúl sang orang susa dong.<bt>I am not ordering you-pl in Korintus to give a lot of money, but I want to test you. Cuz (elaboration) the congregations in Makedonia are already wanting/going to help/assist them. So (consequently), by this means you can also show that you really love people in difficulty. [EXEG: NLT] [NOTE: Q: Add “sayang … sang orang susa di Yerusalem dong”? A: With restructuring of vs.6, and what is in vs.11, that would make it very heavy. My concern is by locking everything in to Jeruslem, local readers will not generalise a related application to themselves about giving to believers in difficulty. Let's leave some things broader.] [NOTE to daughter translations: In Gk the focus is on “genuineness of your love”, rather than “do you genuinely want to show your love”, but ALT: Jadi, beta mau tanya sang bosong di Korintus dong, “Kira-kira bosong ju mau kasi tunju batúl-batúl bosong pung sayang sang orang susa dong, ko?”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epitage: command, order hetrwn: other|i(8) (8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">epitage: command, order hetrwn: other<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>humetera: your gnesios: genuine, sincere<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>dokimaxw: approve, accept as proved, tested and proved LITERALLY: I say this not as a command but to prove by the earnestness of others that your love also is genuine.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Te bosong su tau bilang, kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong. Dolu Dia sama ke orang kaya. Ma Dia pili ko jadi orang malarat ko tolong sang bosong, ko biar bosong bisa jadi kaya dalam banya hal.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you already know that our Bos Yesus Kristus has shown His goodness/grace/ kindness/ generosity to you. Previously He was like a rich person. But He chose to become a poor person to help/assist (lex. choice not implying financial) you-pl, so that you could become rich in many things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: for you know the grace"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: for you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, that although he was rich, for you he became poor, that you might become rich by his poverty.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Taon lalu, bosong su mulai kumpul doi kasi sang dong. Bosong sonde cuma kasi doi sa, ma bosong bantu dari bosong pung hati ju. Jadi iko beta, bosong musti bekin bagini:<bt>Last year, You had already begun to collect money for them. You did not only just give money, but you helped/assisted from your livers too. So (consequently), according to me, this is what you should do: [EXEG: I don't think there is a textual basis for saying “you (in Corinth) were the group that first thought to help those in Jerusalem” (even thought NLT and Uma BT say that, I think it is noise leftover from the KJV misrendering of Gk “previously began”] [EXEG: What is the basis for /bantu dari bosong pung hati/? /Dari/ goes to manner/ motivation, which is the focus of vs.8-9. Consultant felt it was appropriate reflection/ explication/ reinforcement of vague “the doing” in vs.10.] [NOTE: OV /Su mulai bantu/ implies money or assistance actually given, whereas the point Paul seems to be making is they began to collect it, but never a) finished collecting it, and b) never delivered it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gnwme: judgment, opinion, advice sumpherw: help,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">gnwme: judgment, opinion, advice sumpherw: help, confer a benefit, be advantageous, profitable, useful<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>proenarxomai: begin perusi: last year<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: And I give my opinion in this; for this benefits you who began last year not only to do but also to desire [to do];</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Dolu bosong su mau bantu Tuhan pung orang yang dapa susa di Yerusalem sana. Jadi sakarang, sumbang kasi abis apa yang bosong su putus mau bantu. Deng barapa yang bosong mampu kasi, na, kasi su. Ma yang pantíng, kasi deng hati samangat.<bt>Previously you were already going to help/assist God2's people who encountered difficulty in Yerusalem (remote). So (consequently) now, contribute making complete what you have already decided to help/assist. And however much you are able to give, na, just give (it, that). But the important thing is, give with an enthusiastic/positive liver. [EXEG: NLT, HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epitelew: complete, end, finish prothumia: willingness,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">epitelew: complete, end, finish prothumia: willingness, readiness, good will<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: and now also finish what you did, so that just as there was a readiness to want [to give], thus also there may be the completion out of what you have.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Te kalo kotong kasi deng hati samangat iko barapa yang kotong mampu kasi, na, itu ju bae. Tarsará kotong sa. Te orang jang kasi deng paksa, apa yang nanti bekin susa sang dia.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if we-inc give with an enthusiastic/positive liver according to how much we are able to give, na, that is good too. It'up to us-inc. Cuz (elaboration) a person shouldn't give by being forced what will later make things difficult for him. [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT: Te orang jang kasi apa yang nanti bekin susa sang dia, tagal kaná paksa.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Terserá"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Terserá</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prokeimai: be present, be set before"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">prokeimai: be present, be set before katho: as much as, in so far as<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>euprosdektos: fully acceptable, pleasant, welcome LITERALLY: For if willingness is present, it is completely acceptable, as much as a person has, not as much as he doesn't have.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="barapa iko bosong pung suka, na,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">barapa iko bosong pung suka, na, itu ju bae. Terserá bosong sa. Kasi barapa yang bosong mampu kasi. Jang kasi yang bekin barát sang bosong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Beta sonde maksud bekin barát sang bosong, ko biar orang laen jadi ringan. Te beta pung maksud, kotong samua pikol sama-sama dong pung susa.<bt>It is not my intention to make things heavy/burden for you-pl, so that other people can be light(weight)/easy. Cuz (elaboration) my intention is for all of us-inc to carry together their trouble/difficulty.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[EXEG: 1) burden you to help"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">[EXEG: 1) burden you to help others (CEV) or 2) burden you to help but not burden others (NLT)]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anesis: rest, relief, ease, relaxation, let"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">anesis: rest, relief, ease, relaxation, let go isotes: equality<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: For I do not mean that others should be eased and you burdened, but from equality.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te beta pung maksud, bosong samua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Te beta pung maksud, bosong samua pikol sama-sama ko jang rasa barát.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te sakarang bosong ada pung lebe, deng dong ada pung kurang. Lama-lama dong ju bisa balas, kalo bosong nanti ada pung kurang. Deng bagitu, kotong bisa pikol sama-sama.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) now you-pl have more/excess, and they have less/lack. Eventually they will also be able to repay/reciprocate, if you-pl later have less/lack. In that way, we-inc can carry (the load) together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="husterema: need LITERALLY: At the present"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">husterema: need LITERALLY: At the present time your plenty will meet their need, so that their plenty may be for your need, thus being equal;<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Itu sama ke Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang,<bt>That is like the Scriptures write saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Orang yang dapa banya,<bt>“The person who got/obtained much,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sonde dapa lebe dari apa yang dong parlú.<bt>did not get/have more than what they needed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng orang yang dapa sadiki,<bt>And the person who got/obtained a little,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sonde dapa kurang dari apa yang dong parlú.&gt;&gt;<bt>did not get/have less that what they needed.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pleonazw: increase, too much, excess. (Adapted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pleonazw: increase, too much, excess. (Adapted from Exodus) elattonew: have less, too little, lack<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: thus it has been written, 'He who has much did not have extra, and he who had little does not lack.'</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang kumpul banya, sonde ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Orang yang kumpul banya, sonde ada pung sisa. Orang yang kumpul sadiki, sonde kurang ju.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 16:18</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al Titus, deng orang laen yang mau antar bawa bantuan<bt>About Titus, and other people who are going to deliver the (financial) aid</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Beta minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah, tagal Dia yang buju-buju sang Titus ko mau tolong sang bosong, sama ke beta mau tolong sang bosong.<bt>I give thanks to God, because He is the one who persuaded Titus to want to help/assist (non-financial) you, just like I want to help/assist you. [EXEG: Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But thanks to God who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But thanks to God who put the same earnestness concerning you in Titus's heart,</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Memang botong ada minta dia pi lia sang bosong. Padahal, itu dia pung mau sandiri ju. Andia ko dia sandiri yang mau pi tolong sang bosong, bukan tagal beta pung minta.<bt>We really were requesting him to go see/check up on you. Whereas in fact, that was also his onw desire. That is why he himself is the one who wanted to go help/assist you, not because of my request.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="huparxw: be authairetos: of ones own"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">huparxw: be authairetos: of ones own accord<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: because indeed he accepted our appeal, and being very earnest, he is going to you of his own accord.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ma dia sonde pi sandiri. Te botong ju su utus botong pung sodara satu ko pi sama-sama deng dia. Samua jama'at di sini kanál sang ini orang, tagal dia su karjá banting tulang ko kasi tau orang so'al Tuhan pung Kabar Bae.<bt>But he didn't go alone. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc have also sent/commissioned one of our siblings to go together with him. All the congregations here know/recognise this person, because he has worked very hard to tell people about God2's Good News.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epainos: praise, approval, recognition, fame LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">epainos: praise, approval, recognition, fame LITERALLY: And we are sending with him the brother who is praised in the gospel among all the churches<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Jama'at pung pamimpin dong ju pili ame sang dia ko jalan sama-sama deng botong, ko tolong botong dalam botong pung karjá yang bae ni. Botong kasi jalan ini karjá, ko kasi tunju kotong pung Bos pung hebat, deng bekin yang bae kasi sang orang susa di Yerusalem.<bt>The leaders of the congregations have also chosen him to go together with us-exc, to help/assist us in this good work of ours-exc. We carry out this work, to show our-inc Bos's greatness/amazingness, and do what is good for those in difficulty in Yerusalem. [EXEG: Is this show God's glory? or glorify God? Gk genitive is vague enough that it could be either. In this context, it is most likely the latter [as in NLT]. But KM “botong kasi jalan ini karjá ko kasi tunju kotong pung Bos pung hebat” can carry both readings. Our protocol is where we can reflect the same ambiguities that are in the Gk, we should. Other problem: I'm not sure ALT “botong kasi jalan ini karjá ko angka tinggi-tinggi kotong pung Bos pung nama” makes any real sense in KM. CHECK.] [EXEG: EXEG: OV do what is good for you there? or “do what is good for those in difficulty in Jerusalem? Gk is vague, but context clearly favours the latter (as in NLT, Uma BT).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xeirotonew: choose, elect by vote, select"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">xeirotonew: choose, elect by vote, select for definite task sunekdemos: traveling companion, travel with<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>prothumia: willingness, readiness, good will LITERALLY: and not only that, but he has been chosen by the churches to travel with us in this gracious work of ours, for the glory of the Lord and for our good will<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Botong cari jalan ko bekin yang batúl, ko biar sonde ada orang yang bisa tudu sang botong bilang, botong sonde karjá batúl waktu antar ini doi kasi pi orang yang parlú dong.<bt>We-exc look for ways to do what is right, so that there is nobody who is able to accuse us saying, we don't work right/correctly when taking/escorting this money to the people who need it. [NOTE to daughter translations: Q: /cari jalan/ can imply uncertainty. A: Yes. On the one hand it nicely reflects the Gk “avoiding this, lest” “guarding against this, lest” - the point being they are taking deliberate and proactive steps to avoid any appearance or charges of corruption. I think CEV undertranslates on this point. On the other hand, KM /cari jalan/ might also be read as not having succeeded, although that was not the response from the UNSs. So ALT: botong usaha karás ko bekin yang batúl… (problem: usaha is often hard to reflect in daughter lgs).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stellw: avoid, try to avoid, keep"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">stellw: avoid, try to avoid, keep away mwmaomai: find fault, blame, censure<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>hadrotes: abundance, liberal, plentiful diakonoumeneei hyph' heemoon: administered by us<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>LITERALLY: avoiding this: that no one blame us in this abundance which is administered by us;</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Te botong ada pikir bae-bae ko bekin yang batúl dari hati yang barisi di Tuhan Allah pung muka, deng di orang pung muka ju.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we are thinking carefully to to what is right from/with a clean liver before God, and before people too. [EXEG: Gk “regard for good things” is vague. Added “bekin yang batúl dari hati yang barisi” for clarifying higher level cohesion.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pronoew: take care, take thought for,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pronoew: take care, take thought for, take into consideration kalos: good, honorable, useful, noble<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>enwpios: before, in front of LITERALLY: for we take thought for what is good not only before the Lord but also before people.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="8:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 3:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Naa, ada satu sodara lai yang botong ada utus pi sama-sama deng Titus dong ko antar itu doi. Botong su pareksa ame sang dia banya kali. Ais botong su tau dia mau karjá banting tulang kasi sang bosong. Dia samangat bagitu, tagal dia su tau bilang, bosong ada bekin yang batúl.<bt>Naa [+shift], There is another sibling whom we-exc are sending/commissioning together with Titus to take/escort that money. We have examined (thoroughly) him many times. So then we already know he is going to work hard for you. He is enthusiastic like that, because he already knows that you are doing what is right. [EXEG: Q: is this brother here the same or different as the one mentioned in vs.18? A: Gk grammar is vague. The article says it is simply a known referent. So it could be anaphoric (the one in vs.18), or someone else who is known to the readers. Interpreting this is conjecture based on context. Ex. Summ. disappointingly does not address the question. NLT, CEV, TB2, TH, Uma, Hughes, all conclude this is a different person than the one in vs.18. Our protocols say we follow the TB in this situation. But it has to be introduced with a presentational clause, so this verse has been restructured from an earlier version.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pepoithesis: trust, confidence pollakis: often, frequently,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pepoithesis: trust, confidence pollakis: often, frequently, many times<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>LITERALLY: And we are sending with them our brother whom we have tested often as being earnest in many things, but now more earnest, because of the great confidence he has in you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Kalo ada orang yang tanya so'al Titus, na, kasi tau sang dong bilang, Titus tu, beta pung sodara yang ada karjá deng beta tarús kasi sang bosong. Orang parcaya di tampa laen ju su pili ame dong pung orang, ko dong iko antar ini doi pi Yerusalem. Dong su bakumpul ko mau pi. Titus ada sama-sama deng dong. Dong samua nanti kasi tunju Kristus pung hebat bagitu.<bt>If anyone asks about Timus, na, tell them, that Titus is my sibling who is working with me continually for you/on your behalf. Believers in other places have also selected their (own) people, so they can accompany escorting this money to Yerusalem. They have already gathered wanting to leave. Titus is together with them. All of them will show Kristus' greatness/amazingness like that. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: 8:6 says they are wanting Titus to come, so removed OV that he was already in Korintus. “Already gathered... with Titus” is from higher level context to make the transition from vs. 23 to 24 make sense. Q: Was the OV structure adequately reflecting 1st 3 words of the Gk? A: No. Restructured to do that. NLT, Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV where did they get"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">!@ CEV where did they get "two" from??</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eite: whether koivoonos: companion, partner|i(23) (23)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">eite: whether koivoonos: companion, partner<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>sunergos: working with LITERALLY: Whether concerning Titus, he is my partner and fellow worker for you; whether our brothers, they are messengers of the churches, to the glory of Christ.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Jadi bosong musti kasi tunju sayang sang orang dong yang antar itu doi. Deng kasi tunju sang dong ju, kanapa botong suka omong bésar so'al bosong. Deng bagitu, orang parcaya dari jama'at di mana-mana tau batúl bilang, bosong ada sayang sang dong.<bt>So (consequently) you-pl must show love to the people who escort that money. And also show them why we-exc like to boast about you. In that way, believers from congregations everywhere will really know that you love them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="endeiksis: proof kauxesis: boasting, pride in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">endeiksis: proof kauxesis: boasting, pride in someone<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>endeiknumi: demonstrate, give proof proswpos: face, before<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>LITERALLY: Therefore show them the proof of your love and our boasting about you, before the churches.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Doi bantuan kasi orang Kristen di Yerusalem<bt>Financial assistance/aid for the Kristen people in Yerusalem</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Yang batúl, beta sonde usa tulis lai, ko minta bosong bantu Tuhan pung orang parcaya dong.<bt>Actually/in truth, I don't need to write further, to request you to help/assist (+financial) God2's believers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="perissos: superfluous, unnecessary LITERALLY: For indeed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">perissos: superfluous, unnecessary LITERALLY: For indeed concerning the [service / help] for the saints, it is unnecessary for me to write to you,<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te beta su tau bosong ada pung samangat bantu orang bagitu. Beta ju suka kasi tau sang orang parcaya di Makedonia so'al bosong pung hati bae. Beta su carita bilang, bosong dari propinsi Akaya su siap dari taon lalu ko mau kirim doi bantuan. Beta ju ada carita so'al bosong pung samangat yang bekin orang laen mau iko bantu sang orang susa dong.<bt>Cuz I already know you are eager/have enthusiasm to help/assist people like that. I also like to/often tell the believers in Makedonia about your goodness/grace/kindness/generosity. I have told/narrated that you-pl from the province of Akaya were already prepared from last year to send financial assistance. I also was telling/narrating about your enthusiasm that makes other people want to participate in helping/assisting people in difficulty.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prothumia: willingness, eagerness paraskeuazw: prepare, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">prothumia: willingness, eagerness paraskeuazw: prepare, be ready<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>erithizw: stir, arouse LITERALLY: for I know your eagerness, which I boast about concerning you in Macedonia, that since last year Achaia has been ready, and your [enthusiasm/eagerness] has stirred most of them.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais beta su kirim kotong pung sodara dong, ko kasi tunju bilang, apa yang botong su carita so'al bosong, sonde omong kosong. Beta kasi tau bagitu, ko biar bosong basiap memang.<bt>So I also sent our-inc siblings to show that what we-exc have told about you is not empty talk/lies/b.s. I tel (you) like that, so that you can be prepared beforehand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kenow: make empty meros: matter, case,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kenow: make empty meros: matter, case, affair, part<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: And I send the brothers, so that our boasting about you would not be empty in this matter, that just as I said, you may be prepared,</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te kalo ada orang Makedonia datang sama-sama deng beta, ais bosong balóm siap, na, kotong samua malu. Jang sampe beta pung parcaya sang bosong, sonde ada pung dasar.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if there are Makedonia people who come together with me, and then you are not yet ready, na, all of us-inc will be embarrassed. May it not be that my faith/trust in you has no foundation/basis.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aparaskeuastos: unprepared, not ready heuriskw: find|i(4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">aparaskeuastos: unprepared, not ready heuriskw: find<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>kataisxune: be humiliated, disgraced, put to shame mepws: lest somehow<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>hupostasis: confidence LITERALLY: lest somehow if any Macedonians come with me and find you unprepared, we will be put to shame--and you too--because of this confidence.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Andia ko beta pikir bilang, ada lebe bae kotong pung sodara dong pi lebe dolo di bosong, ko bosong samua bisa ator itu doi bantuan iko bosong pung janji dolu. Bosong musti kasi dari bosong pung hati bae. Jang kasi deng kake'ek.<bt>That's why I think that it would be better/best for our-inc siblings to go on ahead to you, so all of you can arrange/put in order that financial assistance according to your previous promise/commitment. You-pl must give from your goodness/grace/ kindness/generosity. Don't give stingily.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaník = 1) a kind of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">kaník = 1) a kind of crab; 2) sakikir</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anagkaios: necessary hetoimos: ready|i(5) (5) |rhegeomai:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">anagkaios: necessary hetoimos: ready<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>hegeomai: consider, think, regard parakalew: urge, requuest, implore, appeal to<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>pleoneksia: greediness, grudgingly given, stingy proepaggellw: promise before<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>proerxomai: go forward, go before prokatagellw: foretell<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>prokatartizw: get ready, arrange in advance, make up beforehand eulogia: blessing, benefit, willing gift<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: Therefore I thought it necessary to urge the brothers that they go beforehand to you and arrange in advance the benefit you had promised, to be ready as a willing gift and not as a stingy one.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dia pung parinsip bagini: &lt;&lt;Orang yang cuma tanam bibit sadiki sa, nanti dapa hasil sadiki ju. Orang yang tanam bibit banya deng sonde tahan-tahan, nanti dapa kambali hasil deng berkat bam-banya ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>The principle is like this: “A person who only plants a few seeds, will later get a small yield. A person who plants many seeds without restraint, will later get back a high/bountiful yield and blessings.” [EXEG: Gk word choice here may indicate attitude as well as amount.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde kobo-kobo = kake'ek ; kobo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">sonde kobo-kobo = kake'ek ; kobo = hold, peluk ; kobo-kobo = peluk kuat-kuat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="speirw: sow, plant pheidomenws: sparingly|i(6) (6)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">speirw: sow, plant pheidomenws: sparingly<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>therizw: reap, harvest eulogiais: praise, blessing, benefit, *large amount<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: The point is this: the one who plants sparingly will reap sparingly, and the one who plants from abundance will reap from abundance.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Tiap orang musti putus sandiri, dia mau kasi barapa. Jang kasi deng kurang hati. Jang kasi cuma tagal orang paksa. Te Tuhan Allah ada sayang sang orang yang kasi dari hati tabuka.<bt>Each person must decide on their own/for themselves, how much s/he wants to give. Don't give with a lacking liver (reluctantly). Don't just give because someone is forcing/pressuring. Cuz (elaboration) God love the person who gives from an open (willing, generous) liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kurang hati = reluctant (here)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">kurang hati = reluctant (here)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proairew: decide, determine, make up the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">proairew: decide, determine, make up the mind, prefer anagke: necessity, compulsion, force<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>hilaros: cheerful, glad, merry LITERALLY: Each one just as he has decided in his heart, not from sorrow or from compulsion, for God loves a cheerful giver.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang ada orang yang coba paksa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Jang ada orang yang coba paksa orang laen ko kasi.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Tuhan mampu kasi bosong samua macam berkat. Dia ju mampu kasi lebe-lebe, ko biar bosong sonde kurang satu apa ju. Te kalo bosong ada parlú, na, nanti bosong dapa lebe dari cukup. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa bagi kasi bosong pung lebe ko tolong samua karjá yang bae.<bt>God2 is able to give you all kinds of *blessings. He is also able to give you excess, to that you aren't lacking in anything. Cuz (elaboration) if/when you have a need, na, you will get more than enough. In that way, you can divide out/share your excess to help all good work. [NOTE to daughter translations: samua karjá yang bae = “do all good work”; samua karjá deng bae = “do all work well”; careful the teams don't get sloppy.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="autarkeia: sufficiency, competence, enough LITERALLY: But"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">autarkeia: sufficiency, competence, enough LITERALLY: But God is able to give you every blessing in abundance, so that you may always have enough of everything, and you may have more than enough for every good cause,<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te kalo bosong ada parlú, na,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Te kalo bosong ada parlú, na, nanti bosong dapa lebe dari cukup. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa bekin samua karjá yang bae.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ada tatulis di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>It is written in the Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah suka bagi kasi orang malarat dong,<bt>“God likes to distribute out to the poor people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dari Dia pung hati bae.<bt>from His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia bekin yang batúl tarús,<bt>He continues to do what is right/correct,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te Dia pung hati lurus batahan tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) His straight/righteous liver, endures continually.” [EXEG: ‘His’ = God; NRSV, TB.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skorpizw: scatter penes: poor, needy|i(9) (9)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">skorpizw: scatter penes: poor, needy<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: just as it has been written, "He scattered, he has given to the poor, his righteousness remains forever."</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 112:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Tuhan yang kasi bibit, ko orang tani dong tanam. Tuhan yang kasi makanan, ko kotong bisa makan. Tuhan yang sama tu, yang nanti kasi bosong berkat ko biar bosong bisa bekin yang batúl. Itu sama ke bosong jadi orang tani, ais Tuhan kasi bibit sang bosong ko bosong tanam. Deng bosong pung hasil tu, Dia bekin tamba hari, tamba banya.<bt>God2 is the one who gives seed so farmers to plant. God2 is the one who gives food for us to be able to eat. that same God2 is the one who later will give you-pl blessing/s so that you can do what is right. That is like you are farmers, and so God2 gives seed for you to plant. And your result/yield/crop, He adds days, adds amount (=keeps increasing).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epixoregew: give, supply, grant sperma: seed,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">epixoregew: give, supply, grant sperma: seed, earthly grainseed<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>xoregew: provide, supply plethunw: increase, multiply<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>sporos: seed, store of seed, seed which has been sown, crop auxanw: grow, cause to grow, increase<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>genema: product, fruit, yield, harvest LITERALLY: And he that gives seed to the sower and bread for food will also supply and increase your store of seed and will cause the product of your righteousness to grow;<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 55:10</note><v n="11" />Te Tuhan mau kasi sang bosong lebe dari bosong sandiri pung parlú, ko biar bosong bisa bantu orang laen dong dari bosong pung hati bae. Jadi kalo bosong su bantu orang laen bagitu, nanti dong minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 wants to give you more than you yourselves need, so that you are able to help/assist (+financial) other people from your goodness/grace/kindness/generosity. So (consequently) if/when you help/assist other people like that, they will give thanks to God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="angka hati = pray, bring desire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">angka hati = pray, bring desire (to God)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ploutizw: make rich, enrich haplotes: generosity,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ploutizw: make rich, enrich haplotes: generosity, liberality, giving free from ulterior motives<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>katergazomai: achieve, bring about, produce, create euxaristia: thankfulness<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: In everything being enriched for all generosity, which through us will produce thanksgiving to God--</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Te itu bantuan yang bosong kasi sang Tuhan pung orang di sana tu, pasti tolong sang dong. Deng itu ju bekin bosong minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>Cuz that help/assistance (+financial) which you give to God2's people there, will surely help/assist (non-financial) them. And that also makes you-pl give thanks to God2. [EXEG: Q: Who will give thanks to God? A: Gk is vague, but this has to be looked at together with vs. 11. Gk in vs.11 clearly implies (they) will give thanks to God because of us (what we do). Vs. 12 could be either resulting in (you-pl) giving thanks to God, or (many people) giving thanks to God. We chose you-pl because one of the main points of vs. 6-10 (context) is the indirect benefit that comes back to the giver (here: the Corinthians).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leitourgia: service, free service, service to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">leitourgia: service, free service, service to the state, religious service prosanaplerow: supply, replenish, fill up<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>husterema: need, want, deficiency LITERALLY: for the performing of this service not only supplies the need, but also overflows in many thanksgivings to God--<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te waktu bosong bantu orang laen dong, itu kasi tunju bukti bilang, bosong ada parcaya deng sunggu-sunggu. Itu ju bekin orang laen dong angka puji sang Tuhan Allah. Te dong bisa lia bosong pung parcaya sang Kristus pung Kabar Bae tu, sonde omong kosong. Itu, tagal bosong ada bekin iko bosong pung parcaya. Ais waktu bosong kasi bantuan dari bosong pung hati bae sang dong, deng kasi orang laen ju, itu yang bekin dong angka puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) when you help/assist (+financial) other people, that shows evidence/proof that you are believing in earnest/sincere/genuine. That also makes other people lift praises to God. Cuz (elaboration) they can see your faith in Kristus' Good News is not empty talk/lies/b.s. That is because you are doing according to your belief. so, when you give help/assistance (+financial) from your goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to them and to other people as well, na, that is what makes them lift praises to God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokime: test, quality of being approved,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">dokime: test, quality of being approved, character hupotage: subjection, subordination, obedience<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>haplotes: generosity, liberalty LITERALLY: under the test of this service, you will glorify God by your obedience in acknowledging the gospel of Christ and by the generosity of your contribution for them and for all,<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu bosong ada tolong sang orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Waktu bosong ada tolong sang orang laen dong, itu kasi tunju bukti, bilang, bosong pung parcaya tu, sunggu-sunggu. Itu ju bekin orang dong ba'omong banya so'al Tuhan Allah, te orang dong bisa/dapa lia, bilang, bosong pung parcaya sang Kristus pung Kabar Bae tu, sonde omong kosong. Te bosong bekin iko bosong pung parcaya. Ais, waktu bosong kasi bantuan dari bosong pung hati bae sang dong, deng sang orang laen dong, itu bekin dong omong banya so'al Tuhan Allah ju.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Naa, orang yang tarima ame bantuan dari bosong, nanti sambayang kasi sang bosong. Dong ju rindu mau lia sang bosong, tagal Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae bam-banya sang bosong.<bt>Naa [shift] the people who receive the help/assistance from you, will pray for you. They also yearn to see you, because God has shown His goodness/ grace/ kindness/generosity to you. [EXEG: Q: shown to you, or shown through you (as NLT)? A: NLT1 is the only source that interpreted Gk epi as ‘through’ here. The normal dative for epi ‘upon’ is the sense of ‘to’ followed by other sources in Ex. Summ. Note NLT2 seems to  have seen this as incorrect and have corrected it. So “used you to show His abundant grace to them” seems to be going beyond the text.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deesis: prayer epipothew: desire, long for|i(14)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">deesis: prayer epipothew: desire, long for<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>huperballw: surpass LITERALLY: and by their prayer for you, they long for you because of the surpassing grace of God in you.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ma Tuhan Allah su parsén ame kasi kotong satu Hadia yang talalu bagus. Andia Yesus! Dia pung harga tu, lebe dari samua! Andia ko kotong samua sama-sama minta sang Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;&lt;Tarima kasi!&gt;&gt;<bt>But God has already presented us-inc (freely) with a gift that is too beautiful/pleasing/awesome. That is Yesus! His price/value is more than everything (else)! That is why all of us-inc together say to God, “Thank you!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anekdiegetos: indescribable Christ as gift; in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">anekdiegetos: indescribable Christ as gift; in Verse 11 it's money as gift. Talk about them the same way?<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: Thanks to God for his indescribable gift.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, kotong samua sama-sama minta &lt;&lt;Tarima"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Jadi, kotong samua sama-sama minta &lt;&lt;Tarima kasi!&gt;&gt; sang Tuhan Allah, tagal Dia su parsén kasi kotong satu kadó yang talalu bagus. Andia, Yesus! Dia pung harga tu, lebe dari samua!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus ada bela so'al dia pung karjá kasi sang Kristus<bt>Paulus defends his work for Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Beta, Paulus sandiri, yang tulis di sini. Pasti ada dari bosong yang pikir bagini: kalo beta ada sama-sama deng bosong, na, beta malu omong taráng-taráng. Ma kalo beta jao dari bosong, beta barani omong deng sonde pake pele-pele. Bagitu, to? Padahal beta minta ko bosong dengar sang beta, tagal Kristus pung hati manis sang bosong, deng Dia suka kasi hati sang bosong.<bt>I, Paulus myself, am the one writing here. Surely there are those of you who think like this: if/when I were together with you, na, I would be shy/embarrassed/ashamed to speak clearly/openly. But if/when I am far from you, I have the courage to speak without restraint/boldly. It's like that, right? Whereas in fact, I request that you listen to me, because of Kristus' kindness/gentleness to you, and (because) He likes to be magnanimous/patient attention/permissive to you. [EXEG: NLT; “I appeal to you by...” Gk /dia/ ‘by, through (means), on account of (reason)’. The connector ‘because’ is the closest way to reflect that relationship in these lgs. See CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi hati = (Mus-can be negative)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">kasi hati = (Mus-can be negative) give undo attention [CHECK with UNS]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prautes: gentleness, humility, courtesy, considerateness, meekness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">prautes: gentleness, humility, courtesy, considerateness, meekness [grace-imparted disposition by which we accept without resistance the disciplines of God] epieikeia: mildness, leniency, clemency, gentleness, graciousness, kindness [from a position of dignity and authority]<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>tapeinos: low, humble, timid, modest, opposite of boldness apeimi: be absent<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>tharrew: be confident, bold, brave LITERALLY: And I myself Paul urge you through the gentleness and leniency of Christ, who face to face indeed am timid among you, but absent bold among you;<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beta malu omong taráng-taráng kasi sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">beta malu omong taráng-taráng kasi sang bosong waktu beta ada sama-sama deng bosong, ma beta sonde malu omong tar pake pele kalo beta jao dari bosong. Bagitu, to?</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ma ada dari bosong saparu yang sonde mau dengar sang beta. Dong omong bilang, botong pung bekin-bekin, sama ke orang laen di ini dunya dong pung bekin-bekin ju. Jadi nanti kalo beta pi sana, mangkali beta musti omong sonde pake pele-pele kasi sang dong. Andia ko beta kasi tau memang sang bosong samua, ko biar nanti beta pi sana, na, beta sonde usa omong karás sang dong.<bt>But there are some of you who don't want to listen to me. They talk saying, what we do, is like other people in this world. So (consequently), later when I go there, perhaps/probably/there's a good chance I must speak without restraint/forthrightly/boldly to them. That is why I'm telling all of you beforehand, so that later when I come there, na, I won't need to speak harshly with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deomai: ask, beg parapeimi: be present|i(2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">deomai: ask, beg parapeimi: be present<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>pepoithesis: trust logizomai: consider, count on, think about, ponder, let the mind dwell on, propose, purpose, have in mind, reckon, reason<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>tolmaw: dare, be courageous, be bold peripatew: go about, walk, live, act<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: but I beg that when I am present I may not have to show boldness with the confidence which I think to be bold against some who consider us as acting in a worldly manner.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Biar kotong ju manusia biasa, ma kalo kotong ada bakanjar deng orang laen, kotong jang pasang kaki ko babakalai sama ke orang di ini dunya yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Even though we-inc are also merely humans, nevertheless if/when we are arguing/fighting with other people, we should not make the effort/strive to fight2 like people in this world who don't know/recognise God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="strateuw: do military service, carry on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">strateuw: do military service, carry on a war, campaign kosmou: needs to sound clearly non-Christian<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: For we live in the flesh, but we do not campaign in a worldly manner--</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te kalo kotong ada babakalai deng orang, jang lupa, te kotong pung sanjata sonde sama deng orang di ini dunya pung. Ais kalo kotong ada babakalai deng orang kapala batu yang bakanjar deng kotong, na, kotong ju ada Tuhan pung kuasa yang bisa bongkar kasi ancor orang pung alasan.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if/when we are fighting2 with people, don't forget, that our-inc weapons are not the same as people in this world have. So/then if/when we are fighting2 with stubborn people who are arguing with us, na, we also have God2's power/authority which can dismantle/break down/apart destroying people's reasons/excuses.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hoplon: weapon strateia: campaign, expedition, military"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hoplon: weapon strateia: campaign, expedition, military service, [strategy]<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>kathairesis: destruction oxurwma: stronghold, fortress, strong fortification<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>logismos: thought, reasoning, argument, imagination kathairew: destroy<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: for the weapons of our warfare are not worldly, but have power through God to destroy strongholds--destroying arguments</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Tuhan pung kuasa bisa bongkar samua parinsip yang malawan sang Tuhan, yang bekin orang sonde mau kanál sang Dia. Dia pung kuasa ju bisa kasi tunju jalan, ko ganti kotong pung cara pikir yang lama, deng cara pikir yang baru. Deng bagitu, kotong balajar ko pikir iko Kristus pung ajaran.<bt>God2's power/authority can dismantle/break down/apart every principle that opposes God2, which makes people not want to know/recognise Him. His power/authority is also able to show the way, to replace our-inc old way of thinking, with a new way of thinking. In that way, we can learn to think according to Kristus' teaching/s.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parinsip ~ prinsip= write it this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">parinsip ~ prinsip= write it this way for KM ; !@ CEV "make them obey Christ" misses it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupswma: height, exaltation epairw: raise up,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hupswma: height, exaltation epairw: raise up, rise up, resist, oppose<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>aixmalwtizw: capture, make prisoner; capturing every thought: persuasion, make um tink diffren kine? Give examples. noema: thought, purpose, plot, design<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: and every high thing that rises up against the knowledge of God, and capturing every thought for the obedience of Christ,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan pung kuasa ju bisa kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Tuhan pung kuasa ju bisa kasi tunju jalan, ko biar kotong pung cara pikir yang lama tu, su ganti deng yang baru. Deng bagitu, itu ajar kotong ko pikir iko Kristus pung ajaran.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 12:2</note><v n="6" />Banya dari bosong su mulai dengar-dengar sang Kristus, deng bekin iko Dia pung mau samua. Ma ada saparu dari bosong yang masi sonde mau dengar-dengar sang Dia. Jadi botong su siap ko hukum sang dong yang sonde mau dengar sang Dia.<bt>Many of you have begun to listen to/obey Kristus, and do according to His whole will/desires. But there are some of you who still don't want to listen to/obey Him. So (consequently), we-exc are ready/prepared to punish those who don't want to listen to/obey Him. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hetoimos: ready, prepared ekdikew: punish, avenge"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hetoimos: ready, prepared ekdikew: punish, avenge someone<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>parakoe: disobedience, unwillingness to hear, failing to listen hotan: whenever<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>plerow: make full, fill up, complete, finish hupokoe: obedience<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: being ready to punish every disobedience when your obedience is complete.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Bosong suka lia hal yang kantara dari luar sa. Ma bosong musti lia orang pung hati. Jadi, kalo ada orang yang anggap diri Kristus pung utusan, na, inga bae-bae. Te botong ju Kristus pung utusan, sama ke dia.<bt>You like to just look at things that are visible on the outside. But you must look at a person's/people's liver/s. So (consequently) if/when there is a person who considers himself Kristus' *apostle (sent/commissioned one), na, remember/think carefully. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc are also Kristus' apostle, just like him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="blepw: look, notice proswpon: face, before,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">blepw: look, notice proswpon: face, before, in front<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>peithw: be convinced, be sure, certain logizomai: consider, think about, ponder, remind himself<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: You look at things according to the outward appearance. If anyone thinks he is of Christ, let him consider this again that just as he is of Christ, so also are we.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Mangkali bosong pikir kata, beta ada omong bésar lebe-lebe so'al kuasa yang kotong pung Bos ada kasi sang botong. Bagitu, to? Sonde! Te itu kuasa ada, ko kasi kuat sang bosong, bukan kasi ancor sang bosong. Jadi beta sonde kasi biar orang bekin malu sang beta tagal dong ada bongkar bekin rusak beta pung karjá.<bt>Perhaps/probably you are thinking that I am talking excessivly big (boasting) about the power/authority which our-inc Bos has given us-exc. It's like that, right? No! Cuz (elaboration) that power/authority exists to strengthen you, not to destroy/ruin/make fall apart you. So (consquently), I don't/won't allow a person to shame/embarrass me because they are dismantling/tearing apart and ruining My work. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mulu bésar = cerewet, grumpy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">mulu bésar = cerewet, grumpy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="perissoteros: greater, more, beyond kauxaomai: boast|i(8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">perissoteros: greater, more, beyond kauxaomai: boast<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>exousia: authority, right, power, jurisdiction oikodome: building, construction<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>kathairesis: destruction, tearing down, demolition aisxunw: be ashamed<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: For if I boast more concerning our authority/power, which the Lord gave for building you up and not your destruction, I am not ashamed,</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Beta sonde ada maksud ko mau bekin taku sang bosong deng beta pung surat dong.<bt>It is not my intention to frighten you with my letters.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokew: seem, appear ekphobew: frighten, scare,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">dokew: seem, appear ekphobew: frighten, scare, terrify<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: that I may not seem as if I would scare you by letters;</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ma itu orang dong ada omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang toe deng Paulus. Te biar dia pung surat karás deng hebat, ma kalo dia datang sandiri, dia kamatek angin, deng dia pung omong sonde ada pung kuasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But those people are talking saying, “Don't care/be concerned about Paulus. Cuz (elaboration) even if his letters are harsh and impressive, nevertheless if he came himself, he is weak/powerless/soft, and his speech/what he has to say has no power/authority.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mamalek"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">mamalek</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phemi: say, affirm, state, declare barus:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">phemi: say, affirm, state, declare barus: burdensome, heavy, weighty, impressive, severe, difficult<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>isxuros: strong, mighty, powerful, forceful, vigorous, effective parousia: presence, behavior<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>asthenes: weak, feeble, sick eksouthenew: despise, treat as nothing, of no account<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: that, it is said, his letters indeed are impressive and powerful, but his bodily presence is weak and his word doesn't count for anything.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Naa, biar ko itu orang yang omong kosong bagitu pikir ini hal: apa yang botong tulis dalam surat dari jao, sonde ada beda deng apa yang botong omong kalo botong datang di bosong pung teng-tenga.<bt>Naa, let those people who are empty talkng/lying/b.s.ing like that think about this matter: what we-exc write in a letter from afar, is no different from what we say if/when we come into your midst.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Let such people consider this,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Let such people consider this, that what we are by word through letters when absent, the same we do when present.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Itu orang dong ju suka angka-angka diri bilang, dong tu, Kristus pung utusan yang hebat. Botong sonde barani banding diri ke dong. Tau sandiri, to? Te botong sonde mungkin hebat sama ke dong na! Orang macam bagitu, cuma cari orang yang sama ke dong-dong sa. Ais dong badukung satu deng satu, tagal dong satu model na! Dong pung bodo lai!<bt>Those people also like to elevate themselves saying, they are Kristus' impressive/amazing *apostles. We-exc don't dare compare ourselves with them. You understand, right? [=idiom signalling there is another meaning] Cuz (elaboration) it's not likely/there's no way we are impressive like them na! [+obvious] People of that sort, only just look for people who are the same as themselves [grammatical construction carries sense of: surely nobody else could be like them]. So then they mutually support each other, because they are the same model/type/kind na! [+obvious] How dumb is that! (idiomatic) [cf. 11:5; +irony]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tau sandiri, to? = You know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Tau sandiri, to? = You know what I'm talking about. ; sama ke dong-dong sa = (carries sense of surely nobody else could be like them) ; basokong = badukung</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tolmaw: dare, presume egkrinw: classify, judge"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">tolmaw: dare, presume egkrinw: classify, judge among<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>sugkrinw: compare sunistemi: commend, present, introduce, recommend<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>metrew: measure suniemi: understand<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: For we do not dare to classify or compare ourselves with those who commend themselves; but they measuring themselves by themselves and comparing themselves with themselves, are without understanding.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ada orang yang suka angka-angka diri,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Ada orang yang suka angka-angka diri, bilang, dong tu, hebat. Botong sonde bekin diri sama ke dong. Botong ju sonde banding diri deng dong. Te orang macam bagitu, cari orang yang sama ke dong dolo, baru puji diri tagal dong sama. Waktu dong bekin bagitu, su jalás dong sonde mangarti apa-apa, iko Tuhan pung ukuran. Orang macam bagitu, cuma cari orang yang sama ke dong-dong sa. Ais, dong deng dong basokong satu deng satu, tagal dong satu model na!<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Padahal botong sandiri sonde omong bésar kalo sonde ada pung dasar. Botong cuma omong bagitu so'al itu tugas yang Tuhan su kasi sang botong. Apa yang botong su bekin kasi sang bosong, cuma iko apa yang Tuhan suru botong bekin sa. Te botong sonde karjá di luar itu.<bt>Whereas in fact, we-exc ourselves don't boast if there is no reason/foundation/basis. We only talk like that about that work/responsibility/mission which God2 has given us. What we have done for you, is only/merely in accord with what God2 ordered/commanded us to do. Cuz (elaboration) we don't work outside of that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ametros: immeasurable, beyond measure metron: measure|i(13)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ametros: immeasurable, beyond measure metron: measure<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>kanwn: sphere merizw: assign<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>ephikneomai: reach LITERALLY: But we do not boast beyond measure, but according to the measure of the sphere which God assigned us, a measure to reach as far as you.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Yang batúl, botong sonde omong lebe-lebe waktu botong ada omong bésar so'al bosong. Te botong ni, yang datang carita sang bosong so'al Kristus pung Kabar Bae. Bosong ju tarima botong pung omong. Kalo Tuhan sonde parná utus sang botong, ma botong ada omong bésar so'al bosong, na, itu yang sonde batúl.<bt>In truth, we don't talk too much (degree)/over the top when we are boasting about you. Cuz (elaboration) we are the ones who came and told/narrated to you about Kristus' Good News. You also accepted what we said. If God2 had never sent/commissioned us, but we were boasting about you, na, that would not be right.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="huperekteinw: overextend, stretch out beyond phthanw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">huperekteinw: overextend, stretch out beyond phthanw: come, arrive<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>Overdo: trying to do more than we need to, or should. LITERALLY: For we are not overextending ourselves as though we did not reach you, for we came to you with the gospel of Christ;<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Kalo orang laen yang karjá, na, botong sonde omong bésar bilang, itu tagal botong yang karjá. Te yang pantíng kasi botong ni, andia, bosong pung parcaya batamba kuat. Deng bagitu, botong pung hasil karjá di bosong dari dolu, batamba tarús.<bt>If another/different person is the one who does the work, na, we don't boast saying, that was because we were the ones who did the work. Cuz (elaboration) what is important for us, is, your faith gets increasingly strong. In that way, the results/fruits of our work among you from before, will continue to increase. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="allotrios: to another kopos: work, labor,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">allotrios: to another kopos: work, labor, toil<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>auksanw: grow megalunw: make large, enlarge, increase, grow<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>kanwn: sphere perisseia: surplus<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: not boasting of things beyond measure of other people's work, but having hope as your faith is increased, that we will be enlarged among you according to our measure, abundantly,</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ais botong bisa pi kasi tau Kristus pung Kabar Bae di tampa-tampa yang ada di bosong pung sablá, yang balóm ada orang karjá di situ. Deng bagitu, botong sonde batabrak deng orang laen yang su kasi jalan dia pung karjá lebe dolu.<bt>So then we are able to go tell Kristus' Good News in various places on the other side/beyond you-pl, which don't yet have anyone working there/that have no workers there. In that way, we-exc don't/won't collide/conflict with other people who have already been carrying out his/their work prior to that. [EXEG: NLT; NOTE to daughter translations: sphere can be 1) territorial, or 2) type of ministry (see NRSV “sphere of action” and LN “defined geographically and functionally”) Try to keep both interpretations open.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="huperekeina: beyond hetoios: ready|i(16) (16) |rLITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">huperekeina: beyond hetoios: ready<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: so that the gospel may be preached in lands beyond you, not boasting about work already done in another person's sphere.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Te di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi, ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo ada orang mau omong bésar, na, biar ko dia omong bésar so'al kotong pung Bos Tuhan Allah sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in the Scriptures it is written saying, “If there is a person who boasts, na, let him just boast about our-inc Bos, God.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the one who boasts,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the one who boasts, let him boast in the Lord;</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 9:24</note><v n="18" />Kalo satu orang omong bésar so'al dia pung diri, itu sonde ada pung arti apa-apa. Ma kalo kotong pung Bos yang angka puji so'al itu orang, na, itu dolo, baru hebat!<bt>If one person boasts about himself, that has no meaning/significance. But if our-inc Bos is the one who lifts praise about that person, na, now that's impressive! (idiomatic)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ grammar of idiom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">@@ grammar of idiom</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunistemi: commend, recommend, present, introduce dokimos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">sunistemi: commend, recommend, present, introduce dokimos: approve, accept, proved, genuine<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: For it is not the person who commends himself who is approved, but the one whom the Lord commends.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te yang pantíng tu, bukan orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Te yang pantíng tu, bukan orang omong bésar so'al dia pung diri. Ma yang pantíng, kalo kotong pung Bos yang angka puji so'al itu orang. Itu dolo, baru hebat!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus pung utusan yang batúl, deng utusan yang sonde batúl dong<bt>Kristus' *apostles that are true, and apostles that are not true</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Beta mau omong gila sadiki. Jadi coba dengar bae-bae sang beta doo! Bagini:<bt>I want to/am going to talk crazy a little. So (consequently) try to listen to me carefully! It's like this: [NOTE to daughter translations: ‘talk crazy’ is different from ‘talk like a crazy person (=incoherent)’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="allow me to speak outrageously, like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">allow me to speak outrageously, like a medieval clown/fool, over the top ; omong gila = speak foolishly ; gila-gila? maen gila = tease ; ke orang gila = incoherent ; harba-biruk =unsystematic, chaotically ; tukang lawak = clown trying to be funny, (but funny isn't an element here) "clown" is a Javanese category, but not a Timorese category.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ophelon: I wish that anexw: endure,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ophelon: I wish that anexw: endure, bear with<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>mikron: a little aphrosune: foolishness, lack of sense<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: I wish you would put up with me in a little foolishness; and indeed, put up with me!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="omong sadiki sama ke orang gila"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">omong sadiki sama ke orang gila</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />beta sama ke bosong pung bapa. Bosong sama ke beta pung ana nona yang su batunangan. Yang sama ke bosong pung tunangan tu, andia Kristus. Ais beta mau jaga bae-bae sang bosong, ko biar nanti bosong kawin deng bosong pung tunangan tu, bosong masi barisi. Jadi beta jaga bae-bae ko jang ada yang ganggu sang bosong, ko bekin rusak bosong pung parcaya.<bt>I am like your-pl father. You-pl are like my daughter who is engaged (to be married). The one who is like your fiancé is Kristus. So then I want to/am going to guard you carefully, so that later when you marry with your fiancé, you are still clean/pure/holy. So (consequently), I guard you carefully so that there is nobody who bothers/harrasses you, to ruin/damage/spoil your faith. [Uma BT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ganggu = 1) bother, disturb, 2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">ganggu = 1) bother, disturb, 2) harrass, sexual harrassment, 3) abuse, defile (sexually) (in increasing degree of being affected)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zelow: strive, exert oneself earnestly, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">zelow: strive, exert oneself earnestly, be deeply concerned about someone, desire zelos: zeal, jealousy<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>harmozw: join or give in marriage, engaged, promised in marriage parthenon: virgin, bride<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>hagnos: pure, holy, chaste paristemi: present<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: I am jealous for you with a godly jealousy, for I promised you to one man in marriage, as a pure virgin, to present you to Christ;</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Bosong sakarang ada iko sang Kristus pung jalan lurus deng hati yang barisi. Ma beta taku, jang sampe ada orang yang tipu ame sang bosong, ko bosong serong dari itu jalan, sama ke ular tipu ame sang Hawa dolu-dolu. Itu ular bisa tipu bagitu, tagal dia tukang putar-balek pung ba'i!<bt>You-pl now are following Kristus' straight/righteous path with clean/pure/holy livers. But I'm afraid lest there are people who deceive (successfully) you, so you deviate from that path, like that snake deceived (successfully) Hawa long ago. The snake could decieve like that, because he was the grandfather of deceivers/con artists!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phobew: be afraid, fear, be frightened"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">phobew: be afraid, fear, be frightened me pws: lest somehow, that perhaps<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>ophis: snake, serpent exapataw: deceive, cheat, entirely deceived [strong]<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>panourgia: cunning, craftiness, trickery, shrewdness noema: thought, mind<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>phtheirw: ruin, corrupt by misleading, destroy, spoil noema: thought<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>haplotes: simplicity, sincerity, uprightness, frankness, single-mindedness hagnotes: purity, sincerity<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: but I fear lest somehow, as the snake deceived Eve by his craftiness, your minds will be mislead from the sincerity and purity to/toward Christ.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 3:1-5, 13</note><v n="4" />Tiap kali orang macam bagitu dong datang di bosong, ais ajar sang bosong so'al Yesus model laen, yang sonde sama ke Yesus yang botong su ajar sang bosong tu, na, akurang ko bosong parcaya ame sang itu orang? Dolu bosong buka hati ko tarima ame Tuhan pung Roh Barisi ko Dia ator sang bosong. Jadi akurang ko sakarang bosong mau tarima ame satu roh model laen lai? Dolu bosong parcaya sang Kristus pung Kabar Bae yang botong kasi tau sang bosong. Jadi akurang ko sakarang bosong mau parcaya deng ajaran model laen lai?<bt>Each time a person of that sort comes to you-pl, and then teaches you about a different model/type/kind of Yesus, that is not the same as Yesus whom we-exc have already taught you, na, why do you believe that person? Previously you opened your livers (welcomed) to receive/accept God's Holy Spirit for Him to oversee/arrange/guide you. So (consequently), why is it that now you want to receive/accept a spirit of a different model/type/kind? Previously you believed in Kristus' Good News what we-exc told to you. So (consequently), why is it that now you want to believe in a teaching of a different model/type/kind?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lambanw: receive, get obtain [more passive]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">lambanw: receive, get obtain [more passive] dexomai: take, receive [more active] (not a hypothetical situation, UBS)<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>kalws: well anexw: endure, bear with, put up with<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: For if someone comes and preaches another Jesus, not the one we preached, or you receive a different spirit, not the one you received, or a different gospel, not the one you took, do you put up with it well?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Dong angka-angka diri bilang, dong tu, Tuhan pung utusan yang talalu hebat. Kira-kira dong pung hak ada lebe dari beta, ko? Sonde! Beta sonde iko pikiran bagitu.<bt>They elevate/promote themselves saying, they are God2's incredibly impressive/amazing *apostles. Perhaps (you think) their rights/authority are more than mine, or (what)? No, ó! I don't go along with thinking like that. [Cf. 10:12]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="husterew: to miss, be less than,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">husterew: to miss, be less than, be inferior huperlian: exceedingly, beyond measure, superior, superlative<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: for I consider I am not inferior to these superior apostles;</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Biar kata, beta sonde pintar omong pake bahasa tinggi-tinggi, ma beta mangarti batúl-batúl apa yang beta omong. Bosong su tau ini hal dong, tagal beta su kasi tunju ulang-ulang sang bosong.<bt>Even if, say, I am not skilled/clever in speaking using high language, nevertheless I really understand what I'm talking about. You already know these things, because I have shown them to you repeatedly. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="idiwtes: layman, unskilled, plain, untrained, uninstructed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">idiwtes: layman, unskilled, plain, untrained, uninstructed LITERALLY: but even if I am unskilled in speaking, not in knowledge, but in every way we have revealed all things to you.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bisa omong pake bahasa tinggi-tinggi,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">bisa omong pake bahasa tinggi-tinggi,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Waktu beta ada ajar Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae sang bosong, beta sonde minta bosong tanggong sang beta. Beta bekin diri kici, ko biar beta bisa angka-angka sang bosong. Kira-kira bosong mau kasi sala sang beta tagal itu, ko?<bt>When I was teaching God's Good News to you, I didn't request you to carry/be (financially) responsible for me. I made myself small/insignificant, so that I could raise/lift you up. Perhaps (you think) you want to fault/blame/accuse me because of that, or (what)?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tapeinow: lower, make lower, abase hupsow:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">tapeinow: lower, make lower, abase hupsow: lift up, exalt<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>dwrean: gratis, without cost, free LITERALLY: Did I commit a sin in abasing myself, so that you might be exalted, because I preached God's gospel to you without cost?<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te orang parcaya dari jama'at yang ada di tampa laen dong yang tanggong sang beta, ko biar beta bisa layani sang bosong. Itu sama ke beta ame dari dong, ko bisa tolong sang bosong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) believers from congregations in other/different places are the ones who carry/be (financially) responsible for me, so that I could serve/minister to you. That is like I take from them, to be able to help you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sulaw: rob opswnion: wages, support|i(8) (8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">sulaw: rob opswnion: wages, support<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: I robbed other churches by accepting support from them, in order to serve you,</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Waktu beta ada sama-sama deng bosong, ais beta ada pung parlú, beta sonde ganggu sang bosong, ko minta apa-apa dari bosong. Kotong pung sodara dong yang datang dari propinsi Makedonia yang bantu sang beta. Ma beta sonde parná bekin barát apa-apa sang bosong, deng beta ju sonde mau bekin bagitu beso-beso.<bt>When I am/was together with you, and then I had a need, I didn't bother you, to request anything from you. Our-inc siblings who came from the province of Makedonia were the ones who helped/assisted (financially) me. But I never burdened you with anything, and I also am not going to do that in the future (tomorrow-tomorrow).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beso-beso = on some occasions in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">beso-beso = on some occasions in the future</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pareimi: be present husterew: to miss|i(9)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pareimi: be present husterew: to miss<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>katanarkaw: to burden husterema: need<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>prosanaplerow: to fill up abares: lightweight<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>terew: to keep, hold, reserve, preserve LITERALLY: and when I was present with you, and was in need, I did not burden anyone; for the brothers who came from Macedonia met my need; and in everything I kept myself from burdening you, and I will keep myself from burdening you.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Filipi 4:15-18</note><v n="10" />Kristus pung Kata-kata, batúl. Beta ju yakin bilang, beta pung kata-kata ju batúl, tagal beta ta'ika deng Kristus. Sonde ada orang di propinsi Akaya sana yang bisa paróp beta pung mulu, deng larang sang beta ko jang omong bésar bilang, beta sonde bekin barát sang bosong bagitu.<bt>Kristus' Words/Message is true. I am also sure/confident that my words/message are also true, because I am bound/linked with Kristus. There is nobody in the province of Akaya there (remote) who can shut my mouth, and forbid me to boast that I do not burden you in that way. [EXEG: Ex. Summ #1.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phrassw: shut, close klima: district, region|i(10)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">phrassw: shut, close klima: district, region<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: As the truth of Christ is in me, this boast of mine will not be silenced in the region of Achaia.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Akurang ko beta omong bagini? Kira-kira, ini tagal beta sonde sayang sang bosong, ko? Biar bosong pikir bagitu, ma Tuhan sandiri tau beta pung sayang sang bosong.<bt>Why do I talk this way? Perhaps this is because I don't love you-pl, or (what)? Even if you think like that, nevertheless god2 himself knows my love for you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Why? Because I do not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Why? Because I do not love you? God knows.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Naa, hal yang beta su parná bekin dong, beta mau bekin tarús. Deng bagitu, orang yang suka angka-angka diri ko omong bésar bilang, apa yang dong bekin sama ke botong, na, dong tu, su sonde ada pung dasar lai.<bt>Naa, the thing/s I have done, I am going to continue to do. In that way, people who like to elevate/promote themselves and boast saying, their deeds are the same as ours-exc, na, they have no more basis.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ CEV missed &quot;boast&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">!@ CEV missed "boast"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekkoptw: remove, cut down, undermine, root"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ekkoptw: remove, cut down, undermine, root out, exterminate aphorme: pretest, excuse, reason<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>thelw: wish, desire, want, like LITERALLY: And what I do I will continue to do, in order to undermine the excuse of those who desire to make excuses, who would like to boast that they are found just as we are.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Dong bilang Tuhan yang utus sang dong. Dong tu, orang karjá yang suka tipu orang! Dong coba-coba bekin diri sama ke Kristus pung utusan yang batúl. Padahal itu samua omong kosong sa!<bt>They say God2 is the one who sent/commissioned them. They are workers who like to deceive people! They keep trying to make themselves like Kristus' true *apostles. Whereas in fact all that is just empty talk/lies/b.s.!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="!@ NLT missed &quot;deceitful workers&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">!@ NLT missed "deceitful workers"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dolios: deceitful metasxematizw: transform|i(13) (13) |rLITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">dolios: deceitful metasxematizw: transform<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: For such men are false apostles, deceitful workmen, disguising themselves as apostles of Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Bosong jang heran, é! Te setan dong pung bos ju coba-coba bekin diri sama ke Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga yang bawa taráng deng hati bae.<bt>You should not be surprised, é! Cuz (elaboration) the boss of the evil spirits keep trying to make himself like God's *angel (underling) from heaven who brings light and/with a good liver (grace/kindness, generosity). [NOTE: KM construction /yang bawa CHARACTERISTIC/ is also used in John's writings ‘water that brings life’ etc..]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thauma: wonder ho Satanaas: da Devil|i(14)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">thauma: wonder ho Satanaas: da Devil<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: And no wonder, for Satan himself is disguised as an angel of light;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sama ke Tuhan Allah pung ana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">sama ke Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga yang pung hati bae.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Andia ko bosong jang heran kalo dia pung orang karjá ju coba-coba bekin diri sama ke orang yang karjá deng hati lurus. Ma ati-ati, te Tuhan Allah nanti balas dong pung jahat.<bt>That is why you should not be surprised if his workers also keep trying to make themselves like a person who works with a straight/righteous liver. But be careful, cuz (elaboration) God will repay/reciprocate their evil.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="megas: great LITERALLY: therefore it is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">megas: great LITERALLY: therefore it is no great thing if his servants also disguise themselves as servants of righteousness, whose end will correspond to their deeds.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus pung utusan yang batúl, pikol sangsara macam-macam waktu dong kasi tau orang so'al Tuhan Yesus<bt>Kristus' true apostles bear/experience various sorts of suffering when they tell people about the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Kalo bosong mau, na, biar ko beta omong gila sadiki lai. Te beta mau coba-coba omong sombong.<bt>If you-pl will let me, na, allow me to talk crazy a little further. Cuz (elaboration) I'm going to try and talk arrogantly. [NOTE to daughter translations--make consistent with 11:1.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="allow me to speak outrageously puku"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">allow me to speak outrageously puku tiang, kaná tembok = omong pi orang laen, padahal tujuan orang laen</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aphrwn: foolish, a fool, ignorant LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">aphrwn: foolish, a fool, ignorant LITERALLY: I repeat: let no one think me foolish, but if you do, then accept me as a fool, so that I too may boast a little.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Yang beta tulis sakarang ko angka-angka diri bagini ni, cuma mau omong gila sa. Te beta pung omong ni, sonde ba'akar di kotong pung Bos.<bt>What I am writing now to elevate myself in this way here, is merely crazy talk. Cuz (elaboration) my speech/what I am saying here, is not rooted/sourced in our-inc Bos.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang lawak = jokester, gagster (Javanese"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">tukang lawak = jokester, gagster (Javanese category, focus on funny; but not Timorese/Kupang category)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupostasis: confidence, conviction, assurance, steadfastness LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hupostasis: confidence, conviction, assurance, steadfastness LITERALLY: What I am saying in this confident boasting, I say not according to the Lord, but as a fool.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ada banya orang yang suka angka-angka diri iko manusia di ini dunya pung biasa. Jadi beta ju mau omong bésar iko dong.<bt>There are many people who like to elevate/promote themselves according to the norms/customs of humans in this world/in the way humans normally do. So (consequently) I also want to boast in the way they do.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since many are boasting the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since many are boasting the way the world does, I too will boast.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Te bosong yang anggap diri orang pikir lurus, kalo nae katumu deng satu orang otak kea, na, bosong kasi biar deng hati luas, to?<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you-pl who think yourselves clear/straight/logical thinkers, if (you) happen to meet/encounter a turtle-brained person (idiom: slow witted), na, you just put up with it/them patiently/generous (attitude), right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="urut dada = accept, patient ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">urut dada = accept, patient ; nae katumu = UNS happen to meet (without intent)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hedews: gladly anexw: endure, put up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hedews: gladly anexw: endure, put up with, bear with, tolerate. IRONY<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: For you gladly put up with fools, being wise yourselves.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo bosong katumu satu tukang lawak,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Kalo bosong katumu satu tukang lawak, na, bosong tahan diri deng hati luas, to? Te bosong anggap diri orang yang pikir lurus, to?</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Kalo orang laen bekin apa-apa sang bosong, na, bosong kasi biar sang dong sa. Conto ke: kalo ada orang bekin sang bosong jadi sama ke dong pung budak, na, bosong kasi biar sa. Kalo ada orang curi ame bosong pung barang, na, bosong kasi biar sa. Kalo ada orang tipu ame sang bosong, na, bosong kasi biar sa. Kalo ada orang angka diri ke orang bésar, deng anggap enteng sang bosong ke orang kici sa, na, bosong kasi tenga sa. Bagitu ju, kalo ada orang tampeleng sang bosong, na, bosong kasi tenga sa.<bt>If other people do anything to you-pl, na, you just let them/put up with them. For example: if there is a person who makes you/treats you as their slave, na, you just let them/put up with them. If there is a person who steals your belongings, na, you just let them/put up with them. If there is a person who decieves you, na, you just let them/put up with them. If there is a person who elevates themselves as an important person, and view you with contempt as if you are an unimportant person, na, you just let them/put up with them. It's the same if there is a person who slaps you around, na, you just let them/put up with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE: in the discussion of irony"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">NOTE: in the discussion of irony in vs. 20-21, Paul is not comparing himself with the receivers of these injustices, but with the doers/perpetrators (in vs. 21). So it doesn't work to reconstruct vs. 20 as “Surely you woudln't put up with someone who XX!”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katadoulow: enslave katesthiw: eat up, consume,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">katadoulow: enslave katesthiw: eat up, consume, devour, swallow, destroy, exploit, rob<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>lambanw: take, take advantage of, catch, take captive, ensnare, seize epairw: raise up, uplift himself, put on airs, be presumptuous, lord it over someone, exalt himself<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>derw: beat, strike, hit, slap LITERALLY: For you put up with it if anyone enslaves you, if anyone exploit you, if anyone takes advantage of you, if anyone puts himself above you, if anyone slaps you in the face.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ma jang mara, é! Te beta malu, tagal botong noe-noe sa. Te botong sonde mampu bekin bagitu, sama ke itu orang dong su bekin kasi sang bosong.<bt>But don't be angry, é! Cuz (elaboration) I'm ashamed/embarrassed, because we-exc are weak/soft. Cuz (elaboration) we are not capable of doing that, like those people who are dong that to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE: if strong sarcasm isn't clear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">NOTE: if strong sarcasm isn't clear here, consider using the device used in 10:12</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma kalo dong mau omong bésar so'al apa, na, beta ju barani omong bésar bagitu. (Ma jang lupa, te beta ada omong gila na!)<bt>But if they want to boast about something, na, I also dare to boast like that. (But don't forget, I'm talking crazy here na! [+obvious])</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="atimia: dishonor, disgrace, shame asthenew: weak,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">atimia: dishonor, disgrace, shame asthenew: weak, powerless<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>tolmaw: dare, be courageous LITERALLY: I speak to my shame, as though we were weak. Whatever anyone dares to boast of, I am talking as a fool, I also dare [to boast].<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Dong orang Ibrani isi-isi, ko? Hoo! Ko beta ju. Dong orang Isra'el, ko? Hoo! Ko beta ju. Dong tu, ba'i Abraham pung turunan, ko? Hoo! Ko beta ju.<bt>Are they a genuine Ibrani? Hoo! [+yes, affirmation] So am I. Are they an Isra'el person? Hoo! So am I. Are they Gf/Ff Abraham's descendants? Hoo! So am I.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Are they Hebrews? I also."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Are they Hebrews? I also. Are they Israelites? I also. Are they Abraham's descendant? I also.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Dong tu, Kristus pung orang karjá, ko? Hoo! Ko beta ju bagitu. (Jang lupa, te beta ada omong lebe-lebe ni!) Memang beta bilang, beta sama ke dong. Padahal beta ni, lebe dari dong. Te beta karjá lebe karás. Orang lempar buang sang beta pi dalam bui lebe banya. Dong firuk sang beta lebe banya. Beta ju amper mati lebe banya.<bt>Are they Kristus' workers? Hoo! So am I. (Don't forget, cuz I'm talking hyperbole/over the top/excessive here!) Yes, I really did say I was like them. Whereas in fact, I am more than they are. Cuz (elaboration) I work harder. People have thrown me in jail more often. They have whipped me more often. I have nearly died more often.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraphronos: be beside oneself, be crazy,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">paraphronos: be beside oneself, be crazy, be out of one's head kopos: work, toil, labor<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>perissoterws: more phulake: guard, prison<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>plege: blow, stroke, scourge huperballontws: exceedingly<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>pollakis: often LITERALLY: Are they servants of Christ? I speak as a fool, I am more. In labors more, in prisons more, in beatings much more, near death often,<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 16:23</note><v n="24" />Te di beta pung orang Yahudi sandiri pung tangan, dong cambuk sang beta lima kali. Tiap kali beta kaná cambuk tu, dong firuk sampe 39 kali.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in the hand of my own Yahudi people, they whipped me five time. Each time I was whipped, they lashed me 39 times.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pentakis: five times tessarakonta: forty|i(24) (24)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">pentakis: five times tessarakonta: forty<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>LITERALLY: Five times I have received from the Jews forty lashes minus one.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 25:3</note><v n="25" />Ada tiga kali orang papoko sang beta deng kayu. Ada satu kali dong lempar batu ko mau bunu bekin mati sang beta. Ada tiga kali beta pung kapal tanggalám. Beta ada ta'apung di laut dalam satu siang-satu malam.<bt>There were three times people beat me with wood. there was one time they stoned me wanting to kill me. there were three times my ship sank/drowned. I was floating/drifting on the deep sea one day-one night.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ta'apung = floating"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">ta'apung = floating</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rabdizw: beat with a rod hapaks:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">rabdizw: beat with a rod hapaks: once<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>nauagew: experience shipwreck nuxthemeron: a day and a night<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>buthos: depth LITERALLY: Three times I was beaten with rods, once I was stoned, three times I was shipwrecked, a night and a day I have been adrift at sea.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 16:22, 14:19</note><v n="26" />Su ulang-ulang beta jalan jao pi mana-mana. Ada bahaya bam-banya yang bekin beta amper mati. Conto ke: banjer di kali bésar, parampok dong, beta pung orang Yahudi sandiri dong, orang yang bukan Yahudi dong, deng orang yang bekin diri sama ke sodara orang parcaya, padahal dong tipu. Beta ju su amper mati di tenga laut, dalam kota, deng di tampa sunyi.<bt>I have repeatedly travelled far to various places. there were many dangers that made me almost die. For example: floods/flashfloods on big rivers, robbers, my own Yahudi people, non-Yahudi people, and people who made themselves out to be believers, whereas in fact they were deceiving. I have almost died at sea, in the city, and in empty places. [STYLE: reordered to cluster similar categories (types of situations vs. types of locations).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hodoiporia: journey, travel kindunos: danger|i(26) (26)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hodoiporia: journey, travel kindunos: danger<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>potamos: river lestos: robber, bandit<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>genos: nation, race, stock, people eremia: desert, uninhabited, wilderness<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>LITERALLY: in travels often, in danger from rivers, in danger from robbers, in danger from my own people, in danger from Gentiles, in danger in the city, in danger in the wilderness, in danger at sea, in danger from false brothers.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 9:23, 14:5</note><v n="27" />Beta karjá banting tulang, deng beta dapa susa macam-macam. Ada banya kali beta sonde dapa tidor. Beta ju lapar deng aus. Ada banya kali beta sonde dapa makan apa-apa. Parná ju beta sonde ada pung pakean, ko beta kaná dingin mau mati.<bt>I worked my buns off (idiom: worked throwing down bones), and I got various sorts of troubles/difficulties. There were many times I wasn't able to sleep. I have also been hungry and thirsty. There were many times I had nothing to eat. (There have also been times when) I have had no clothes, or/and experienced extreme cold.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kopos: toil, labor, work moxthos: labor,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kopos: toil, labor, work moxthos: labor, exertion, hardship<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>agrupnia: wakefulness, sleepless nights limos: hunger<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>dipsos: thirst nesteia: fasting, without food<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>gumnotes: nakedness, exposure, destitution psuxos: cold<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>LITERALLY: in hard work and hardship, in many sleepless nights, in hunger and thirst, in going without food many times, in cold and exposure,</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Kalo sonde mau itong itu hal dong samua, na, itong bagini sa: te tiap hari beta ada stres, tagal beta ada pikir so'al kotong pung sodara orang parcaya samua yang bakumpul di mana-mana.<bt>If (you) don't want to count all those things, na, then just make note of these: cuz (elaboration) every day I have stress (assimilated loan), because I think/worry about all our-inc sibling believers who are gathered in many places.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xwpis: apart from parektos: outside|i(28) (28)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">xwpis: apart from parektos: outside<span class="Italic">(28) (28) </span>epistasis: pressure, merimna: anxiety, concern, worry, care, distraction<span class="Italic">(28) (28) </span>LITERALLY: Apart from other things, there is the daily pressure on me of my concern for all the churches.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Kalo ada orang yang rasa diri sonde mampu, na, inga sang beta. Te beta ju bagitu. Kalo ada orang yang buju-buju orang parcaya ko iko-iko bekin sala, beta jadi malu, deng jengkel.<bt>If there is someone who feels unable/incapable/inadequate, na, remember me. Cuz (elaboration) I am also like that. If there is a person who persuades/coaxes/cajoles believers to following along doing wrong, I am ashamed, and upset/indignant. [EXEG: “burn”; MC says it means “shame” here, others say “indignant”, some say “angry”, “distressed”; NIC1 “shame and indignation”, ICC1 “shame and distress”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jengkel @@ Can first &amp; second"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">jengkel @@ Can first &amp; second part be made more parallel? @@ already is about as parallel as the Greek, but structurally inadequate (doer verb) and shame (experiencer verb) take different grammatical frames</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asthenew: weak skandalixw: cause to fall|i(29)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">asthenew: weak skandalixw: cause to fall<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>purow: burn, set on fire, be inflamed [with sympathy, readiness to aid/indignation]; also shame LITERALLY: Who is weak, and I do not feel weak? Who is made to fall, and I do not burn?<span class="Italic">(29)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Naa. Kalo beta musti omong bésar, lebe bae beta omong bésar so'al hal-hal yang kasi tunju bilang, beta ni, noe-noe sa. Batúl!<bt>Naa [shift]. If I have to boast, it's better that I boast about things that just show that I am weak/soft. That's right!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If it is necessary to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If it is necessary to boast, I will boast about the things in which I am weak.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Kotong pung Bos Yesus pung Bapa, andia Tuhan Allah, tau beta sonde omong kosong. Itu pantas kalo orang angka puji sang Dia tarús-tarús.<bt>Our-inc Bos Yesus' Father, that is Lord God, knows that I am not lying. It is appropriate if/that people lift praises to Him continually. [EXEG: OV had 2 subjects, whereas Gk has single subject. KTb.] [DISCOURSE/STYLE: Mirroring the typical Jewish side-comment-as-honorific here would be heavy information load and skewed focus in the RLs here. So, yes, it is a bit tacked on as a separate proposition, as in CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The God and Father of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The God and Father of the Lord Jesus knows, who is to be praised forever, that I am not lying.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Conto ke, dolu di kota Damsik, raja Aretas pung gubernor suru orang ko tepa sang beta di kota pung pintu dong, ko dong bisa tangkap ame sang beta.<bt>For example, previously/long ago, in the city of Damsik, king Aretas' gubernor ordered people to ambush me at the city gates/doors, so they could catch/arrest me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ethnarxes: governor phrourew: guard|i(32) (32) |rpiazw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ethnarxes: governor phrourew: guard<span class="Italic">(32) (32) </span>piazw: seize, grasp, take hold of LITERALLY: In Damascus the governor under King Aretas guarded the city to seize me,<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Ma beta pung tamán dong kasi maso sang beta di satu karanjang, ais dong kasi turun sang beta pake tali dari kota pung tembok luar. Jadi beta lolos dari gubernor pung tangan. Inga, te kalo beta sandiri, na, sonde bisa, to?<bt>But my friends put me in a basket, and then they lowered me using a rope from the outer wall of the city. So (consequently), I escaped/got through from the gubernor's hands. Remember/think, cuz if I was on my own, I couldn't do it/have done it, right? [EXEG: Last sentence required by UNS confusion in several groups to make explicit the nature of the link of 32-33 back to 30-31.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lolos"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">lolos</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thuris: window sargane: basket|i(33) (33) |rxalaw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">thuris: window sargane: basket<span class="Italic">(33) (33) </span>xalaw: let down teixos: wall, [city] wall<span class="Italic">(33) (33) </span>ekpheugw: run away, flee, escape LITERALLY: And I was let down in a basket through a window in the wall, and I escaped his grasp.<span class="Italic">(33)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:32-33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 9:23-25</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus lia satu hal, tingka ke dia ada mimpi<bt>Paulus sees something, as if he is dreaming/like he is dreaming</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Kalo bosong mau, na, biar ko beta omong bésar sadiki lai. Padahal omong bésar sonde ada pung guna. Ma beta mau kasi tau sang bosong hal-hal yang kotong pung Bos su kasi tunju sang beta, sama ke dalam mimpi.<bt>If you-pl will let me, na, permit me to boast a little more. Whereas in fact boasting has no use. But I am going to tell you things that our-inc Bos has shown me, like in a dream.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kauxaomai: boast, brag, glory, pride himself"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">kauxaomai: boast, brag, glory, pride himself dei: it is necessary, must<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>sumpherw: help, profitable, gain, expedient, confer a benefit, be advantageous, useful, contribute to epxomai: come, come to, go on<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>optasia: vision apokalupsis: revelation, disclosure, uncovering, laying bare<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: I must boast; indeed, it is not profitable, but I go on to visions and revelations of the Lord.</Message></Annotation><v n="2-4" />Beta kanál satu orang yang ta'ika deng Kristus. Ampa blas taon lalu, ada yang bawa nae sang dia pi langit yang paling tinggi. Ma beta sonde tau, kalo dia nae masi deng dia pung badan, ko, dia pung roh sa yang nae. Cuma Tuhan yang tau. Beta ju tau bilang, waktu dia ta'angka nae pi Tuhan pung Tampa Bagus tu, dia dengar kata-kata yang talalu hebat, sampe-sampe manusia sonde bisa omong.<bt>I know a person who is bound/linked with Kristus. 14 years ago, there was (someone, something) that took him up to the highest heaven. But I don't know if he went up still with his body, or, only just his spirit is what went up. Only God2 knows. I also know that when he was taken up to God2's Beautiful Place, he heard words/message that were so incredible to the point that humans cannot speak/say.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oida: know. He's probably talking about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">oida: know. He's probably talking about himself. etos: year<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>dekatessares: fourteen eite: whether<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>swma: body ektos: outside<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>harpazw: snatch, catch toioutos: such a kind<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>tritos: third LITERALLY: I know a man in Christ who, fourteen years ago, was snatched up to the third heaven, whether in the body I do not know, or out of the body I do not know, God knows.<span class="Italic">(2) (2) (2) (2) (2) (2) (2) (2) </span>xwris: apart from, separated LITERALLY: And I know that such a man--whether in the body, or apart from the body, I don't know, God knows--paradeisos: Paradise arretos: inexpressible, not to be spoken, unutterable, unspeakablehrema: word ekson: possible, lawfullalew: speak, tell, utter, say LITERALLY: that he was snatched into Paradise and heard inexpressible words which are not possible for man to speak.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="su tapisa dari dia pung badan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">su tapisa dari dia pung badan,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="UNS = kata-kata yg menyentuh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">UNS = kata-kata yg menyentuh</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Jadi buat orang macam bagitu, beta mau omong bésar. Ma beta sonde mau omong bésar so'al beta pung diri sandiri. Cuma so'al hal yang beta sonde mampu bekin, baru beta omong bésar bagitu.<bt>So (elaboration) for a person like that, I'm going to boast. But I don't want to boast about myself. Only about things that I am not capable of doing, only then will I boast like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="astheneia: weakness, bodily weakness, infirmity LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">astheneia: weakness, bodily weakness, infirmity LITERALLY: On behalf of such a one I will boast, but I will not boast of myself, except in my weaknesses.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Andekata beta mau omong bésar, beta sonde parlú omong kosong, te beta ada banya hal yang batúl yang beta bisa omong. Ma beta tahan diri sa, ko orang jang pikir bilang, beta lebe hebat dari apa yang dong dengar deng lia dari beta.<bt>If perchance [+hypothetical] I were to boast, I wouldn't need to empty talk/lie, cuz (elaboration) I have many true things that I can say. But I restrain myself, so people don't think that I am greater/more impressive than what they hear and see from me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thelew: wish, desire, want aphrwn: foolish,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">thelew: wish, desire, want aphrwn: foolish, ignorant, lacking soberness of mind<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>aletheia: truth eipon: say<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>pheidomai: refrain, forbear, hold back, spare logizomai: consider, think, reckon, calculate, count, take into account<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>blepw: see LITERALLY: For even if I wish to boast, I will not be foolish, for I speak the truth; but I will hold back, lest anyone think of me beyond what he see me do or hears from me<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng bagitu, orang jang pikir beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Deng bagitu, orang jang pikir beta lebe hebat dari apa yang dong dengar deng lia dari beta, pake dong pung mata deng talinga sandiri.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Lebe-lebe lai, Tuhan su kasi tunju sang beta banya hal yang hebat.<bt>Even more than that, God2 has shsown me many impressive/great things. [EXEG: 7a goes with 12:6; NRSV, NLT, Ex. Summ. HCE.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma beta ju kaná susa, ko biar beta jang sombong. Te setan dong pung bos ada utus dia pung ana bua satu ko maen ganggu tarús sang beta, sama ke ada satu duri yang maen tusu-tusu beta pung badan. Weh! Beta sangsara batúl!<bt>But I have also been effected by trouble/difficulty so that I don't get arrogant. Cuz (elaboration) the boss of the evil spirits has sent/commissioned one of his underlings/angels to keep bothering/harrassing me, just like there is a thorn that keeps poking/piercing my body. Weh! I really suffer/am tormented!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="huperbole: excess, above measure, abundance, extraordinary"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">huperbole: excess, above measure, abundance, extraordinary quality or character apokalupsis: revelation<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>dio: wherefore huperairew: rise up, be exalted, be elated, be lifted up, puffed up, conceited<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>skolops: thorn, splinter, pointed stake sarks: flesh, body, physical<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>aggelos: figurative "messenger" Satanaa: da Devil<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>kolaphizw: strike, hit, whack, beat, torment, hurt, harass, buffet LITERALLY: and by the abundance of revelations. Wherefore, so that I may not be proud, a thorn in the flesh was given me, a messenger of Satan to strike me, so that I may not be proud.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Su tiga kali beta minta ko Tuhan angka buang ini hal dari beta.<bt>Three times already I requested for God2 to take away this thing/matter from me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tris: three times parakalew: appeal to,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">tris: three times parakalew: appeal to, ask, beg, request<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>aphistemi: keep away, make go away, remove, keep away, take away LITERALLY: About this thing, I asked the Lord three times to take it away from me;<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ma Dia manyao sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta kasi tunju Beta pung hati bae sang lu. Itu cukup kasi sang lu. Te waktu lu sadar bilang, iko lu pung kuat sandiri sonde cukup, na, di situ Beta pung kuasa batamba kuat.&gt;&gt; Andia ko beta mau omong bésar tamba, waktu beta sonde mampu bekin satu hal. Te deng bagitu, beta tau bilang, Kristus pung kuasa ada idop di beta.<bt>But He responded to me saying, “I show My goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you-sg. That's enough for you. Cuz (elaboration) when you are aware that according to/by means of your own strength is not enough, na, there (i.e. in that situation) My power/authority increases strength.” That is why I want to boast more/additionally, when I am not able/capable of doing something. Cuz (elaboration) in that way, I know that Kristus' power/authority is living/alive in me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apkew: sufficient, enough telew: to perfect,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">apkew: sufficient, enough telew: to perfect, complete, finish<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>"handle" needs an object; "trouble" is generic enough hedews: gladly<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>episkenow: take up quarters, stay in, rest on, live in LITERALLY: and he said to me, my grace is sufficient for you; my power is perfected in weakness. Therefore, instead I will gladly boast in my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may live in me.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Dia manyao sang beta, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Ma Dia manyao sang beta, bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta kasi tunju Beta pung hati bae sang lu. Itu cukup kasi sang lu. Te Beta pung kuasa batamba kuat, waktu lu sadar, bilang, iko lu pung kuat sandiri sa, sonde cukup.&gt;&gt; Andia ko beta mau omong bésar tamba, waktu beta sonde mampu bekin satu hal. Te deng bagitu, beta tau, bilang, Kristus pung kuasa ada idop di beta.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Andia ko, kalo beta rasa sonde mampu karjá satu hal sandiri, beta pung hati tanáng-tanáng sa. Jadi waktu orang dong omong bekin hina sang beta, ko, bekin susa sang beta, ko, bekin sangsara sang beta, ko, siksa sang beta, tagal beta jadi Kristus pung orang, na, beta pung hati tatáp tanáng sa. Te kalo beta sandiri sonde mampu, na, beta dapa kuasa dari Kristus ko beta mampu bekin itu hal.<bt>That is why, if/when I feel unable/incapable/inadequate to do something on my own, my liver is just calm/settled. So (consequently), when people speak despising me, or, cause trouble/difficulty for me, or, cause suffering for me, or, persecute/torment me, because I am Kristus' person, na, my liver just stays calm. Cuz (elaboration) when I myself am unable, na, I get/obtain power/authority from Kristus so I am able to do that matter.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eudokew: well pleased, glad, take pleasure,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">eudokew: well pleased, glad, take pleasure, happy, content, delight, approve hubresis: shame, insults, reproaches, mistreatment, insulting abuses, violent mistreatments, insolent actions, brawling<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>anagke: torture, mistreated, trouble, hardships, distress, calamity, instruments of torture, anguish, injuries, insults diwgmos: persecution<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>stenoxwria: distresses, suffering, difficulties, agonies, calamities, anguish, trouble LITERALLY: For this reason I am content in weaknesses, in insults, in hardships, in persecutions, in distresses, for Christ's sake, for when I am weak, then I am strong.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus jadi pikiran so'al orang parcaya di Korintus<bt>Paulus worries about the believers in Korintus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Naa, bosong ada idop tingka ke Tuhan sonde parná utus sang beta pi situ. Andia ko, mau sonde mau, tadi beta omong gila sadiki. Dia pung batúl, bosong yang musti omong bésar so'al beta. Beta memang sonde ada pung arti apa-apa. Ma kalo banding beta deng itu &lt;&lt;orang yang talalu hebat dong&gt;&gt; yang bilang Tuhan ada utus sang dong, na, dong tu, sonde lebe hebat dari beta.<bt>Naa, [shift] you-pl are living as if God2 never sent/commissioned me to go there. That is why, like it or not, earlier I spoke a little crazy. In truth, you are the ones who must boast about me. I really am insignificant. But if/when comparing with those “people who are so incredibly impressive” who say God2 has sent/commissioned them, na, they are not greater/more impressive than I. [NOTE: 1st sentence is required for bridging high-level cohesion, explicating link with apostleship issues from “you forced me to”, and following HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ginomai: be, become aphrwn: foolish, ignorant|i(11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">ginomai: be, become aphrwn: foolish, ignorant<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>enagkaw: force, make, drive, compel, make necessary, constrain opheilw: owe, be indebted, be obligated, must [still pending]<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>sunistemi: commend, show approval, present, introduce, recommend husterew: to miss, be behind, lack, inferior, be less than<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>huperlian: exceedingly, chief, beyond measure See 11:5<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: I have been foolish; [but] you forced me; for I ought to have been commended by you. For I am not at all inferior to the superlative apostles, even though I am nothing.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Tiap kali Tuhan utus satu orang ko kasi tau orang so'al Dia, itu orang bekin tanda heran macam-macam pake kuasa, ko kasi tunju bukti bilang, Tuhan yang utus sang dia. Ma jang lupa, te waktu beta ada di bosong pung teng-tenga, beta ju bekin tanda heran bagitu dong. Ma beta karjá bagitu deng sabar tarús sa.<bt>Each time God2 sends/commissions a person to tell people about Him, that person does various sorts of amazing signs using power/authority, to show evidence/ proof that God2 is the one who sent/ commissioned him. But don't forget, cuz when I am in your midst, I also did amazing signs like that. But I worked like that with continual patience.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="semeion: sign, mark, proof, indication, evidence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">semeion: sign, mark, proof, indication, evidence katergazomai: achieve, do, perform, accomplish<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>hupomone: patience, perseverance, endurance, steadfastness, fortitude terasis: wonder, omen, portent, acts that cause wonder, ...amazement, astounding and unusual happening<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>dunamis: miracle, mighty deeds, mighty works, powerful acts LITERALLY: Indeed the signs of an apostle were performed among you in all patience, signs and wonders and miracles.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ma jang mara, é! Cuma ada satu hal sa, yang beta sonde bekin di bosong, yang orang laen ada bekin di jama'at laen. Andia, beta sonde minta ko bosong tanggong ame sang beta.<bt>But don't be angry, é! There is just one thing that I did not do among you, that other people are doing in other congregations. That is, I did not request that you carry (financial) responsibility for me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hessoomai: be less favored, miss out,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hessoomai: be less favored, miss out, be weaker, be inferior, be worse off, be defeated, be overpowered, be discriminated against loipos: other, remainder<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>katanarkaw: burden, bother xarizomai: give freely, forgive<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>adikia: wrongdoing, unfair LITERALLY: For how were you less favored than the remaining churches, except that I myself did not burden you? Forgive me this wrong.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Bagini! Beta su siap datang di bosong kali katiga. Beta sonde parlú bosong tanggong beta pung ongkos idop. Beta ju sonde parlú bosong pung harta. Te iko kotong pung adat, sonde pantas ana kici dong simpan harta kasi dong pung mama-bapa. Yang pantas tu, andia orang tua yang simpan harta kasi dong pung ana-ana. Jadi beta sonde parlú ko bosong simpan harta kasi sang beta, te bosong sama ke beta pung ana-ana! Yang beta parlú tu, andia bosong pung diri deng bosong pung sayang.<bt>It's like this! I'm ready to come to you for the third time. I don't need you to carry (financial) responsibility for my living costs. I also don't need your belongings/possessions. Cuz (elaboration), according to our-inc adat/customs/culture, it is not appropriate for small children to store away possessions for their mother-father. What is appropriate, is for parents to be the ones to store away possessions for their children. So (consequently), I don't need for you to store away possessions for me, cuz (elaboration) you are like my children! What I need is your selves and your love/affection. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. &amp; MC from higher level context and vs. 15. “I want you” = “I want yourselves and your affection”; UNS's drew a blank at consultant check without the explication.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ I want you yourselves, &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">@@ I want you yourselves, &gt; I want your love then add footnote “the original says” Restructured</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hetoimos: be ready katanarkew: burden|i(14) (14)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hetoimos: be ready katanarkew: burden<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>zetew: want, try to obtain, desire to possess, seek goveus: paarents<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>thesaurizw: store up, gather, save, lay up treasure, accumulate money LITERALLY: Look! The third time I am ready to come to you, and I will not be a burden; for I do not want what is yours, but you, for children ought not to store up for their parents, but parents for their children.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta sonde parlú bosong tanggong beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Beta sonde parlú bosong tanggong beta pung ongkos idop. Te beta sonde parlú bosong pung harta. Yang beta parlú tu, andia bosong sandiri. Te, iko kotong pung adat, sonde pantas ana kici dong simpan harta kasi dong pung mama-bapa. Yang pantas tu, andia orang tua yang simpan harta kasi dong pung ana-ana. Jadi, beta sonde parlú ko bosong simpan harta kasi sang beta, te bosong sama ke beta pung ana-ana!</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Beta suka béli barang kasi sang bosong. Beta ju suka karjá banting tulang ko biar bosong bisa idop iko Tuhan pung mau. Kalo beta talalu sayang sang bosong, bosong ju musti sayang bale sang beta bagitu. Jadi akurang ko bosong ada tahan-tahan bosong pung sayang? Sonde pantas, to?<bt>I like to buy things for you. I also like to work hard (idiom) so that you can live according to God2's will. If I love you too much/excessively, you-pl should also love me in return. So (consequently), why is it that you hold back your love? That's not appropriate, right? [STYLE: Ex. Summ. NLT, MC; at consultant check UNS's didn't get the RQ even with the answer given (see \ov below).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hedws: gladly dapanaw: spend, pay expenses|i(15)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">hedws: gladly dapanaw: spend, pay expenses<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>ekdapanaw: be spent, spend completely psuxe: soul, life, self, seat and center of life that transcends the earthly<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>perissoterws: more, more abundantly, so much, greater, increase hesswn: lesser, less, diminish, weaker<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>agapaw: love, cherish LITERALLY: And I gladly will spend and be spent for your souls. If I love you more, am I loved less?<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo beta talalu sayang sang bosong,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Kalo beta talalu sayang sang bosong, kira-kira bosong pung sayang sang beta jadi kurang, ko? Sonde!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ada dari bosong yang mangaku bilang, beta sonde bekin barát sang bosong. Ma ada ju yang bilang, beta jadi orang yang talalu pintar putar-balek deng tipu ame sang bosong, sampe bekin bosong iko beta pung mau.<bt>There are those among you who acknowledge/confess that I have not burdened you. But there are also those who say I am a person who is so clever at deception and trickery, to the point that I make you follow my will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="estw: agree, grant something, granted, let"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">estw: agree, grant something, granted, let it be so katabarew: burden<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>huparxw: be by nature panourgos: clever, crafty, sly, tricky, catch off guard, ready to do anything, up to every trick, unscrupulous, unprincipled, cunning<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>dolos: deceit, trickery, guile, lies, cunning, treachery, fraud lambanw: take, receive, catch, get the better of<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: But granting that I did not burden you; I was tricky, [you say,] and got the better of you by deceit.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Jadi karmana? Kira-kira itu orang dong yang beta kirim pi sang bosong, ada tipu ame sang bosong, ko?<bt>So (consequently), how is it? Perhaps those people who I sent to you, have been tricking you, or (what)?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apestalka: send pleonektew: make a gain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">apestalka: send pleonektew: make a gain of, take advantage of, outwit, defraud, cheat, exploit, seek unlawful gain<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: Did I cheat you by any of those whom I have been sending to you?</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te beta su buju-buju sang Titus ko pi sang bosong. Beta su kirim satu sodara yang laen ko pi deng dia ju. Kira-kira Titus ada tipu ame sang bosong, ko? Sonde, to? Te Titus deng beta ni, satu model. Botong ada karjá hal yang sama, te botong dua pung pikir tu, sama ju.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I kept persuading/coaxing/cajoling Titus to go to you. I also sent another sibling to go with him. Perhaps Titus has been tricking you, or (what)? No, right? Cuz (elaboration) Titus and I are the same sort/type/model. We-exc do the same work, cuz (elaboration) the two of us also think the same. [EXEG: This trip has already happened. See Ex.Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parakalew: implore, beg, urge sunapostellw: send"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">parakalew: implore, beg, urge sunapostellw: send with<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>peripatew: go about, live, behave, act, follow ixnos: footprint, step<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: I urged Titus, an sent the brother with him. Did Titus cheat you? Did we not behave in the same spirit? In the same steps?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Sodara sayang dong! Kira-kira bosong ada pikir dari tadi bilang, botong ada bela diri di bosong pung muka, ko? Sonde! Te samua yang botong omong ni, Tuhan Allah su tau. Jadi botong sonde bisa sambunyi apa-apa dari Dia. Botong ju ada ta'ika deng Kristus. Tagal botong sayang sang bosong, andia ko samua yang botong bekin tu, ada pung maksud ko botong bisa bekin kuat sang bosong.<bt>Dear siblings! Perhaps you have been thinking from earlier, that we-exc are defending ourselves in front of you, or (what)? No! Cuz (elaboration) everything that we are saying here, God already knows. So (elaboration), we can't hide anything from Him. We are also bound/linked with Kristus. Because we-exc love you-pl, that is why everything that we do, is intended for us to strengthen you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="palai: long ago, all along dokew:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">palai: long ago, all along dokew: think<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>apologeomai: defend oneself, make excuse katenanti: in the sight of, in the presence of, before<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>lalew: speak oikodome: building up, help, for your good, edifying<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: Have you been thinking all along that we have been defending ourselves to you? We speak before God in Christ; and all things, beloved ones, for your upbuilding.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Nanti, kalo beta jadi datang di bosong, beta ada pikir-pikir, jang sampe bosong sonde jadi orang yang sama ke beta pung mau. Te jang-jang ada yang bakanjar, iri hati, simpan hati, ada yang cuma pikir dia pung diri sandiri sa, ada yang omong bekin busu orang pung nama bae, ada yang bagosip, ada yang sombong, deng bekin kaco samua. Mangkali beta ju jadi orang yang sonde sama ke yang bosong suka.<bt>Later, if/when it works out for me to come to you-pl, I am thinking/worrying, that perhaps you are not people who are like what I want. Cuz (elaboration) what if there are those who are arguing. jealous, angry/vengeful, there are those who only think about themselves, there are those who speak ruining others' reputations, there are gossips, there are those who are arrogant, and cause all sorts of chaos/disruption. Perhaps/probably I am also a person that is not the same as what you like.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makan hati = jengkel ; camburu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">makan hati = jengkel ; camburu = jealous (usually limited to the context of pacaran)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phobew: be afraid hoios: of what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">phobew: be afraid hoios: of what sort<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>thelw: wish heuriskw: find<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>eris: strife, quarreling zelos: jealousy<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>thumos: anger eritheia: selfishness, factions, divisions<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>katalalia: slander psithurismos: gossip<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>phusiwsis: pride, conceit, arrogance akatastasia: disturbance, disorder<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>LITERALLY: For I fear that perhaps I may come and find you not what I wish, and you may find me not what you wish, but there may be quarreling, jealousy, anger, selfishness, slander, gossip, pride, and disorder;</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Nanti kalo beta datang di bosong, beta jadi pikiran tagal bosong pung bekin-bekin. Jang sampe Tuhan Allah mau bekin beta jadi malu di bosong pung muka. Jang sampe beta bekin orang rasa barát, tagal ada banya dari bosong yang masi idop bekin jahat, ma sonde mau tobat, ko bale iko Tuhan pung jalan lurus. Dong kamomos! Te ada yang maen serong deng orang yang bukan dia pung laki ko dia pung bini. Dong bekin macam-macam deng sonde tau malu.<bt>Later when I come to you, I will be worried because of your behaviour/deeds. May it not be that God is going to make me ashamed/embarrassed in front of you. May it not be that I will make people feel heavy (sad, discouraged, depressed, awkward), because there are many of you who are still living doing evil, but don't want to repent, to turn and follow God2's straight/righteous path/way. They are filthy/defiled! Cuz (elaboration) there are those who play off-track (sexually) with people who are not their husband or wife. They do various sorts of things knowing no shame.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tapeinow: lower ho theos mou: my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">tapeinow: lower ho theos mou: my God<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>penthew: be sad, sorry proamartanw: sin beforehand<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>metanoew: change mind, repent akatharsia: impurity<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>porneia: prostitution, unchastity, fornication, every kind of unlawful sexual intercourse, promiscuity aselgeia: licentiousness, debauchery, sensuality<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>prassw: practice, do LITERALLY: I fear that when I come again my God may humble me before you. I may have to mourn over many who sinned before and have not repented of the impurity, sexual promiscuity, and debauchery they have practiced.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jaga bae-bae bosong pung idop<bt>Guard your lives carefully</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi ini kali katiga yang beta mau pi lia sang bosong. Kalo ada yang mau tudu orang, na, jang lupa dia pung atoran. Te Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo ada yang tudu satu orang, musti ada dua ko tiga saksi yang omong sama dolo, baru tarima. Te kalo sonde bagitu, na, jang tarima.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), this is the third time I want to come see you-pl. If there are those who want to accuse people, na, don't forget the rule/regulation. Cuz (elaboration) the Scriptures write saying, “If there are those who accuse a person, there must be two or three witnesses who say the same thing first, before accepting. Cuz (elaboration) if it is not like that, na, don't accept (it).”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is the third time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is the third time I am coming to you. Any charge must be established by the testimony of two or three witnesses.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 17:6, 19:15</note><v n="2" />Waktu beta pi bosong kali kadua dolu, beta su kasi inga sang itu orang yang idop bekin jahat dong. Sakarang beta kasi inga sang dong lai, sama-sama deng samua orang yang idop bekin jahat dong. Sama ke dolu, beta kasi inga bilang, nanti kalo beta jadi datang, beta sonde kasi biar sang dong.<bt>When I went to you previously the second time, I reminded/warned those people who were living doing evil. Now I remind/warn them again, the same as all people who live doing evil. Just like before, I warn (them) that later if/when it works out for me to come, I will not just let them off/spare them/permit them. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I warned those who sinned"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I warned those who sinned before and all the others, and now I warn them again while absent, as I did when present on my second visit, that if I come again I will not spare them.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu beta pi di bosong kali"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">Waktu beta pi di bosong kali kadua dolu, beta su kasi inga sang bosong. Sakarang beta kasi inga satu kali lai dari jao, bagini: nanti kalo beta jadi datang, beta sonde kasi biar sang itu orang tadi yang idop bekin jahat dong. Ko sambarang orang yang idop bekin jahat tu, awas! (unclear connection?)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Bosong ada cari-cari bukti bilang, Kristus ada omong lewat beta. Naa. Kalo Kristus mau ator ame sang bosong, Dia bekin deng kuasa bésar di bosong pung teng-tenga. Te Dia sonde karjá deng noe-noe.<bt>You-pl are looking for evidence/proof that Kristus speaks by/via me. Naa. [shift, main point] If Kristus is going to handle/take care of/straighten you out, He will do it with great power/authority in your midst. Cuz (elaboration) He does not work weakly/softly. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since you look for proof"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since you look for proof that Christ is speaking in me, who is not weak but powerful among you,</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Waktu dong bunu bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang, memang Dia noe, te Dia su lapás buang Dia pung kuasa. Ma Tuhan Allah su kasi kuasa sang Kristus ko Dia idop sakarang. Ais biar kotong yang jadi Dia pung orang ada rasa sonde mampu, ma Tuhan Allah su kasi kotong idop baru. Andia ko botong bisa layani sang bosong pake Dia pung kuasa.<bt>When they killed Him on the *cross, He really was weak/soft, cuz (elaboration) He had completely released/let go of His power/authority. But God has given power/authority to Kristus for His to live now. So even if/though we-inc who are His people are feeling unable/incapable/inadequate, nevertheless God has given us new life. that is why we-exc are able to serve/minister to you using His power/authority. [EXEG: HCE, Baluchi.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Even though we who are his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">"Even though we who are his disciples are weak, nevertheless God has given us new life through Jesus and we will present ourselves to you with God's power" (Baluchi)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For he was crucified in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For he was crucified in weakness, but he lives by the power of God. For we are weak in him, but in dealing with you we shall live with him by the power of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Pareksa bosong pung hati sandiri-sandiri ko cari tau bilang, bosong ada parcaya batúl sang Kristus, ko sonde. Dia pung kuasa ada kantara di bosong pung idop, ko sonde? Uji sang bosong pung diri bagitu. Te kalo Dia sonde ta'ika deng bosong, bosong sonde jadi Dia pung orang.<bt>Examine your own (individual) livers to find out whether you are really believing in Kristus, or not. Is His power/authority is visible/evident in your lives, or not? Test yourselves like that. Cuz (elaboration) if He is not bound/linked with you-pl, (then) you are not His person/people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@GRAMMAR Complementiser ‘bilang’ as ‘whether’ here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z">@@GRAMMAR Complementiser ‘bilang’ as ‘whether’ here because of semantics of verb</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Examine yourselves to see whether"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Examine yourselves to see whether you are in the faith. Test yourselves. Or do you not know that Christ Jesus is in you? Unless indeed you fail the test.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Kalo bosong pareksa sang botong, na, bosong bisa lia Dia pung kuasa ada kantara di botong pung idop. Deng bagitu, botong lolos.<bt>If/when you examine us-exc, na, you can see His power/authority is visible/evident in our lives. In that way, we pass/come through.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I hope you will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I hope you will find out that we have not failed the test.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Botong ju sambayang minta sang Tuhan Allah, ko biar bosong jang bekin sala apa-apa. Botong sonde pusing kalo orang suka, ko sonde, deng apa yang botong bekin. Ma botong suka ko bosong bekin yang batúl, biar orang saparu mau tola buang sang botong. Bagitu ju, sonde apa-apa.<bt>We-exc also pray requesting God so that you do not do any wrong/sin. We do not care whether people like, or not, what we do. But we like/desire for you to do what is right, even if some people reject us. (Even if) it's like that, it doesn't matter. [NOTE ‘other people’ changed to ‘some people’ May 2011. CR]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But we pray to God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But we pray to God that you may do nothing wrong, not that we may appear to have passed the test, but that you may do what is right, though we may seem to have failed.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te kotong sonde bisa bekin apa-apa ko malawan apa yang batúl. Botong cuma tau bekin yang batúl sa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc can not do anything to oppose what is true. We-exc only know/able to do what is true/correct.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we cannot do anything"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we cannot do anything against the truth, but only for the truth.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Kalo bosong jadi kuat, deng botong jadi noe, botong sanáng sa. Te botong ada sambayang minta ko Tuhan bekin bosong tamba langkáp.<bt>If you-pl become (process) strong, and we-sc become weak/soft, we're just happy. Cuz (elaboration) we have been praying requesting that God2 make you increasingly complete.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we are glad when"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we are glad when we are weak and you are strong. What we pray for is your improvement/perfecting.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Andia ko, biar beta ada jao-jao dari bosong, beta tulis ini hal dong sakarang, ko biar nanti beta pi sana, na, beta sonde usa omong karás sang bosong lai. Beta jadi kotong pung Bos pung utusan. Ma Dia kasi beta hak deng kuasa ko kasi kuat sang bosong, bukan kasi ancor sang bosong.<bt>That is why, even though I am far/distanced from you, I write these things now, so that later when I come, na, I won't need to speak harshly with you anymore. I am our-inc Bos's *apostle (sent/commissioned one). But He gave me the right and power/authority to strengthen you, not to destroy/ruin/fall apart you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore I write these things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore I write these things while I am away from you, that when I come I may not have to be severe in my use of the authority which the Lord has given me for building up and not for tearing down</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus tutu dia pung surat<bt>Paulus closes his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sodara sayang dong! Beta pung kata tarahir ni, salam manis sa. Bekin lurus samua hal. Dengar bae-bae beta pung nasiat. Idop satu hati. Bosong musti babae satu deng satu. Sayang tu, ba'akar di Tuhan Allah. Beta minta ko Dia ada sama-sama deng bosong tarús, deng Dia tolong bosong ko bosong idop badame satu deng satu.<bt>Dear siblings! My final words here, are simply a sweet (warm) greeting. Make everything straight (right, as it should be). Listen carefully (obey) my advice. Live one livered (one accord, same purpose). You must be in reciprocally good/right relationships with each other [eirene = peace, sense #2]. Love is rooted/sourced in God. I request that He be together with you continually, and (that) He help/assist you so you live in peace (relational) with each other. [STYLE: different lexeme for variation; same goal.] [EXEG: Subject of Gk clause is complex “the God of love and peace”; predicate is “will be with you”. In translation, simplified “God will be with you” is easy, but modifying the subject with two abstract nouns (the second of which encompasses 3 senses) makes heavy info load and skewed focus in RLs. Further complication is that with no copulas, equative clauses work with nouns like ‘teacher’, but not with qualities like ‘love’ and ‘peace’. So can we find an equivalent structure not using an equative clause structure? The use of ‘brings’ used in John's writings (living bread, living water, etc.) doesn't work here. Restructured with CR, Amarasi 2014. Reflects all 3 options in Ex.Summ. Can't do the same with polysemous Gk ‘peace’ here. Cf. handling of abstract ‘love’ in 1 Cor 13 and 1 Jn 4:7.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Finally brothers, goodbye. Make everything"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Finally brothers, goodbye. Make everything right. Listen to my appeal. Agree with each other. Live in peace. And the God of love and peace will be with you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Bosong musti batogor pake ciom manis, yang pantas kasi Tuhan pung orang barisi. Tuhan Allah pung orang di sini dong samua ada titip salam manis kasi sang bosong.<bt>You must reciprocally greet using a sweet kiss/sniff, that is appropriate for God2's clean/holy/pure people. All of God's people here send sweet greetings to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Greet each other with a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Greet each other with a holy kiss. All God's people send you their greetings.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Beta minta ko kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong. Beta minta ko Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung sayang sang bosong. Beta ju minta ko Tuhan pung Roh Barisi kasi tunju Dia pung hati manis, ko biar bosong samua idop satu hati.<bt>I request that our-inc Bos Yesus Kristus show His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you-pl. I ask that God show/demonstrate His love to you. I also request that God2's Clean/Holy/Pure Spirit show His kindness/gentleness, so that you all live one livered (one accord, shared purpose, supporting each other).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The grace of the Lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:47Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ and the love of God, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit be with you all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bagitu sa,<bt>That's all,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Paulus<bt>Paulus</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>